<L>&THORN;e vorme &thorn;at he myd spek. wes Marie Maudeleyne.</L>
<L N="555">&THORN;o heo com to his buryles. hyne for to seche.</L>
<L>Heo wende &thorn;at &thorn;e gywes hedde fur-stole vre soule leche.</L>
<L>Marie stod wi&thorn;-vte &thorn;e dure. and sore wepe bi-gon.</L>
<L>&THORN;o heo ne funde nouht ihesu crist. &thorn;et wes hire leof-mon.</L>
<L>He adun stupede. and lokede myd eye.</L>
<L N="560">If heo of vre louerde. ouht &thorn;er iseye.</L>
<L>&THORN;o seyh heo &thorn;er twey engles. myd hwite clo&thorn;es and swote.</L>
<L>&THORN;e on set at &thorn;e heuede. &thorn;e o&thorn;er at &thorn;e vote.</L>
<L>Wymmon hwi wepestu. hi seyden hire to.</L>
<L N="564">For hi habbe&thorn; myne louerd. i not hwer i-do.</L>
<L>Marie hire drouh abak. and lokede heo bi-hynde.</L>
<L>&THORN;o yseyh heo ihesu crist. &thorn;et heo &thorn;er wende vynde</L>
<L>Vre louerd hire gon axi. for hwi and for hwan.</L>
<L N="568">Wepestu. and hwam &thorn;u seche. say me wymmon.</L>
<L>Marie him onswerede. and &thorn;us him seyde to.</L>
<L>&THORN;e gywes habbe&thorn; mynne louerd. of &thorn;isse stude i-do.</L>
<L>Ich not neuer hwydere. hi habbe&thorn; hyne ibrouht.</L>
<L N="572">&THORN;er-vore ich am ful sori. and habbe hyne isouht.</L>
<L>Hauestu hyne awey ibore. seye me gode mon.</L>
<L>And ich hyne vecche wille. al my seolf on.<MILESTONE N="226" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Heo nuste nouht &thorn;at he hit wes. &thorn;et vre bendes to-brek.</L>
<L>Heo wende hit were &thorn;e leyhtunward. &thorn;at to hire spek.</L>
<L N="577">Iesus &thorn;o nemde marie. and cudde hwat he wes.</L>
<L>Marie in hire lyue. neuere so bly&thorn;e nes.</L>
<L>Heo clepede hyne mayster. &thorn;et is rabony.</L>
<L N="580">And fel to his fote. and bed hym mercy.</L>
<L>Ihesuc spek to marie. and hire &thorn;o for-bed.</L>
<L>&THORN;at heo attryne ne scolde. his honde ne his fet.</L>
<L>Ich ne astey nouht yete. vp to myne vadere.</L>
<L N="584">Ac go to myne bro&thorn;ren. &thorn;er hi beo&thorn; to-gadere.
<PB REF="00000070.tif" N="54"></L>
<L>Saye heom &thorn;at ich astye. to mynes vader riche.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is my vader and eke heore. and ioye euer ilyche.</L>
<L>After &thorn;et ihesu crist. myd marie hedde ispeke.</L>
<L N="588">Heo nolde vor none &thorn;inge. his heste &thorn;o to-breke.</L>
<L>Heo com to his disciples. &thorn;er hi to-gadere were.</L>
<L>Neuer of tydinge. hy er so glad nere.</L>
<L>Heo seyde to heom &thorn;e wordes. &thorn;et hire heyhte ihesuc.</L>
<L>And &thorn;at he wes from de&thorn;e aryse. and to me seyde &thorn;us.</L>
<L N="593">&THORN;o hi &thorn;is iherde. hi were swy&thorn;e bly&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;at vre louerd wes aryse. from de&thorn;e to lyue.</L>
<L>As heo stode and speken. and weren at wenynge.</L>
<L N="596">Of vre louerdes aryste. and fele o&thorn;er &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>Vre louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;e wes ibore. of &thorn;e meyde.</L>
<L>He stod amydde heom alle. and to heom &thorn;us seyde.</L>
<L>Sibsumnesse eu beo among. ne beo ye nouht of-dredde.</L>
<L N="600">Ich hit am &thorn;at her bi-vore. eu alle myd me ledde.</L>
<L>Hi weren aferd and offruyht. and no wunder nes.</L>
<L>Heo wenden &thorn;et hit were a gost. &thorn;at a-mong heom wes.</L>
<L>Ihesuc to heom seyde. of hwan beo ye of-ferde.</L>
<L N="604">And beo&thorn; in eure heorte. &thorn;ouhtes fele a-rerde.</L>
<L>Iseo&thorn; nu&thorn;e bo&thorn;e myne v&eacute;t. and ek myne honde.</L>
<L>&THORN;at ich hit am ihesu crist. &thorn;at her myd eu stonde.<MILESTONE N="226b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Hondle&thorn; nv and iseo&thorn;. &thorn;at gost naue&thorn; none bon.</L>
<L N="608">Ne vleys ne bon nou&thorn;er. as me is vp-on.</L>
<L>&THORN;o he hedde so yseyd. he dude more yet.</L>
<L>He schewede heom his honde. and so he dude his fet.</L>
<L>Yet heo hit nyleuede. &thorn;e more ne &thorn;e lesse.</L>
<L N="612">Ac &thorn;uhte muche wunder. of heore gladnesse.</L>
<L>Vre louerd ihesu crist. myd heom bi-gon to speke</L>
<L>Habbe ye ouht here. &thorn;at mon may of ete.</L>
<L>Hi hym bivore brouhten. of one visse ibred.</L>
<L N="616">And ek enne huny-comb. hi weren swi&thorn;e gled.</L>
<L>Vre louerd nom and et &thorn;er-of. to-uore heom euervychone.</L>
<L>And sewede &thorn;at he wes a-ryse. myd fleysse and myd bone.</L>
<L>Aveole kunne wise. vre louerd him tok on.</L>
<L N="620">To schewen his apostles. &thorn;et he wes god and mon.
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="55"></L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e &thorn;at he wes a-ryse. from de&thorn;e to lyue.</L>
<L>&THORN;et vs alle bouhte. myd his wndes fyue.</L>
<L>Ofte he heom myd spek. &thorn;er hi weren to-gedere.</L>
<L N="624">Er he wolde astyen. to heuene to his vedere.</L>
<L>He heyhte heom holde treowe luue. euerych to o&thorn;re.</L>
<L>As ich habbe eu yluued. for ye beo&thorn; alle bro&thorn;re.</L>
<L>Vre louerd heom bleu vp-on. &thorn;et alle &thorn;ing con dyhte.</L>
<L N="628">Vnder-uonge&thorn; he seyde. &thorn;e holigostes myhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;eo &thorn;at ye alese&thorn; here, of heore sunnes bende.</L>
<L>Hi schulle beon vnbunden. euer buten ende.</L>
<L>And &thorn;eo &thorn;at ye her bynde&thorn;. ine lyue &thorn;isse.</L>
<L N="632">Hi beo&thorn; euer ibunde. wyte&thorn; ye myd iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;o vre louerd astye wolde. from eor&thorn;e to heuene</L>
<L>He seyde to his apostles. hi weren elleouene.</L>
<L>Herkne&thorn; alle to me. &thorn;e more and &thorn;e leste.</L>
<L N="636">Ich eu wille senden on. mynes fader biheste.</L>
<L>Sytte&thorn; in &thorn;e burewe. and ich eu wille dihte.</L>
<L>Fort ye beon byweued. of heueliche myhte.<MILESTONE N="227" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>He seo&thorn;&thorn;e heom vt ledde. in-to bethany.</L>
<L N="640">And myd his swete honde. gon heom blessy.</L>
<L>&THORN;o he heom hedde iblessed. &thorn;at scop &thorn;e sunne and mone.</L>
<L>He astey to heuene. &thorn;er-after ful sone.</L>
<L>Hi stoden and biheolden. hw he to heuene asteyh.</L>
<L N="644">Mid his swete moder. he wes hire heorte neyh.</L>
<L>&THORN;er stoden twei veyre men. neren hi nouht ihud.</L>
<L>Ac were myd hwite clo&thorn;es. swy&thorn;e veyre iscrud.</L>
<L>And hi to heom seyden. men of galile.</L>
<L N="648">Toward &thorn;are heuene. hwat bi-holde ye.</L>
<L>&THORN;e ilke sulue ihesuc. &thorn;at is from eu y-nume.</L>
<L>He wile hym sulf eft-sone. hider to ev cume.</L>
<L>Mid fleysse and myd bone. as he heonne ywende.</L>
<L N="652">He wile eft hider cume. &thorn;eos word he eu sende.</L>
<L>&THORN;o heo &thorn;is iherden. hi turnden heom ayeyn.</L>
<L>Mid muchele gladnesse. eft to iherusalem.</L>
<L>And weren in &thorn;e temple. god heryinde.</L>
<L N="656">And &thorn;ene king of heuene. euer blessynde.
<PB REF="00000072.tif" N="56"></L>
<L>At &thorn;on heye vndarne. a wit-suneday.</L>
<L>&THORN;er hi were to-gadere. as ich eu segge may.</L>
<L>And heryeden vre louerd crist. and heore bede sunge.</L>
<L N="660">&THORN;e holy gost heom com vp-on. in fury tunge.</L>
<L>So sone so hi weren. of &thorn;e holy goste attende.</L>
<L>Heo arysen alle to-gadere. and vt heom iwende.</L>
<L>And speken godes wordes. hi weren swi&thorn;e gled.</L>
<L N="664">Of none monne in eor&thorn;e. nere hi &thorn;o of-dred.</L>
<L>&THORN;o were in iherusalem. as ich me vnderstonde.</L>
<L>Men wunyinde. of alle kunnes londe.</L>
<L>&THORN;o heo iherden &thorn;e apostles. godes lore teche.</L>
<L N="668">Eueruych &thorn;er vnderstod. his icunde speche.</L>
<L>Heo seyden heom bi-twenen. hwat may &thorn;is beo.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos men &thorn;at we heren speke. hi beo&thorn; of galile.<MILESTONE N="227b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And we iherden heom heryen. in heore preching.</L>
<L N="672">After vre tunge. &thorn;en heoueliche kyng.</L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e in alle londes. hi eoden vor to prechen.</L>
<L>And for to fully &thorn;at folk. and godes lawe techen.</L>
<L>Hi nolden &thorn;o bileue. vor kayser. ne vor kynge.</L>
<L N="676">Ne vor nore pyne. heore prechynge.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-vore heo iwenden. in-to alle londes.</L>
<L>And fullede kinges. eorles. and bondes.</L>
<L>And alle men and wymmen. &thorn;at wolde to heom cume.</L>
<L N="680">And bileuen on ihesu crist. &thorn;et is godes sune.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-uore &thorn;e veond of helle. hedde muchel onde.</L>
<L>Vor hi by-nomen him saulen. in water. and in londe.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-vore he hine bi-&thorn;ouhte. hw he don myhte.</L>
<L N="684">And euer wes abute. bi daye. and bi nyhte.</L>
<L>Vor bryngen heom to de&thorn;e. &thorn;et spek myd his y-corene.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wes. Nerun. and Dacyen. and mo &thorn;et beo&thorn; vor-lorene.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos n&oacute;men &thorn;e apostles. and heom to de&thorn;e dude.</L>
<L N="688">And vre louerd heom vnderveng. a-non i &thorn;e stude.</L>
<L>Nv hi beo&thorn; ine blisse. myd &thorn;on heuene kynge.</L>
<L>&THORN;at is heore mede. vor heore prechinge.</L>
<L>Bidde we alle ihesu crist. vor heore erndinge.</L>
<L N="692">&THORN;at he vre saule. to &thorn;are blisse brynge.
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="57"></L>
<L>Vor his swete moder luue. of hwam he vleyss nom.</L>
<L>He habbe mercy of vs. &thorn;at is god and mon.</L>
<L>And lete vs so her libben. in &thorn;isse wrecche lyue.</L>
<L N="696">&THORN;at we moten to him cume. for his wundes fyue.</L>
<L>And he &thorn;at haue&thorn; &thorn;is rym iwryten. beo hwat he beo.</L>
<L>God in &thorn;isse lyue. hyne lete wel i&thorn;eo.</L>
<L>And alle his iveren. bo&thorn;e yonge and olde.</L>
<L N="700">God heom lete heore ordre. trewliche her holde.</L>
<L>&THORN;at hi mote to-gadere cume. to heueriche blysse.</L>
<L>Hwanne hi schullen to-party. vt of lyue &thorn;isse.<MILESTONE N="228" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>He &thorn;et alle &thorn;ing ischop. &thorn;is vs graunty.</L>
<L N="704">Vor his leue moder luue. seynte Mary.</L>
<L>And heo vre erende bere. so is hire ywune.</L>
<L>Mid alle o&thorn;er halewe. to hire swete sune. AmeN.
</L>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="2" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000074.tif" N="58">
<HEAD>II. A Moral Ode. [<I>Same MS, leaf</I> 242.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Tractatus quidam in anglico.</HEAD>
<L>Ich am eldre &thorn;an ich wes a winter and ek on lore.</L>
<L>Ich welde more &thorn;an ich dude. my wyt auhte beo more.</L>
<L>Wel longe ich habbe child ibeo. a werke and eke on dede.</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;ah ich beo of wynter old. to yong ich am on rede.</L>
<L>Vnned lif ich habbe ilad. and yet me &thorn;ink&thorn; ich lede.</L>
<L>Hwenne ich me bi&thorn;enche. ful sore ich me adrede.</L>
<L N="7">Mest al &thorn;at ich habbe idon. is idelnesse and chilce.</L>
<L>Wel late ich habbe me bi-&thorn;ouht. bute god do me mylce.</L>
<L>Veole idel word ich habbe ispeke. seo&thorn;&thorn;e ich speke cu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>And feole yonge deden ido. &thorn;at me of-&thorn;inche&thorn; nu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Al to l&oacute;me ich habbe agult. on werke and on worde.</L>
<L>Al to muchel ich habbe i-spend. to lutel i-leyd an horde.</L>
<L N="13">Best al &thorn;at me likede er. nv hit me mys-lyke&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;e muchel folewe&thorn; his wil. him seolue he bi-swike&thorn;.</L>
<L>Mon let &thorn;i fol lust ouer-go. and eft hit &thorn;e like&thorn;.</L>
<L N="16">Ich myhte habbe bet i-do. heuede ich eny selh&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Nv ich wolde and i ne may. for elde. ne for vnhelh&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Elde is me bi-stolen on. er &thorn;an ich hit wiste.</L>
<L>Ne may ich bi-seo me bi-fore. for smoke ne for myste.</L>
<L N="20">Erewe we beo&thorn; to donne g&oacute;d. vuel al to &thorn;riste.
<PB REF="00000075.tif" N="59"></L>
<L>More eye stonde&thorn; mon of mon. &thorn;an him to cryste.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wel ne do&thorn; hwile he may. hit schal him sore reowe.</L>
<L>Hwenne alle men repen schule. &thorn;at heo ear seowe.</L>
<L N="24">Dod to gode &thorn;at ye Muwen. &thorn;e hwile ye beo&thorn; alyue.</L>
<L>Ne lipne no mon to muchel. to childe. ne to wyue.</L>
<L>&THORN;e him seolue for-yet. for wiue. o&thorn;er for childe.</L>
<L>He schal cumen on vuele stude. bute god him beo Milde.</L>
<L N="28">Sende vch sum god bivoren him. &thorn;e hwile he may to heouene.</L>
<L>Betere is on almes bi-uoren. &thorn;ane beo&thorn; after seouene.</L>
<L>Ne beo &thorn;e leouere &thorn;an &thorn;i seolf. &thorn;i mey ne &thorn;i mowe.</L>
<L>Sot is &thorn;at is o&thorn;er mannes freond. more &thorn;an his owe.</L>
<L N="32">Ne lipne no wif to hire were. ne were to his wyue.</L>
<L>Beo vor him seolue vych mon. &thorn;e hwile he beo&thorn; alyue.</L>
<L>&THORN;is<NOTE PLACE="foot">Read <I>Wis</I>.</NOTE> is &thorn;at him seolue bi&thorn;enk&thorn;. &thorn;e hwile he mot libbe.</L>
<L>Vor sone wille&thorn; him for-yete &thorn;e fremede and &thorn;e sibbe.<MILESTONE N="242b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="36">&THORN;e wel nule do hwile he may. ne schal he hwenne he wolde.</L>
<L>Mony monnes sore iswynk. ofte habbe&thorn; vnholde.</L>
<L>Ne scholde nomon don a virst. ne slakien wel to donne.</L>
<L>Vor mony mon bihote&thorn; wel. &thorn;at hit for-yete&thorn; sone.</L>
<L N="40">&THORN;e mon &thorn;at wile syker beo. to habbe godes blysse.</L>
<L>Do wel him seolf &thorn;e hwile he may. &thorn;enne haue&thorn; he hit myd iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos riche men wene&thorn; to beon syker. &thorn;urh walles and &thorn;urh diche.</L>
<L>Ah heo do&thorn; heore ayhte in siker stude. &thorn;at sende&thorn; hit to heoue-riche.</L>
<L N="44">Vor &thorn;er ne &thorn;arf. he beon adred. of fure ne of &thorn;eue.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar ne may hit bynyme. &thorn;e lo&thorn;e ne &thorn;e leoue.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ne &thorn;arf he beon of-dred. of yefte. ne of yelde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ider we sende&thorn; and seolf bere&thorn;. to lutel and to selde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ider we schulde drawen and don. wel ofte and il&oacute;me.</L>
<L N="49">Ne may &thorn;er non hit vs bynymen. myd wrongwise dome.
<PB REF="00000076.tif" N="60"></L>
<L>&THORN;ider we schulden drawen and don. wolde ye me ileue.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;er ne may hit vs by-nyme. &thorn;e king. ne &thorn;e schirr&eacute;ue.</L>
<L N="52">Al &thorn;e beste &thorn;at we habbe&thorn;. &thorn;ider we schulde sende.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;er we hit myhte vinden eft. and habben .o. buten ende.</L>
<L>He &thorn;at her do&thorn; eny god. to habbe godes ore.</L>
<L>Al he schal vynde &thorn;er. an hundred folde more.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at ayhte wile holde wel. &thorn;e hwile he may him wolde.</L>
<L>Yeue hit for godes luue. &thorn;enne do&thorn; he hit wel iholde.</L>
<L N="58">Vre swynk and vre tyleh&thorn;e. is iwuned to swynde.</L>
<L>Ah heo &thorn;at hit yeue&thorn; for godes luue. eft hit mowen ivynde.</L>
<L>Ne schal non vuel beon vn-bouht. ne no god vn-vor-gulde.</L>
<L>Vuel we do&thorn; al to muchel. god; lasse &thorn;ane we scholde.</L>
<L N="62">&THORN;e &thorn;at mest do&thorn; nv to g&oacute;de. and te &thorn;e leste to la&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Ey&thorn;er to lutel and to muchel. schal &thorn;unchen heom ef[t] to ba&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;er me schal vre werkes weyen by-vore heouene kinge.</L>
<L>And yeuen vs vre swynkes lean. after vre earnynge.</L>
<L>Everuych mon myd &thorn;at he haue&thorn;. may bugge heoueriche.</L>
<L N="67">&THORN;e riche and &thorn;e poure bo&thorn;e. ah nouht alle ilyche.</L>
<L>&THORN;e poure. myd his penye. &thorn;e riche myd his punde.</L>
<L>&THORN;at is &thorn;e wunderlicheste ware. &thorn;at euer was ifunde.</L>
<L>And ofte god con more &thorn;onk. ye &thorn;at yue&thorn; him lasse.</L>
<L>Alle his werkes. and his yeftes. is in ryhtwisnesse.<MILESTONE N="243" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="72">Lvtel lok is gode leof. &thorn;at cume&thorn; of gode wille.</L>
<L>And lutel he let on muchel wowe. &thorn;er &thorn;e heorte is ille.</L>
<L>Heouene and eor&thorn;e he ouer-syh&thorn;. his eyen beo&thorn; so brihte.</L>
<L>Sunne. and Mone. heuene. and fur. beo&thorn; &thorn;eostre. ayeyn his lyhte.</L>
<L N="76">Nis him for-hole nowiht. ne ihud. so muchele beo&thorn; his myhte.</L>
<L>Nis no so derne dede idon. in so &thorn;eostre nyhte.</L>
<L>He wot hwat &thorn;enche&thorn;. and hwat do&thorn;. alle quyke wyhte.</L>
<L>Nis no louerd such is crist. ne king. such vre dryhte.
<PB REF="00000077.tif" N="61"></L>
<L N="80">Heouene and eor&thorn;e. and al &thorn;at is. biloken is. in his honde.</L>
<L>He do&thorn; al &thorn;at his wille is. a watere. and eke on londe.</L>
<L>He makede fysses in &thorn;e sea. and fuweles in &thorn;e lufte.</L>
<L>He wit and wald alle &thorn;ing. and schop alle schafte.</L>
<L N="84">He wes erest of alle &thorn;ing. and euer by&thorn; buten ende.</L>
<L>He is on ewiche stude. wende hwer &thorn;u wende.</L>
<L>He is buuen and bi-ne&thorn;en. bi-voren vs and bi-hinde.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at godes wille do&thorn;. ichwer may him fynde.</L>
<L N="88">Hvych rune he iher&thorn;. &thorn;e wot alle dede.</L>
<L>He &thorn;urh-syh&thorn;. vych monnes &thorn;onk. wy hwat schal vs to rede.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at breke&thorn; godes hes. and gulte&thorn; so il&oacute;me.</L>
<L>Hwat schulle we seggen o&thorn;er don. at &thorn;e muchele dome.</L>
<L N="92">&THORN;e &thorn;at luue&thorn; vnryht. and heore lif. vuele lede&thorn;.</L>
<L>We &thorn;at neuer god ne duden. &thorn;en heueneliche deme&thorn;.</L>
<L>Hwat schulle seggen o&thorn;er don. &thorn;er engles heom drede.</L>
