<L N="312">And of alle vre sunnen. vs lete cume to bote.</L>
<L>Vve wilne&thorn; after worldes ayhte. &thorn;at longe ne may ileste.</L>
<L>And mest legge&thorn; vre swynk. on &thorn;ing vnstudeueste.</L>
<L>If &thorn;at we swunken for gode. half. &thorn;at we do&thorn; for eyhte.</L>
<L>Nere we nouht so ofte bi-cherd. ne so vuele by-&thorn;ouhte.</L>
<L N="317">Yef we seruede god. so we do&thorn; earmynges.</L>
<L>We Mihte habbe more of heouene. &thorn;an eorles o&thorn;er kynges.</L>
<L>Ne mowe nouht weryen heom. wi&thorn; chele ne wi&thorn; hunger.</L>
<L N="320">Ne wi&thorn; elde ne wi&thorn; de&thorn;e. &thorn;e eldure ne &thorn;e yonge.</L>
<L>Ah &thorn;er nys hunger. ne &thorn;urst. ne de&thorn;. ne vnhel&thorn;e ne elde.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;is world we &thorn;enche&thorn; ofte; and &thorn;er-of al to selde.</L>
<L>Vve schulde vs bi-&thorn;enche. wel ofte and wel il&oacute;me.</L>
<L N="324">Hwat we beo&thorn;. to hwan we schulen. and of hwan we comen.</L>
<L>Hw lutle hwile we beo&thorn; here. hw longe elles-hware.</L>
<L>And after gode wel wurche. &thorn;enne ne &thorn;uruue noht kare.</L>
<L N="327">If we were wyse men. &thorn;us we schulde &thorn;enche.</L>
<L>Bute we wur&thorn;e vs iwar. &thorn;es world vs wile for-drenche.</L>
<L>Mest alle men he yeue&thorn; drynke. of one deofles [schenche.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS reads: <I>senthe</I>, in a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L N="330">He schal him cunne schilde wel. yef he him. [wole bi-&thorn;en che.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS reads: <I>wole bi-yenthe</I>, in a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mid almyhtyes godes luue. vte we vs werie.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; &thorn;eos wrecche worldes luue. &thorn;e heo vs ne derye.</L>
<L>Mid festen. and almesse and beoden. were we vs wi&thorn; sunne.<MILESTONE N="247" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000086.tif" N="70"></L>
<L N="334">Mid &thorn;e wepnen &thorn;at god haue&thorn; yeuen. to alle monkunne.</L>
<L>Lete we &thorn;eo brode stret. and &thorn;ene wey grene.</L>
<L>&THORN;at lat &thorn;e nye&thorn;e to helle. of folke. and mo ich wene.</L>
<L>Go we &thorn;ene narewe wey. &thorn;ene wey so schene.</L>
<L N="338">&THORN;er for&thorn; fare&thorn; lutel folk. and &thorn;at is wel e&thorn;-sene.</L>
<L>&THORN;e brode stret is vre wil. &thorn;at is vs lo&thorn; to lete.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at al felewe&thorn; his wil. he fare&thorn; &thorn;e brode strete.</L>
<L>&THORN;e narewe wey is godes heste. &thorn;at for&thorn; fare&thorn; wel fawe.</L>
<L>&THORN;at beo&thorn; &thorn;eo. &thorn;e heom schede&thorn; wel. wi&thorn; vych vn&thorn;ewe.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos go&thorn; vnne&thorn;e ayeyn &thorn;e cleo. ayeyn &thorn;e heye hulle.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos lete&thorn; awei al heore wil. for godes hestes to fulle.</L>
<L N="345">Go we alle &thorn;ene wei. for he vs wile brynge.</L>
<L>Mid &thorn;e fewe feyremen by-uoren heouene kinge.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is alre Mureh&thorn;e mest. myd englene songe.</L>
<L>Wel edy wur&thorn; &thorn;ilke mon. &thorn;at &thorn;er by&thorn; vnderuonge.</L>
<L N="349">&THORN;e lest haue&thorn; mureh&thorn;e. he haue&thorn; so muche. ne bit he namore.</L>
<L>Hwo so &thorn;eo blisse for &thorn;isse foryet. hit may him rewe sore.</L>
<L>Ne may no pyne ne no wone beon in heouene riche.</L>
<L N="352">&THORN;ah &thorn;er beon wonynges feole. and o&thorn;er vnyliche.</L>
<L>Summe habbe&thorn; lasse Mureh&thorn;e. and summe habbe&thorn; more.</L>
<L N="354">Vych after &thorn;at he dude her. and after &thorn;at heo swunken sore.</L>
<L>Ne wr&thorn; &thorn;er bred ne wyn. ne nones kunnes este.</L>
<L>God one schal beon eche lif. and blisse eche reste.</L>
<L>&THORN;er nys nou&thorn;er fou ne grey. ne konyng. ne hermyne.</L>
<L N="358">Ne oter. ne acquerne. Beuveyr ne sablyne.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;er ne wur&thorn; ful iwis. worldes wele none.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;e Mureh&thorn;e &thorn;at me vs bihat; al hit is god one.</L>
<L>Nis &thorn;er no Mureh&thorn;e so muchel. so is godes syhte.</L>
<L N="362">He is so&thorn; sunne. and briht. and day bute nyhte.</L>
<L>He is vyche godes sul. nys him nowiht wi&thorn;-vte.</L>
<L>Nis heom nones godes wone; &thorn;at wune&thorn; hym abute.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is weole bute wone. and reste bute swynke.<MILESTONE N="247b" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="71"></L>
<L N="366">Hwo may &thorn;ider cume and nule. hit schal hym sore of|&thorn;inche.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is blysse bute teone. and lif wi&thorn;-vte de&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;eo &thorn;at schulle wunye &thorn;er. bli&thorn;e mvwen heo beon e&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is yonghede buten ealde. and hele buten vnhel&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="370">&THORN;er nys seorewe ne no sor. neuer non vnhel&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e me dryhten iseo. so he is myd iwisse.</L>
<L>He one may beon and schal. englene and monne blisse.</L>
<L N="373">&THORN;eo schulen of him more iseon. &thorn;at her him luuede more.</L>
<L>And more iseon and iwyten. his Milce and his ore.</L>
<L>On him heo schullen fynden. al &thorn;at mon may luste.</L>
<L>And on lyues bec<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS bee.</NOTE> iseon. al &thorn;at heo her nusten.</L>
<L N="377">Crist seolf one schal beon. i-nouh to alle derlinges.</L>
<L>He one is more and betere. &thorn;an alle wordliche &thorn;inges.</L>
<L>Inouh hi habbe&thorn; &thorn;at hyne habbe&thorn;. &thorn;at alle &thorn;inges welde&thorn;.</L>
<L>Him to seonne murie hit is. so fayr he is to biholde.</L>
<L N="381">God is so swete and so muchel. in his godnesse.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at wes and is. is wel wurse and lasse.</L>
<L>Ne may nomon hit segge. ne wyten myd iwisse.</L>
<L N="384">Hu muchele Mureh&thorn;e habbe&thorn; heo. &thorn;at beo&thorn; in heuene blisse.</L>
<L>To &thorn;are blisse bringe vs god. &thorn;at leste&thorn; buten ende.</L>
<L>Hwenne he vre saule vn-bind. of lichomliche bende.</L>
<L>Crist vs lete such lif lede. and habbe her such ende.</L>
<L N="388">&THORN;at we mote to him cume. hwenne we heonne wende&thorn;. Amen.</L>
<L>Bidde we nu leoue freond. yonge and ek olde.</L>
<L N="390">&THORN;at he &thorn;at &thorn;is wryt wrot. his saule beo &thorn;er atholde. Amen.
</L>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="3" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000088.tif" N="72">
<HEAD>III. Sinners Beware! [<I>Same MS, leaf</I> 248.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eos holy gostes myhte.</L>
<L>Vs helpe. and rede and dihte.</L>
<L>And wisse vs and theche.</L>
<L N="4">To wyten vs wy&thorn; &thorn;an vnwihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;at bi daye and bi nyhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;enche&thorn; vs to bi-peche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He make&thorn; vs don sunnen.</L>
<L N="8">And habben of mon-kunne.</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e muchel onde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;enche&thorn; vs i-wynne.</L>
<L>And wunye vs wi&thorn;-Inne.</L>
<L N="12">And vs habben an honde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ac bidde we crist yorne.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he. &thorn;at heom werne.</L>
<L>For his holynesse.</L>
<L N="16">For &thorn;e &thorn;at to heom turne&thorn;.</L>
<L>In helle heo schulle for-berne.</L>
<L>On eche sorynesse.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah ich hit segge and swerie.</L>
<L N="20">If we vre suppen herye.</L>
<L>And luuye&thorn; hyne swi&thorn;e.</L>
<L>He vs wille werye.</L>
<L>&THORN;at feondes vs ne derye.</L>
<L N="24">&THORN;at fulle beo&thorn; of ny&thorn;e.
<PB REF="00000089.tif" N="73"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne schulle we nouht beo here.</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e vale yere.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i er we wende.</L>
<L N="28">Makie we us clene and skere.</L>
<L>&THORN;at we englene ivere.</L>
<L>Mawe beon o buten ende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;at is in heouene blysse.</L>
<L N="32">Heo cume&thorn; &thorn;er myd iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;at luuye&thorn; godes lore.</L>
<L>Hwo &thorn;at for lyue &thorn;isse.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-of schal mysse.</L>
<L N="36">Hit schal him reowe sore.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hit sey&thorn; in &thorn;e godspelle.</L>
<L>Ne may no tunge telle.</L>
<L>&THORN;e blisse &thorn;at &thorn;er is euere.</L>
<L N="40">Ne of &thorn;are pyne of helle.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-to we beo&thorn; to snelle.</L>
<L>A-way. heo ne ende&thorn; neuere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN helle beo&thorn; &thorn;e pynen.</L>
<L N="44">&THORN;at make&thorn; heorte chynen.</L>
<L>&THORN;e stude is swi&thorn;e vnvele.</L>
<L>&THORN;er no lyht ne shine&thorn;</L>
<L>Ne non. o&thorn;er at-tryne&thorn;.</L>
<L N="48">To helpe ne to hele.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Her is chele and hete.<MILESTONE N="248b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And hunger vnymete.</L>
<L>And &thorn;urst elles to kene.</L>
<L N="52">Wikede<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS Pikede.</NOTE> beo&thorn; &thorn;e sete.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e wurmes eke.</L>
<L>&THORN;at do&thorn; &thorn;e saule teone.
<PB REF="00000090.tif" N="74"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;ar is wop and wonynge.</L>
<L N="56">And muche bymenynge.</L>
<L>&THORN;at heo ibore were.</L>
<L>And &thorn;ar nys no yeyn-cherrynge.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;ar nys non endynge.</L>
<L N="60">&THORN;e enes cume&thorn; &thorn;ere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;i we auhte nyme gome.</L>
<L>Her. er we. &thorn;ider c&oacute;me.</L>
<L>And serue heouene kinge.</L>
<L N="64">Bisechen hym ilome.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he vs at &thorn;e dome.</L>
<L>From &thorn;are pyne vs brynge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vte we sunnen lete.</L>
<L N="68">And nyme scryf[t] and b&eacute;te.</L>
<L>Of vre Misdede.</L>
<L>To donne he beo&thorn; swete.</L>
<L>&THORN;y vs. is. e&thorn;-gete.</L>
<L N="72">Helle &thorn;at is vnlede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eo seuen heaued-sunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;at we ofte beo&thorn; inne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e saule wille&thorn; amerre.</L>
<L N="76">Heo beo&thorn; of swikele kunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-myd &thorn;e wy&thorn;erwynne.</L>
<L>Vs alle &thorn;enche&thorn; bicharre.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>PRude and modynesse.</L>
<L N="80">Ne arhhede ne sorynesse.</L>
<L>And ny&thorn;e and ek onde.</L>
<L>Wra&thorn;&thorn;e and swikelnesse.</L>
<L>Hordom and yuernesse.</L>
<L N="84">&THORN;eos we auhte vnderstonde.
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="75"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eos beo&thorn; sunnen seouene.</L>
<L>&THORN;at brynge&thorn; vt of heouene.</L>
<L>Swi&thorn;e vele manne.</L>
<L N="88">&THORN;e weyes beo&thorn; vn-euene.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; wepynde stefne.</L>
<L>To helle he schulle &thorn;enne.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv wene&thorn; monye riche.</L>
<L N="92">To beon englene ilyche.</L>
<L>For heore prude cla&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-fore heo schule siche.</L>
<L>And in helle smyche.</L>
<L N="96">Acoryen hit ful wra&thorn;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He wene&thorn; for heore ayhte.<MILESTONE N="249" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>To heouene beo cu&thorn;lehthe.</L>
<L>Ah bute heo hit ryht dele.</L>
<L N="100">Of heouene heo beo&thorn; bipahte.</L>
<L>And &thorn;ane ueonde by-cauhte.</L>
<L>For heore muche weole.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv wene&thorn; ek &thorn;es wrecche.</L>
<L N="104">&THORN;at he ne &thorn;urue recche.</L>
<L>For he ayhte nabbe&thorn;.</L>
<L>Ac sathanas &thorn;e frecche.</L>
<L>&THORN;e saule wule drecche.</L>
<L N="108">Hwanne he agult habbe&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e ryche myd iwisse.</L>
<L>Wel myhte cume to blisse.</L>
<L>If he hit wolde of-seruie.</L>
<L N="112">&THORN;e poure may wel mysse.</L>
<L>Bute he his pouernesse.</L>
<L>Mid mylde heorte &thorn;olye.
<PB REF="00000092.tif" N="76"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;es Munekes wene&thorn; summe.</L>
<L N="116">&THORN;at gedere&thorn; gersumme.</L>
<L>&THORN;at heo hit schulle bruke.</L>
<L>Ah hwen de&thorn; schal cume.</L>
<L>Al hit wur&thorn; heom bi-nume.</L>
<L N="120">And he bitauht &thorn;e puke.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e preost &thorn;at singe&thorn; masse.</L>
<L>For his yuernesse.</L>
<L>And for owe &thorn;inge.</L>
<L N="124">Bute he do almesse.</L>
<L>In eche sorinesse.</L>
<L>His saule he may brynge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;es knyhtes beo&thorn; so bolde.</L>
<L N="128">Hwenne heo habbe&thorn; aquolde.</L>
<L>Heore crystene iv&eacute;re.</L>
<L>Ah sathanas &thorn;e olde.</L>
<L>&THORN;e saule wule at-holde.</L>
<L N="132">And makie heo vnfere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eos playdurs beo&thorn; wel kene.</L>
<L>&THORN;at werie&thorn; red and grene.</L>
<L>And al &thorn;is vnriht deme&thorn;.</L>
<L N="136">Ho schule &thorn;ah heo ne wene.</L>
<L>In helle habben teone.</L>
<L>&THORN;er as feondes reme&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;es chapmen monye bi str&eacute;te.</L>
<L N="140">Beo&thorn; swi&thorn;e vnymete.</L>
<L>Ne recche&thorn; hwat hi swerie.</L>
<L>Bute heo habben biy&eacute;te.</L>
<L>&THORN;i sathanas &thorn;e kete.</L>
<L N="144">&THORN;e saule wule derye.
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="77"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Of alle men a londe.<MILESTONE N="249b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Mest swynke&thorn; &thorn;e bonde.</L>
<L>And mest biyet myd ryhte.</L>
<L N="148">If he hit cu&thorn;e vnderstonde.</L>
<L>And theo&thorn;e ryht vnder his honde.</L>
<L>To heouene he cume myhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah for al his sore swynke.</L>
<L N="152">In helle he may adrynke.</L>
<L>If he stele&thorn; cristes theo&thorn;inge.</L>
<L>Sur hit schal him &thorn;inche.</L>
<L>Deop in helle stunche.</L>
<L N="156">His saule he may bringe.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eos prude leuedies.</L>
<L>&THORN;at luuye&thorn; drywories.</L>
<L>And breke&thorn; spusynge.</L>
<L N="160">For heore lecherye.</L>
<L>Nulle&thorn; here sermonye.</L>
<L>Of none gode &thorn;inge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Heo drawe&thorn; heore wede.</L>
<L N="164">Mid seolkene &thorn;rede.</L>
<L>Ilaced and ibunde.</L>
<L>Ah he &thorn;at beo&thorn; nv lea&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Remen heo schule and grede.</L>
<L N="168">Deope in helle grunde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mvnekes and Nunnen.</L>
<L>&THORN;at heom wyte ne kunnen.</L>
<L>From sucche lecherye.</L>
<L N="172">Heo schule to helle cume.</L>
<L>Alle heore clo&thorn;es buue.</L>
<L>Ne schule heom warantye.
<PB REF="00000094.tif" N="78"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>So&thorn;liche betere heom were.</L>
<L N="176">&THORN;at heo ibore n&eacute;re.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne &thorn;ider schulen w&eacute;nde.</L>
<L>So&thorn; is &thorn;at ich eu l&eacute;re.</L>
<L>Hwo so enes cume&thorn; &thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="180">He wr&thorn; &thorn;er buten ende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah we wene&thorn; lyuie.</L>
<L>And longe sunegie.</L>
<L>And eft at &thorn;on ende.</L>
<L N="184">Alle vre sunnen endye.</L>
<L>Bi-wepen and bi-reusye.</L>
<L>And so to heouene wende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah ne beo nouht to &thorn;ryste.</L>
<L N="188">Ne &thorn;er-to nouht ne truste.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-vppon ich eu lere.</L>
<L>For nes non &thorn;at wiste.</L>
<L>Bute him seolue criste.</L>
<L N="192">Hwenne his ende-day were.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>So&thorn;liche hwenne we beo&thorn; dede.</L>
<L>Euerych schal vo &thorn;e mede.<MILESTONE N="250" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>After his ernynge.</L>
<L N="196">Bute we vs bi-rede.</L>
<L>&THORN;e gost hit schal ivrede.</L>
<L>And fare&thorn; to pynynge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne bali me bynde&thorn;.</L>
<L N="200">On here me hyne bi-winde&thorn;.</L>
<L>And brynge&thorn; hine on eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wurmes hine ifynde&thorn;.</L>
<L>To axe heo hyne grynde&thorn;.</L>
<L N="204">&THORN;ar-to we schule iwur&thorn;e.
<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="79"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He ly&thorn; and rote&thorn; lowe.</L>
<L>Naue&thorn; he &thorn;at beo his owe.</L>
<L>Of ayhte ne of londe.</L>
<L N="208">Ne naue&thorn; he mey ne mowe.</L>
<L>&THORN;at durre one &thorn;rowe.</L>
<L>Bi hym sitte ne stonde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>So&thorn;liche nakede and bare.</L>
<L N="212">Wi&thorn; wope and wi&thorn; kare.</L>
<L>We come to &thorn;isse lyue.</L>
<L>Al so we schule fare.</L>
<L>And al vre prude &thorn;are.</L>
<L N="216">Vor-leten and bileuen.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Her-of we owe &thorn;enche.</L>
<L>And vre sunnen aquenche.</L>
<L>Mid beden and myd almesse.</L>
<L N="220">And cunnen at-blenche.</L>
<L>From sathanases wrenche.</L>
<L>And from his swikelnesse.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;ah we beon falle in sunne</L>
<L N="224">Ne ligge we noht &thorn;er-inne.</L>
<L>Ah ute we vp aryse.</L>
<L>And schenden vre wy&thorn;erwine.</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;enche&thorn; vs to bi-gynne.</L>
<L N="228">&THORN;enne do&thorn; we as &thorn;e wise.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vte we leten vs schryue.</L>
<L>And &thorn;ene ueond vt of vs dryue.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;arf vs noht schomye.</L>
<L N="232">Ne beo&thorn; noht on &thorn;isse lyue.</L>
<L>Wymmen ne wapmen fyue.</L>
<L>&THORN;at ofte ne sunegie.
<PB REF="00000096.tif" N="80"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah &thorn;es modie gume.</L>
<L N="236">And &thorn;eos leuedies at &thorn;e frume.</L>
<L>Heo dyhte&thorn; heom vnwreste.</L>
<L>And &thorn;eos gedelynges summe.</L>
<L>Hwenne heo to schrifte come.</L>
<L N="240">Heo beo&thorn; schomeuaste.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nule heo &thorn;e so&thorn;e telle.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah me scholde heom aquelle.</L>
<L>Ne vnwreo heore Misdede.</L>
<L N="244">For-&thorn;i heo schule in helle.<MILESTONE N="250b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Euer schrinke and swelle.</L>
<L>And fo &thorn;er lu&thorn;re mede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwo nule hyne her rede.</L>
<L N="248">And vnwreo his Misdede.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e preoste one.</L>
<L>He schal eft lude grede.</L>
<L>&THORN;e quike and ek &thorn;e dede.</L>
<L N="252">Iheren hi schulen vychone.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enne schal him schome sore.</L>
<L>&THORN;e schome him &thorn;ynche&thorn; more.</L>
<L>&THORN;an muchel of his pyne.</L>
<L N="256">Bute he do bi preostes lore.</L>
<L>And yeorne bidde godes ore.</L>
<L>Ne schal him no god attryne.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>At &thorn;e Munte of olyuete.</L>
<L N="260">We schulle vs eft alle y-mete.</L>
<L>&THORN;e gode and &thorn;e vnwreste.</L>
<L>&THORN;e day wur&thorn; mylde and swete.</L>
<L>And bytter heom &thorn;at lete.</L>
<L N="264">To donne godes heste.
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="81"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er cume&thorn; god myd his rode.</L>
<L>His honde and his syde al a blode.</L>
<L>And schewe&thorn; hu he vs bouhte.</L>
<L N="268">Offerd &thorn;enne beo&thorn; &thorn;e gode.</L>
<L>And wo is &thorn;enne &thorn;e ouermode.</L>
<L>&THORN;at er &thorn;ar-of ne rouhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Loke seyde god nu&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="272">Hwat ich for ou ou&thorn;e.</L>
<L>And hwat ich gon &thorn;olye.</L>
<L>Lutel &thorn;onk ye me cu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Mid heorte ne myd Mu&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="276">Nolde ye me &thorn;onkie.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He seyde &thorn;enne to his gode.</L>
<L>And spek myd Milde mode.</L>
<L>Mine gode. ye me fedde.</L>
<L N="280">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>And schrudden and wel bihedden.</L>
<L N="284">And leyden in softe bedde.</L>
<L>&THORN;o ic a-mong eu eode.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i ich eu wulle a-redde.</L>
<L>From sathanas &thorn;e vn-ledde.</L>
<L N="288">For her ye habbe&thorn; neode.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e gode sey&thorn; &thorn;enne.</L>
<L>Louerd hwer and hwenne.</L>
<L>Dude we &thorn;e godd&eacute;de.</L>
<L N="292">&THORN;o ye yeue &thorn;ene pouere monne.</L>
<L>&THORN;o he help nedde nenne.</L>
<L>Bute as he for me hed.
<PB REF="00000098.tif" N="82"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He sey&thorn; &thorn;enne to &thorn;e wrecchen.</L>
<L N="296">Ye nolden of me recchen.<MILESTONE N="251" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For hunger ich swal &thorn;ar-vte.</L>
<L>Ye nolden me in vacchen.</L>
<L>Ye weren eu seolue wr[e]cchen.</L>
<L N="300">So Modi and so prute.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He grede&thorn; &thorn;anne heye.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wrecches and &thorn;e vnsleye.</L>
<L>&THORN;at luuede &thorn;e vnredes.</L>
<L N="304">Louerd myd vre eye.</L>
<L>Neuer we &thorn;e ne yseyen.</L>
<L>Hwenne &thorn;u neode heddest.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>[H]e sey&thorn; &thorn;enne Myne.</L>
<L N="308">Poure vn-hole hyne.</L>
<L>To eure dure come.</L>
<L>For chele hy gunne hwyne.</L>
<L>For hunger hi hedde pyne.</L>
<L N="312">Ye nolden nyme gome.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er-of ye nolde hede.</L>
<L>Ne yeuen of eure brede.</L>
<L>Of drenche ne of clo&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="316">To day ye schule&thorn; y-frede.</L>
<L>And vnder-fo lu&thorn;re mede.</L>
<L>For ye me beo&thorn; ful lo&thorn;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Myne gode he say&thorn; myd iwisse.</L>
<L N="320">To day ye schulle myd blysse.</L>
<L>To heueryche wende.</L>
<L>And ye to &thorn;esternesse.</L>
<L>And to eche sorynesse.</L>
<L N="324">And &thorn;er beo buten ende.
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="83"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He yeorre&thorn; and heo grede&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;e feondes heom for&thorn; lede&thorn;.</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e lychom and saule.</L>
<L N="328">And bete&thorn; heom and schrede&thorn;.</L>
<L>And lu&thorn;re heom bilede&thorn;.</L>
<L>Mid pykes and myd eaule.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e saule sey&thorn; to &thorn;e lychome.</L>
<L N="332">Acursed wur&thorn;e &thorn;i nome.</L>
<L>&THORN;in heaued and &thorn;in heorte.</L>
<L>&THORN;u vs hauest iwroht &thorn;es schome.</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;ene eche grome.</L>
<L N="336">Vs schal euer smerte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e gode. &thorn;e Milde. and &thorn;e clene.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah heo i-seon alle y-mene.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at kun &thorn;at we of come.</L>
<L N="340">Nulle&thorn; heo neuer ene.</L>
<L>By-reusy ne bi-mene.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;ar-to nyme g&oacute;me.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah wolde we vs wel dihte.</L>
<L N="344">And leden vre lyf myd rihte.<MILESTONE N="251b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;e hwiles we beo&thorn; here.</L>
<L>Ich hit eu segge and plyhte.</L>
<L>A domes day we Myhte.</L>
<L N="348">Beon engles iv&eacute;re.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Bidde we vre dryhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;at day scop and nyhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;at do vre saule bote.</L>
<L N="352">&THORN;at we in heuene lyhte.</L>
<L>Among &thorn;an englen bryhte.</L>
<L>Wunyen and beo mote. Amen.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="4" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000100.tif" N="84">
<HEAD>IV. The Woman of Samaria.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Incipit de Muliere samaritana. [<I>Same MS, leaf</I> 251, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;o ihesu crist an eor&thorn;e was. Mylde weren his dede.</L>
<L>Alle heo beo&thorn; on boke iwryten. &thorn;at me may heom rede.</L>
<L>&THORN;o he to monne wes iboren. of &thorn;are swete Marie.</L>
<L N="4">And wes to ful elde icumen. he venk to prechie.</L>
<L>A lutel te-for &thorn;e tyme. &thorn;at he wolde de&thorn; &thorn;olye.</L>
<L>He neyleyhte<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS neylehyte.</NOTE> to one bureh. &thorn;at hatte samarie.</L>
<L>Al so he. &thorn;iderward. sum&thorn;ing neyhleyhte.</L>
<L N="8">He sende his apostles by-voren. and het heom and tauhte.</L>
<L>Heore in and heore bil&eacute;uynge. grey&thorn;i &thorn;at heo schulde.</L>
<L>Heo duden heore louerdes hestes; ase &thorn;eines heolde.</L>
<L>Al so heo weren a-gon. &thorn;e apostles evervychone.</L>
<L>Iesus at ore walle. reste him seolf al one.</L>
<L>Ase he &thorn;er reste. ase weri wei were.</L>
<L N="14">&THORN;ar com gon o wymmon. al one buten ivere.</L>
<L>Ase heo wes er iwuned. heo com myd hire st&eacute;ne.</L>
<L>And ihesuc to &thorn;are wymmon. bi-gon his &thorn;urst to mene.</L>
<L>Yef me drynke wymmon. he seyde myd mylde Mu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;eo wymmon him onswerede. al so to mon vnku&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="19">Hwat ar-tu. &thorn;at drynke me byst. &thorn;u &thorn;inchest of iude|londe.</L>
<L>Ne mostu drynke vnder-fo. none of myne honde.</L>
<L>&THORN;o seyde ihesu crist. wymmon. if &thorn;u vnderst&oacute;de.</L>
<L N="22">Hwo hit is. &thorn;at drynke byd. &thorn;u woldest beon of o&thorn;er mode.
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="85"></L>
<L>&THORN;u woldest bidde &thorn;at he &thorn;e yeue. drynke &thorn;at ilast euere.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at ene drynke&thorn; &thorn;er-of. ne schal him &thorn;urste neuere.<MILESTONE N="252" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Louerd &thorn;o seyde &thorn;e wymmon. yef me &thorn;ar-of to drynke.</L>
<L N="26">&THORN;at ich ne &thorn;urve more. to &thorn;isse welle swynke.</L>
<L>Heo nuste hwat heo mende. heo wes of wytte poure.</L>
<L>Heo nuste noht &thorn;at heo spek. of &thorn;an holy gostes froure.</L>
<L>Sete &aacute;dun que&thorn; ihesu crist. wymmon &thorn;ine stene.</L>
<L>Go and clepe &thorn;ine were. and cume&thorn; hider y-mene.</L>
<L>I nabbe heo seyde nenne were. ich am my seolf al one.</L>
<L N="32">Nabbe ich of wepmonne. nones kunnes y-mone.</L>
<L>Wel &thorn;u seyst qua&thorn; ihesu crist. w&eacute;re. &thorn;at &thorn;u nauest nenne.</L>
<L>Fyue &thorn;u hauest ar &thorn;isse iheued. and yet &thorn;u hauest enne.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;u nu&thorn;e hauest. and heuedest summe &thorn;rowe.</L>
<L N="36">He is an o&thorn;er wyues were. more &thorn;an &thorn;in owe.</L>
<L>Louerd heo seyde hwat art &thorn;u. ich wot myd iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;u me hauest so&thorn; iseyd. of alle wordes &thorn;isse.</L>
<L N="39">&THORN;i of one &thorn;inge. sey me iredynesse.</L>
<L>Bi-twene &thorn;is twam volke. me &thorn;unche&thorn; a wundernesse.</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;eo men &thorn;at wunye&thorn;. in samaryes tune.</L>
<L>Alle heo bidde&thorn; heom to gode. an-vppe &thorn;isse dune.</L>
<L N="43">And alle &thorn;ilke &thorn;at beo&thorn;. wi&thorn;-inne iherusal&eacute;me.</L>
<L>No-hwere bute in &thorn;e temple. ne wene&thorn; god iqu&eacute;me.</L>
<L>Ilef me wymmon qua&thorn; ihesu crist. and &thorn;ar-of beo vnderstonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;at schal cume &thorn;e ilke day. and nv he is neyh honde.</L>
<L N="47">&THORN;at ne beo neuer &thorn;e mon. in so seorre londe.</L>
<L>If he myd swete &thorn;ouhtes bi&thorn;. &thorn;at he ne bi&thorn; vnderstonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah he nou&thorn;er ne beo. an-vppe &thorn;isse dune.</L>
<L>Ne in &thorn;e heye temple. of ierusalemes tune.</L>
<L>Ye nuten hwat ye bidde&thorn;. &thorn;at of gode nabbe&thorn; im&oacute;ne.</L>
<L N="52">For al eure bileue. is on stokke. o&thorn;er on stone.</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;eo &thorn;at god iknowe&thorn;. heo wyten myd iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;at hele. is icume to monne. of folke iudaysse.</L>
<L N="55">Louerd heo seyde nv quidde&thorn; men. &thorn;at cumen is Messyas.</L>
<L>&THORN;e king. &thorn;at wur&thorn;. and nu&thorn;en. is. and euer yete was.
<PB REF="00000102.tif" N="86"></L>
<L>Hwenne he cume&thorn; he wyle vs alle ryhtleche.<MILESTONE N="252b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>For he nule. ne he ne con. nenne mon bipeche.</L>
<L>Ich hit am qua&thorn; ihesu crist. &thorn;at wi&thorn; &thorn;e holde speche.</L>
<L N="60">&THORN;at Messyas am icleped. and am &thorn;es worldes leche.</L>
<L>Mid &thorn;on comen from &thorn;e bureh. &thorn;e apostles euervych&oacute;ne.</L>
<L>And wundrede &thorn;at ihesu wolde speke. wi&thorn; &thorn;are wymmon one.</L>
<L>Ah &thorn;eyh heom &thorn;uhte wunder. no &thorn;ing heo ne seyde.</L>
<L N="64">Ac &thorn;e wymmon anon. hire stene adun leyde.</L>
<L>And orn to &thorn;are bureh anon. and dude heom to vnder|stonde.</L>
<L>Of one Mihtye wihte. &thorn;at cumen is to londe.</L>
<L N="67">T&oacute; alle &thorn;at heo myhte. iseon o&thorn;er y-mete.</L>
<L>Heo gradde and seyde. ich habbe iseye &thorn;ane so&thorn;e pro|phete.</L>
<L>ch wene wel &thorn;at hit beo crist. of hwam. &thorn;e prophete sayde.</L>
<L N="70">&THORN;urh ihesu cristes Milce. and &thorn;ureh his wyssynge.</L>
<L>Monye &thorn;er byleuede. on &thorn;e heye kinge.</L>
<L>And vrnen vt of &thorn;e bureuh. myd wel Muchel &thorn;rynge.</L>
<L>And comen to ihesu &thorn;ar he set. and beden his blessynge.</L>
<L N="74">&THORN;o byl&eacute;uede &thorn;at folk. mucheles &thorn;e more.</L>
<L>For his mylde speche. and for his mylde lore.</L>
<L>And &thorn;us was &thorn;es bureuh a-red. vt of helle sore.</L>
<L>And byl&eacute;uede on al-Mihty god. nu&thorn;e and euer-more.</L>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="5" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>V. Fortune.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Weole &thorn;u art awaried &thorn;ing. vn-euene constu dele.</L>
<L>&THORN;u yeuest a wrecche weole y-nouh. noht &thorn;urh his hele.</L>
<L>Wy&thorn; freomen &thorn;u art ferly feid. wi&thorn; sauhte and make heom sele.</L>
<L>&THORN;e poure i londe naue&thorn; no lot. wi&thorn; riche for to mele.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="6" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000103.tif" N="87">
<HEAD>VI. The Five Joys of the Virgin.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Her bi-gynne&thorn; &thorn;e vif Blyssen of vre leuedi seynte Marie.<MILESTONE N="254" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<LG N="1" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Leuedy for &thorn;are blisse.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u heddest at &thorn;e frume.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;u wistest myd iwisse.</L>
<L N="4">&thorn;at ihesuc wolde beo &thorn;i sune.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwile we beo&thorn;. on lyue &thorn;isse.</L>
<L>sunnen<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS summen.</NOTE> to don is vre wune.</L>
<L>Help vs nv &thorn;at we ne mysse.</L>
<L N="8">of &thorn;at lif &thorn;at is to cume.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="2" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Moder. bli&thorn;e were &thorn;u &thorn;o.</L>
<L>hwanne &thorn;u iseye heouen-king.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e ibore wi&thorn;-vte wo.</L>
<L N="12">&thorn;at scop &thorn;e and alle &thorn;ing.</L>
<L>Beo vre scheld from vre iv&oacute;.</L>
<L>and yef vs &thorn;ine blessyng.</L>
<L>And bi-wyte vs euer-mo.</L>
<L N="16">from alle kunnes suneging.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Leuedi al myd rihte.</L>
<L>&thorn;u were gled and bli&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;o crist &thorn;ureh his myhte.</L>
<L N="20">ar&oacute;s from de&thorn;e to lyue.</L>
<L>&THORN;at alle &thorn;ing con dihte.</L>
<L>and wes i-boren of wyue.</L>
<L>He make vs clene and bryhte.</L>
<L N="24">for his wundes fyue.
<PB REF="00000104.tif" N="88"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="4" TYPE="stanza">
<L>From &thorn;e Munt of olyuete.</L>
<L>&thorn;o &thorn;i sone to heouene steyh.</L>
<L>&THORN;u hit by-heolde myd eye swete.</L>
<L N="28">for he wes &thorn;in heorte neyh.</L>
<L>&THORN;er he haue&thorn; imaked &thorn;i sete.</L>
<L>in o stude &thorn;at is ful heyh.</L>
<L>&THORN;er &thorn;e schulen engles grete.</L>
<L N="32">for &thorn;u ert bo&thorn;e. hende and sleyh.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="5" TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e king &thorn;at wes of &thorn;e ibore.</L>
<L>to heouene. he &thorn;e vette.</L>
<L>To &thorn;are blisse &thorn;at wes for-lore.</L>
<L N="36">and bi hym seolue sette.</L>
<L>Vor he hedde &thorn;e icore.</L>
<L>wel veyre he &thorn;e grette.</L>
<L>Bly&thorn;e were &thorn;u &thorn;er-vore.</L>
<L N="40">&thorn;o engles &thorn;e imette.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Moder of Milce. and mayde hende.</L>
<L>ich &thorn;e bidde as i con.</L>
<L>Ne let &thorn;u noht &thorn;e world vs blende.</L>
<L N="44">&thorn;at is ful of vre ivon.</L>
<L>Ac help vs at vre lyues ende.</L>
<L>&thorn;u &thorn;at bere god and mon.</L>
<L>And vs alle to heouene sende.</L>
<L N="48">hwenne we schulle &thorn;is lif for-gon.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesuc for &thorn;ire moder bene.<MILESTONE N="254b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;at is so veyr and so bryht.</L>
<L>Al so wis so heo is quene.</L>
<L N="52">of heouene and eor&thorn;e. and &thorn;et is ryht.</L>
<L>Of vre sunnes make vs clene.</L>
<L>and yef vs &thorn;at eche lyht.</L>
<L>And to heouene vs alle i-m&eacute;ne.</L>
<L N="56">louerd &thorn;u bryng. for wel &thorn;u Miht.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="7" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000105.tif" N="89">
<HEAD>VII.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Hwon holy chireche is vnder uote.</HEAD>
<L>Hwile wes seynte peter. i-cleped symon.</L>
<L>&THORN;o que&thorn; vre louerd him to. &thorn;u schalt hoten ston.</L>
<L>Ich wile myne chireche. sette &thorn;e up-on.</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;eo &thorn;at heo schulde biwite. nv beo&thorn; hire ivon.</L>
<L>Of alle hire forme freond. nv naue&thorn; heo non.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-fore is hire wur&thorn;sype. wel neyh al agon.</L>
<L>&THORN;o her wes symon. and nv is symonye.</L>
<L N="8">&THORN;at muchel del haue&thorn; amerd. of &thorn;ere clergie.</L>
<L>Bidde we vre louerd crist. &thorn;at hire warantye.</L>
<L>For his swete moder luue. seynte Marie.</L>
<L>So&thorn;&thorn;e wes seynte peter. pope ine Rome.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is &thorn;at heued. and auhte to beon. of &thorn;e cristend&oacute;me.</L>
<L>Clement. and Gregorie. &thorn;at him after come.</L>
<L>Hi hedden teone and seorewe. ofte and il&oacute;me.</L>
<L>For hi heolden cristes men. myd sib and myd some.</L>
<L N="16">And eke holi chireche wi&thorn;-vten &thorn;eowedome.</L>
<L>&THORN;o heo stod ful vaste. and seo&thorn;&thorn;e sume stunde.</L>
<L>Nu me kaste&thorn; hire to. myd markes and myd punde.</L>
<L>Of seolure and of golde. to vellen heo to grunde.</L>
<L N="20">Nis nv non &thorn;at wile for hire. &thorn;olie de&thorn; ne wunde.</L>
<L>So&thorn;&thorn;e seynt thomas &thorn;olede de&thorn;. al myd vnrihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;e Archebisscop stephne. for hire gon to fyhte.</L>
<L>And seynt Admund so&thorn;&thorn;e. ful veyre hire dihte.</L>
<L>For holden hire wurschipe. hi duden al heore myhte.</L>
<L>Nv is holy chireche vuele vnder honde.</L>
<L>Al hire weorre&thorn; &thorn;at wune&thorn; ine londe.</L>
<L>Bispes. and clerekes. knyhtes. and bonde.</L>
<L N="28">Kynges and eorles. to hire habbe&thorn; onde.<MILESTONE N="255" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And &thorn;e seolue pope. &thorn;at heo bi-wyte scholde.</L>
<L>Habbe he &thorn;e yeftes. of seoluer and of golde.</L>
<L>Markes and pundes. myd rihte o&thorn;er myd wronge.</L>
<L>Heo let heom alle i-wur&thorn;e. &thorn;at beo&thorn; so swy&thorn;e stronge.</L>
<L>Away &thorn;at heo bi vre daye. so is vnder vote.</L>
<L>Bidde we alle ihesu crist. &thorn;at hyre sende bote.</L>
<L>For his swete moder luue. &thorn;at is so veyr and swote.</L>
<L N="36">&THORN;at we in &thorn;isse lyue. hit i-seon mote. Amen.
</L>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="8" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000106.tif" N="90">
<HEAD>VIII. Anthem of St Thomas the Martyr.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Incipit Antiphona de sancto Thoma Martyre in Anglico.<MILESTONE N="258b" UNIT="folio"></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>HAly thomas of heoueriche.</L>
<L>Alle apostles eueliche.</L>
<L>&THORN;e Martyrs &thorn;e vnderstonde.</L>
<L N="4">Godfullyche. in heore honde.</L>
<L>Selcu&thorn; dude vre dryhtin.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he water wende to win.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ert help in engelaunde.</L>
<L N="8">Vre stephne vnderstonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;u ert froure a-mong mon-kunne.</L>
<L>Help vs nv of vre sunne. Evovae.<NOTE PLACE="foot">This word is struck through with a red line.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="9" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>IX. On Serving Christ.</HEAD>
<L>Hwi ne serue we crist. and seche&thorn; his sauht.</L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e vs wes at &thorn;e font. fulluht by-tauht.</L>
<L>Ne beo we siker of &thorn;e lif. on-lepy nauht.</L>
<L N="4">Crist kundeliche kyng. cu&thorn; &thorn;u &thorn;i mayht.<MILESTONE N="259" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Rihtwise louerd. on rode wes rauht.</L>
<L>And &thorn;olede dom vor his du&thorn;e. &thorn;at he wes ded strauht.</L>
<L>Yef we habbe&thorn; werkes. yeynes &thorn;i wille wrauht.</L>
<L N="8">Louerd haue merci of vs. &thorn;at neuer ne faht.</L>
<L>Hwi ne beo we duhty men. and duten vre deden.</L>
<L>Al we schullen a-syen. and seo to &thorn;e nede.</L>
<L>&THORN;er &thorn;e crysmechild for sunnes. sore schal drede.</L>
<L N="12">I-seon vre louerd crist. &thorn;at schal &thorn;is world fede.
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="91"></L>
<L>Showen his wunden. so blodi to-bleden.</L>
<L>Nouht for his gultes. bute for Adames deden.</L>
<L>Leste he schulde his du&thorn;e. from him seolue scheden.</L>
<L N="16">Leue we &thorn;is for sayn. so&thorn; al so &thorn;e crede.</L>
<L>As ich ihere bolde men. vpe bok rede.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ere feole to fordeme. in schynynde wede.</L>
<L>Nis so wlonk vnder crist. ridynde on stede.</L>
<L N="20">Ne &thorn;eos crefty clerekes. &thorn;at vpe bok rede.</L>
<L>For gold ne for seoluer. ne for glysyinde wede.</L>
<L>For al &thorn;e weole and &thorn;e wyn. &thorn;at riche men fede.</L>
<L>For seolk. ne for cendal. ne for deore [wedes]<NOTE PLACE="foot">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L N="24">&THORN;at ne schal at &thorn;e dom. beon demed of heore dedes.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is &thorn;e sunfulle. vnsofte to beon.</L>
<L>Hwer he not no wey. fyr for to fleon.</L>
<L>And Adames eyres beo&thorn; parted on &thorn;re.</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;er is gronynge and grure. and gryslich gle.</L>
<L>Bi-seche we &thorn;e louerd. &thorn;at welde&thorn; &thorn;e ueo.</L>
<L>As he for monkunnes neodes. don wes on &thorn;e treo.</L>
<L>And seynte Marie &thorn;e brude. &thorn;at bryht is and bleo.</L>
<L N="32">Leue &thorn;at we moten at schrifte vre sunnes vn-wreo.</L>
<L>Hwi nule we &thorn;enchen and beo &thorn;olemode.</L>
<L>For him &thorn;at &thorn;olede for vs. &thorn;e wunden of blode.</L>
<L>&THORN;ayh we her hoppen. ihosed and ischode.</L>
<L N="36">Heonne we schulle &thorn;rynge. &thorn;at er were so mode.<MILESTONE N="259b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Bi-leue&thorn; oure weorre. warlawes wode.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;es world is bi-heled. myd he&thorn;ene-hode.</L>
<L>Seynte peter wes prynce. and pyned is on rode.</L>
<L N="40">For to volewen vre fader. his wille. &thorn;et he stode.</L>
<L>And we wy&thorn; sunnes gete&thorn;. saulene fode.</L>
<L>Ye mowen iheren fur drerlyke. me deme&thorn; &thorn;is gode.</L>
<L>Nv ye Muwen iheren. in chireche. bo syngen and rede.</L>
<L>Hw seynte laurence. wes ibrouht bunde. for to brede.</L>
<L N="45">So he wes i-hyed. and hot on &thorn;e glede.</L>
<L>Ful Derlike<NOTE PLACE="foot">kerlike <I>altered to</I> Derlike.</NOTE> &thorn;is deore mon. dute his dede.
<PB REF="00000108.tif" N="92"></L>
<L>Leste he schulde his saule. horyen and schede.</L>
<L N="48">In he&thorn;ene helle &thorn;er hirdsype is gnede.</L>
<L>Bi-seche we vre louerd. &thorn;at schal &thorn;is world fede.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he haue mercy of vs. of vre Misdede.</L>
<L>Seynt iohan is &thorn;e beste. &thorn;at euer wes iwrouht.</L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e god makede Middelerd. and mon myd his &thorn;ouht.</L>
<L>&THORN;ureh his sely sermun. serewe him wes by-&thorn;ouht.</L>
<L>&THORN;e prophetes heued to present me brouht.</L>
<L>For to folewen vre fader. so he haue&thorn; [&thorn;ouht].<NOTE PLACE="foot">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L N="56">Hwo ysayh. euer blisse byterluker ibouht.</L>
<L>Seynt thomas wes biscop. and barunes him quolde.</L>
<L>Heo brutlede him ful breoly. &thorn;e beornes &thorn;at were bolde.</L>
<L>For he wolde &thorn;e lawe. leoflyche holde.</L>
<L N="60">As god wy&thorn; his werkes. i &thorn;is world stolde.</L>
<L>For &thorn;e luue of vre fader. vihten. he nolde.</L>
<L>&THORN;er he &thorn;olede pyne. as &thorn;e peple. me tolde.</L>
<L>For &thorn;e dute of &thorn;e dom. he &thorn;et lif solde.</L>
<L N="64">Hwe schullich<NOTE PLACE="foot">So in MS.</NOTE> &thorn;auh vre heorte beon in [? wolde]</L>
<L>Alle we schulle to &thorn;e de&thorn; dreoreliche gon.</L>
<L>And bi-leuen vre leoue freond. euervych on.</L>
<L>Me graue&thorn; &thorn;is gode. in greote and in ston.</L>
<L N="68">&THORN;er were&thorn; vre wlite. in wurmene won.<MILESTONE N="260" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ne geyne&thorn; vs no grene. ne no [scarlat non].<NOTE PLACE="foot">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;e robes of russet. ne of rencyan.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;e ronke racches. &thorn;at ruskit &thorn;e ron.</L>
<L N="72">Bo&thorn;e him schal rotye &thorn;at body and &thorn;e bon.</L>
<L>&THORN;ayh &thorn;u frayny after freond. ne fyndestu n&oacute;n.</L>
<L>Bute saule for seorewe make&thorn; hire mon.</L>
<L>He &thorn;at fulewede him seolue. in &thorn;e flum iurdan.</L>
<L N="76">&THORN;ureh &thorn;e sybnesse of seynt iohan.</L>
<L>&THORN;ureh &thorn;e riche blode &thorn;e roche to-chon.</L>
<L>Louerd haue mercy of vs. euervychon. Amen.
</L>

</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="10" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000109.tif" N="93">
<HEAD>X. A Luue Ron.</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Incipit quidam cantus quem composuit frater Thomas de hales de ordine fratrum Minorum. ad instanciam cuiusdam puelle deo dicate.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>A Mayde cristes me bit yorne.</L>
<L>&thorn;at ich hire wurche a luue ron.</L>
<L>For hwan heo myhte best ileorne.</L>
<L N="4">to taken. on o&thorn;er so&thorn; lefmon.</L>
<L>&THORN;at [t]reowest were of alle berne.</L>
<L>and best wyte cu&thorn;e a freo wymmon.</L>
<L>Ich hire nule nowiht werne.</L>
<L N="8">ich hire wule teche as ic con.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mayde. her &thorn;u myht biholde.</L>
<L>&thorn;is worldes luue nys bute o res.</L>
<L>And is by-set. so fele-volde.</L>
<L N="12">vikel. and frakel. and wok. and les.</L>
<L>&THORN;eos &thorn;eines &thorn;at her weren bolde.</L>
<L>beo&thorn; aglyden. so wyndes bles.</L>
<L>Vnder molde hi ligge&thorn; colde.</L>
<L N="16">and falewe&thorn; so do&thorn; medewe gres.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nis no mon iboren o lyue.</L>
<L>&thorn;at her may beon studeuest.</L>
<L>For her he haue&thorn; seorewen ryue.</L>
<L N="20">ne tyt him neuer [Ro ne Rest.]<NOTE PLACE="foot">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>Toward his ende he hye&thorn; blyue.</L>
<L>and lutle hwile he her i-lest.</L>
<L>Pyne and de&thorn; him wile of-dryue.</L>
<L N="24">hwenne he wene&thorn; to libben best.
<PB REF="00000110.tif" N="94"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nis non so riche. ne non so freo.</L>
<L>&thorn;at he ne schal heonne. sone &aacute;way.</L>
<L>Ne may hit neuer his waraunt beo.</L>
<L N="28">gold. ne seoluer. vouh. ne gray.</L>
<L>Ne beo he no &thorn;e swift. ne may he fleo.</L>
<L>ne weren his lif enne day.</L>
<L>&THORN;us is &thorn;es world as &thorn;u mayht seo.</L>
<L N="32">al so &thorn;e schadewe &thorn;at glyt away.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;is world fare&thorn; hwilynde.</L>
<L>hwenne on cume&thorn; an o&thorn;er go&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wes bi-fore. nv is bihynde.</L>
<L N="36">&thorn;at er was leof nv hit is lo&thorn;.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i he do&thorn; as &thorn;e blynde.</L>
<L>&thorn;at in &thorn;is world. his luue do&thorn;.</L>
<L>Ye mowen iseo. &thorn;e world aswynde.<MILESTONE N="260b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="40">&thorn;at wouh go&thorn; for&thorn;. abak &thorn;at so&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eo luue &thorn;at ne may her abyde.</L>
<L>&thorn;u treowest hire myd muchel wouh.</L>
<L>Al so hwenne hit schal to-glide.</L>
<L N="44">hit is fals. and mereuh. and frouh.</L>
<L>And fromward in vychon tide.</L>
<L>hwile hit leste&thorn; is seorewe inouh.</L>
<L>An ende ne werie mon so syde.</L>
<L N="48">he schal to-dreosen. so lef on bouh.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Monnes luue nys buten o stunde.</L>
<L>nv he luue&thorn;. nv he is sad.</L>
<L>Nu he cume&thorn;. nv wile he funde.</L>
<L N="52">nv he is wro&thorn;. nv he is gled.</L>
<L>His luue is her and ek a lunde.</L>
<L>nv he luue&thorn; sum &thorn;at he er bed.</L>
<L>Nis he neuer treowe ifunde.</L>
<L N="56">&thorn;at him triste&thorn;. he is amed.
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="95"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Yf mon is riche of worldes weole.</L>
<L>hit make&thorn; his heorte smerte and ake.</L>
<L>If he dret &thorn;at me him stele.</L>
<L N="60">&thorn;enne do&thorn; him pyne nyhtes wake.</L>
<L>Him waxe&thorn; &thorn;ouhtes monye and fele.</L>
<L>hw he hit may witen wi&thorn;-vten sake.</L>
<L>An ende hwat helpe&thorn; hit to hele.</L>
<L N="64">al de&thorn; hit wile from him take.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer is paris and heleyne.</L>
<L>&thorn;at weren so bryht and feyre on bleo.</L>
<L>Amadas. tristram. and dideyne.<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS and dideyne. tristram.</NOTE></L>
<L N="68">yseude. and alle &thorn;eo.</L>
<L>Ector wi&thorn; his scharpe meyne.</L>
<L>and cesar riche of wordes<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Read</I> worldes.</NOTE> feo.</L>
<L>Heo beo&thorn; iglyden vt of &thorn;e reyne.</L>
<L N="72">so &thorn;e schef[t] is of &thorn;e cleo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hit is of heom al so hit n&eacute;re.</L>
<L>of heom me haue&thorn; wunder itold.</L>
<L>Nere hit reu&thorn;e for to heren.</L>
<L N="76">hw hi were wi&thorn; pyne aquold.</L>
<L>And hwat hi &thorn;oleden alyue h&eacute;re.</L>
<L>al is heore hot iturnd to cold.</L>
<L>&THORN;us is &thorn;es world of false fere.</L>
<L N="80">f&oacute;l. he is. &thorn;e on hire is bold.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eyh he were so riche mon.</L>
<L>as henry vre kyng.</L>
<L>And al so veyr as absalon.</L>
<L N="84">&thorn;at neuede on eor&thorn;e non euenyng.</L>
<L>Al were sone his prute agon.</L>
<L>hit nere on ende wr&thorn; on heryng.</L>
<L>Mayde if &thorn;u wilnest after leofmon.</L>
<L N="88">ich teche &thorn;e enne treowe king.
<PB REF="00000112.tif" N="96"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L><B>A</B> swete if &thorn;u iknowe.</L>
<L>&thorn;e gode &thorn;ewes of &thorn;isse childe.</L>
<L>He is feyr. and bryht on heowe.</L>
<L N="92">of glede chere. of mode mylde.</L>
<L>Of lufsum lost. of truste treowe.</L>
<L>freo of heorte. of wisdom wilde.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;urhte &thorn;e neuer rewe.</L>
<L N="96">myhtestu. do &thorn;e in his ylde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He is ricchest mon of londe.</L>
<L>so wide so mon speke&thorn;. wi&thorn; mu&thorn;.</L>
<L>Alle heo beo&thorn; to his honde.</L>
<L N="100">est. and west. nor&thorn;. and su&thorn;.</L>
<L>Henri king of engelonde.<MILESTONE N="261" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>of hym he halt. and to hym buh&thorn;.</L>
<L>Mayde to &thorn;e he send his schonde.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Read</I> sonde.</NOTE></L>
<L N="104">and wilne&thorn; for to beo &thorn;e cu&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne byt he wi&thorn; &thorn;e lond ne leode.</L>
<L>vouh. ne gray. ne rencyan.</L>
<L>Naue&thorn; he &thorn;er-to. none neode.</L>
<L N="108">he is riche and wel[i man.]</L>
<L>If &thorn;u him woldest luue beode.</L>
<L>and by-cumen his leouemon.</L>
<L>He brouhte &thorn;e to suche wede.</L>
<L N="112">&thorn;at naue&thorn; king ne kayser non.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwat spekestu of eny bolde.</L>
<L>&thorn;at wrouhte &thorn;e wise salomon</L>
<L>Of iaspe. of saphir. of merede golde.</L>
<L N="116">and of mony on o&thorn;er ston.</L>
<L>Hit is feyrure of feole volde.</L>
<L>more &thorn;an ich eu telle con.</L>
<L>&THORN;is bold mayde &thorn;e is bihote.</L>
<L N="120">if &thorn;at &thorn;u bist his leouemon.
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="97"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hit stont vppon a treowe mote.</L>
<L>&thorn;ar hit neuer truke ne schal.</L>
<L>Ne may no Mynur hire vnderwrote.</L>
<L N="124">ne neuer false &thorn;ene grundwal.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-inne is vich balewes b&oacute;te.</L>
<L>blisse. and Ioye. and gleo. and G&aacute;l.</L>
<L>&THORN;is bold. mayde is &thorn;e bih&oacute;te.</L>
<L N="128">and vych o blisse &thorn;ar-wy&thorn;-al.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er ne may no freond fleon o&thorn;er.</L>
<L>ne non fur-leosen his iryhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;er nys hate ne wre&thorn;&thorn;e nou&thorn;er.</L>
<L N="132">of prude. ne of onde. of none wihte.</L>
<L>Alle heo schule wy&thorn; engles pleye.</L>
<L>some. and sauhte. in heouene lyhte.</L>
<L>Ne beo&thorn; heo mayde. in gode weye.</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;at wel luue&thorn; vre dryhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne may no mon hine iseo.</L>
<L>al so he is. in his Mihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;at may wi&thorn;-vten blisse beo.</L>
<L N="140">hwanne he isih&thorn; vre drihte.</L>
<L>His sihte is al ioye and gleo.</L>
<L>he is day wy&thorn;-vte nyhte.</L>
<L>Nere he. mayde ful seoly.</L>
<L N="144">&thorn;at myhte wunye myd such a knyhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He haue&thorn; bi-tauht &thorn;e o tresur.</L>
<L>&thorn;at is betere. &thorn;an gold o&thorn;er pel.</L>
<L>And bit &thorn;e luke &thorn;ine bur.</L>
<L N="148">and wilne&thorn; &thorn;at &thorn;u hit wyte wel.</L>
<L>Wy&thorn; &thorn;eoues. wi&thorn; reueres. w&igrave;&thorn; lechurs.</L>
<L>&thorn;u most beo waker and snel;</L>
<L>&THORN;u art swetture &thorn;ane eny flur.</L>
<L N="152">hwile &thorn;u witest &thorn;ene kastel.
<PB REF="00000114.tif" N="98"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hit is ymston. of feor iboren.</L>
<L>nys non betere vnder heouene grunde.</L>
<L>He is to-fore alle o&thorn;re i-coren.</L>
<L N="156">he hele&thorn; alle luue wunde.</L>
<L>Wel were. a lyue iboren.</L>
<L>&thorn;at myhte wyten &thorn;is ilke stunde.</L>
<L>For habbe &thorn;u. hine. enes for-l&oacute;ren;</L>
<L N="160">ne by&thorn; he neuer eft ifunde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;is ilke ston. &thorn;at ich &thorn;e nemne.</L>
<L>Mayden-hod icleoped is.</L>
<L>Hit is o derewur&thorn;e gemme.<MILESTONE N="261b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="164">of alle o&thorn;re he ber&thorn; &thorn;at pris.</L>
<L>And brynge&thorn; &thorn;e wi&thorn;-vte wemme.</L>
<L>in-to &thorn;e blysse of paradis.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwile &thorn;u hyne witest vnder &thorn;ine hemme.</L>
<L N="168">&thorn;u ert swetture &thorn;an eny spis.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwat spekstu of eny st&oacute;ne.</L>
<L>&thorn;at beo&thorn; in vertu o&thorn;er in [? grace]<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS <I>pris</I> in a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of Amatiste. of calcyd&oacute;ne.</L>
<L N="172">of lectorie. and tupace.<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>y-wys</I> is added in a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>Of iaspe. of saphir. of sardone.</L>
<L>smaragde. Beril. and crisopace.</L>
<L>Among alle o&thorn;re ymstone.</L>
<L N="176">&thorn;es beo&thorn; deorre. in vyche place.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mayde. al so ich &thorn;e tolde.</L>
<L>&thorn;e ymston of &thorn;i bur.</L>
<L>He is betere an hundred folde.</L>
<L N="180">&thorn;an alle &thorn;eos in heore culur.</L>
<L>He is idon in heouene golde.</L>
<L>and is ful of fyn amur.</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;at myhte. hine wite scholde.</L>
<L N="184">he schyne&thorn; so bryht in heouene bur.
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="99"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwen &thorn;u me dost in &thorn;ine rede.</L>
<L>for &thorn;e to cheose a leofmon.</L>
<L>Ich wile don as &thorn;u me bede.</L>
<L N="188">&thorn;e beste &thorn;at ich fynde con.</L>
<L>Ne do&thorn; h&eacute; mayde. on vuele dede.</L>
<L>&thorn;at may cheose. of two &thorn;at on.</L>
<L>And he wile wi&thorn;-vte neode.</L>
<L N="192">take &thorn;et wurse. &thorn;e betere let gon.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;is rym mayde ich &thorn;e sende.</L>
<L>open and wi&thorn;-vte sel.</L>
<L>Bidde ic &thorn;at &thorn;u hit vntrende.</L>
<L N="196">and leorny bute bok vych del.</L>
<L>Her-of &thorn;at &thorn;u beo swi&thorn;e hende.</L>
<L>and tech hit o&thorn;er maydenes wel.</L>
<L>Hwo so cu&thorn;e hit to &thorn;an ende.</L>
<L N="200">hit wolde him stonde muchel stel.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne &thorn;u sittest in longynge.</L>
<L>drauh &thorn;e for&thorn; &thorn;is ilke wryt.</L>
<L>Mid swete stephne &thorn;u hit singe.</L>
<L N="204">and do al so hit &thorn;e byt.</L>
<L>To &thorn;e he haue&thorn; send one gretynge.</L>
<L>god al-myhti &thorn;e beo myd.</L>
<L>And leue cumen to his brud&thorn;inge.</L>
<L N="208">heye in heouene. &thorn;er he sit.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>And yeue him god endynge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at haue&thorn; iwryten &thorn;is ilke wryt. Amen.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="11" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000116.tif" N="100">
<HEAD>XI. The Annunciation of the Virgin Mary. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 261, <I>back, the latter part on leaf</I> 254.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Item cantus.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>FRom heouene in-to eor&thorn;e. god gretynge he sende.</L>
<L>Bi on Archaungle. &thorn;at to Marye wende.</L>
<L>Milde wes &thorn;at mayde. swete and swi&thorn;e hende.</L>
<L N="4">And of fayre ibere. Gabriel hire grette. &thorn;us que&thorn;inde.</L>
<L>Edy beo &thorn;u mayde. &thorn;us wunyinde.</L>
<L>&THORN;er schal a child in &thorn;e kenyen. and springe.</L>
<L>I-lef me Marie.</L>
<L N="8">Marie him onswerede. myd stephne swi&thorn;e mylde.</L>
<L>Hw myhte hit iwur&thorn;e &thorn;at ich were myd childe.</L>
<L>Monnes im&oacute;ne on me. ne may. n&oacute;mon fynde.</L>
<L>Of-dred wes &thorn;at mayde.</L>
<L N="12">. . . . .</L>
<L>Of &thorn;ine swete wordes. ich am swi&thorn;e gled.<MILESTONE N="254" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ich am godes wenche. ful wel ich habbe i-sped.</L>
<L>Al his wille beo ifuld. as &thorn;u hauest iseyd.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L N="16">Bidde we &thorn;ilke louerd. wende hwer we wende.</L>
<L>&THORN;at to &thorn;e swete mayde. gabriel gon sende.</L>
<L>&THORN;at for his swete moder luue. &thorn;at feyr is and hende.</L>
<L>Bringe vs to &thorn;e blisse. &thorn;at leste&thorn; buten ende. Amen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="12" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>XII. Fragment of a Song. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 262.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Naue&thorn; my saule. bute fur and &yacute;s.</L>
<L>and &thorn;e lichome eor&thorn;e and treo.
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="101"></L>
<L>[B]idde we alle &thorn;en heye kyng.</L>
<L N="4">&thorn;at welde schal &thorn;e laste dom.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he vs lete &thorn;at ilke &thorn;ing.</L>
<L>&thorn;at we mowen his wille don.</L>
<L>He vs skere of &thorn;e ty&thorn;ing.</L>
<L N="8">&thorn;at sunfule schulle an-vnderfon.</L>
<L>Hwenne de&thorn; heom lat to &thorn;e Mureh&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;at neuer ne by&thorn; undon. Amen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="13" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>XIII. Signs of Death. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 262.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>[H]wenne &thorn;in heou bloke&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;i streng&thorn;e woke&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;i neose colde&thorn;.</L>
<L N="4">And &thorn;i tunge volde&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e byleue&thorn; &thorn;i bre&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;i lif &thorn;e at-ge&thorn;.</L>
<L>[M]e<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. He; <I>but the</I> H <I>is by a later hand</I>.</NOTE> nyme&thorn; &thorn;e nu&thorn;e wrecche.</L>
<L N="8">On flore me &thorn;e strecche&thorn;.</L>
<L>And ley&thorn; &thorn;e on b&eacute;re.</L>
<L>And bi-preone&thorn; &thorn;e on here.</L>
<L>And do&thorn; &thorn;e ine putte. wurmes iv&eacute;re.</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;eonne bi&thorn; hit sone of &thorn;e. al so &thorn;u neuer nere.</L>
</LG>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="14" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>XIV. Three Sorrowful Tidings. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 262.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>[V]yche day me cume&thorn; tydinges &thorn;reo.</L>
<L>For wel swi&thorn;e sore beo&thorn; heo.</L>
<L>&THORN;e on is &thorn;at ich schal heonne.</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;at o&thorn;er &thorn;at ich noth hwenne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;ridde is my meste kare;</L>
<L>&THORN;at ich not hwider ich scal fare.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="15" TYPE="item">
<DIV2 TYPE="version"><PB REF="00000118.tif" N="102">
<HEAD>XV. The Proverbs of Alfred. TEXT I. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 262.]</HEAD>
<HEAD>Incipiunt documenta Regis Aluredi.</HEAD>
<LG N="1" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>1.</HEAD>
<L>AT Seuorde</L>
<L>s&eacute;te &thorn;eynes monye.</L>
<L>fele Biscopes.</L>
<L N="4">and fcole bok-il&eacute;red.</L>
<L>Eorles prute.</L>
<L>knyhtes egleche.</L>
<L>&thorn;ar wes &thorn;e eorl Alurich.</L>
<L N="8">of &thorn;are lawe swi&thorn;e wis.</L>
<L>And ek Ealured</L>
<L>englene hurde.</L>
<L>Englene durlyng;</L>
<L N="12">on englene londe he wes kyng.</L>
<L>Heom he bi-gon l&eacute;re.</L>
<L>so ye mawe i-hure.</L>
<L>hw hi. heore lif</L>
<L N="16">lede scholden.</L>
<L>Alured. he wes in englene lond.</L>
<L>and king. wel swi&thorn;e strong.</L>
<L>He wes king. and he wes clerek.</L>
<L N="20">wel he luuede godes werk.</L>
<L>He wes wis on his word.</L>
<L>and war. on his werke.</L>
<L>he wes &thorn;e wysuste mon;</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;at wes engle-londe on.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="2" TYPE="stanza">

<PB REF="00000120.tif" N="104">
<HEAD>2.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;vs que&thorn; Alured</L>
<L>englene frouer.</L>
<L>wolde ye mi leode</L>
<L N="28">lusten &eacute;ure louerde.</L>
<L>he &oacute;u wolde wyssye.</L>
<L>wisliche &thorn;inges.</L>
<L>hw ye myhte worldes.</L>
<L N="32">wr&thorn;sipes welde.</L>
<L>and ek eure saule.</L>
<L>somnen to criste.</L>
<L>wyse were &thorn;e wordes.</L>
<L N="36">&thorn;e seyde &thorn;e king Alured.</L>
<L>Mildeliche ich Munye.<MILESTONE N="262b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>myne leoue freond.</L>
<L>poure and riche.</L>
<L N="40">leode myne</L>
<L>&thorn;at ye alle a-drede.</L>
<L>vre dryhten crist.</L>
<L>luuyen hine and lykyen.</L>
<L N="44">for he is louerd of lyf.</L>
<L>He is one. god;</L>
<L>ouer alle godnesse.</L>
<L>He is one gleaw.</L>
<L N="48">ouer alle glednesse.</L>
<L>He is one. blisse.</L>
<L>ouer alle blissen.</L>
<L>He is one monne.</L>
<L N="52">Mildest mayster.</L>
<L>He is one. folkes fader.</L>
<L>and frouer.</L>
<L>He is one. rihtwis.</L>
<L N="56">and so riche king.</L>
<L>&thorn;at him ne schal beo wone.</L>
<L>nouht of his wille.
<PB REF="00000122.tif" N="106"></L>
<L>we<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> &thorn;e.</NOTE> hine her on worlde.</L>
<L N="60">wr&thorn;ie &thorn;enche&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>3.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;vs que&thorn; alured.</L>
<L>englene urouer.</L>
<L>Ne may non ryhtwis king.</L>
<L N="64">vnder criste seoluen.</L>
<L>Bute if he beo</L>
<L>in boke ilered.</L>
<L>And he. his wyttes</L>
<L N="68">swi&thorn;e wel kunne.</L>
<L>And he cunne lettres.</L>
<L>lokie him seolf one.</L>
<L>hw he schule his lond</L>
<L N="72">laweliche holde.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>4.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>&THORN;e eorl and &thorn;e e&thorn;elyng.</L>
<L>ibure&thorn; vnder g&oacute;dne king.</L>
<L N="76">&thorn;at lond to leden.</L>
<L>myd lawelyche deden.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e clerek and &thorn;e knyht.</L>
<L>he schulle d&eacute;men euelyche riht.</L>
<L N="80">&thorn;e poure. and &thorn;e ryche.</L>
<L>d&eacute;men ilyche.</L>
<L>Hwych so &thorn;e mon sowe&thorn;;</L>
<L>al swuch he schal mowe.</L>
<L N="84">And eueruyches monnes dom.</L>
<L>to his owere dure churre&thorn;.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="5" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>5.</HEAD>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>&thorn;an knyhte bi-houe&thorn;.</L>
<L N="88">kenliche on to f&oacute;ne.</L>
<L>for to werie &thorn;at lond.
<PB REF="00000124.tif" N="108"></L>
<L>wi&thorn; hunger and wi&thorn; herivnge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e chireche habbe gry&thorn;.</L>
<L N="92">And &thorn;e cheorl beo in fry&thorn;.</L>
<L>his sedes to sowen.</L>
<L>his medes to mowen.</L>
<L>And his plouh beo i-dryue.</L>
<L N="96">to vre alre bihoue.</L>
<L>&thorn;is is &thorn;es knyhtes lawe.</L>
<L>loke he &thorn;at hit wel fare.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>6.</HEAD>
<L>&THORN;vs que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="100">&thorn;e mon. &thorn;e on his youh&thorn;e.</L>
<L>yeorne leorne&thorn;.</L>
<L>wit and wisdom.</L>
<L>And iwriten reden;</L>
<L N="104">he may beon on elde.</L>
<L>wenliche lor&thorn;eu.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e &thorn;at nule one youh&thorn;e</L>
<L>yeorne leorny.</L>
<L N="108">wit and wysdom.</L>
<L>and iwriten rede.</L>
<L>&thorn;at him schal on elde.</L>
<L>sore rewe.</L>
<L N="112">&thorn;enne cume&thorn; elde.</L>
<L>and vnhel&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne beo&thorn; his w&eacute;ne</L>
<L>ful wro&thorn;e isene.</L>
<L N="116">Bo&thorn;e heo beo&thorn; bi-swike.</L>
<L>and eke hi beo&thorn; a-swunde.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="7" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>7.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>Wy&thorn;-vte wysdome</L>
<L N="120">is weole wel vnwur&thorn;.
<PB REF="00000126.tif" N="110"></L>
<L>for &thorn;ey o mon ahte.</L>
<L>huntseuenti Acres.</L>
<L>and he hi hadde isowen.</L>
<L N="124">alle myd reade golde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;at <MILESTONE N="263" UNIT="folio">gold greowe.</L>
<L>so gres do&thorn; on eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>nere he for his weole.</L>
<L N="128">neuer &thorn;e fur&thorn;er.</L>
<L>Bute he him of frum&thorn;e.</L>
<L>freond iwrche.</L>
<L>for. hwat is gold. bute ston.</L>
<L N="132">bute if hit haue&thorn; wismon.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="8" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>8.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>Ne scolde neuer yongmon</L>
<L>howyen to swi&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;eih him his wyse</L>
<L>wel ne lykie.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;eih he ne welde.</L>
<L>al &thorn;at he wolde.</L>
<L N="140">for god may. yeue &thorn;enne he wule.</L>
<L>god after vuele.</L>
<L>weole after wowe.</L>
<L>wel is him &thorn;at hit ischapen is.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="9" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>9.</HEAD>
<L N="144">&thorn;us sey&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>STrong hit is to reowe.</L>
<L>a-yeyn &thorn;e s&eacute;&eacute; &thorn;at flowe&thorn;.</L>
<L>so hit is to swynke.</L>
<L N="148">a-yeyn vnylimpe.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon. &thorn;e on his youh&thorn;e.</L>
<L>swo swinke&thorn;.</L>
<L>and worldes weole her iwin&thorn;.</L>
<L N="152">&thorn;at he may on elde.
<PB REF="00000128.tif" N="112"></L>
<L>idelnesse holde.</L>
<L>And ek myd his worldes weole.</L>
<L>god iqueme er he quele.</L>
<L N="156">you&thorn;e and al &thorn;at he haue&thorn; idrowe.</L>
<L>is &thorn;enne wel bi-towe.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="10" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>10.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="160">Monymon wene&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at he wene ne &thorn;arf.</L>
<L>longes lyues.</L>
<L>ac him lye&thorn; &thorn;e wrench.</L>
<L N="164">for &thorn;anne his lyues</L>
<L>alre best luuede.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne he schal l&eacute;ten;</L>
<L>lyf his owe.</L>
<L N="168">for nys no wrt uexynde</L>
<L>a wude. ne a velde.</L>
<L>&thorn;at euer mvwe &thorn;as feye</L>
<L>fur&thorn; vp-holde.</L>
<L N="172">Not no mon &thorn;ene tyme.</L>
<L>hwanne he schal. heonne turne.</L>
<L>Ne nomon &thorn;ene ende.</L>
<L>hwenne he schal heonne wende.</L>
<L N="176">Dryhten hit one wot.</L>
<L>dowe&thorn;es louerd.</L>
<L>hwanne vre lif</L>
<L>leten schule.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="11" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>11.</HEAD>
<L N="180">&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>Yf &thorn;u seoluer and gold.</L>
<L>yefst<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yetst.</NOTE> and weldest in &thorn;is world.</L>
<L>Neuer vpen eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="184">to wlonk. &thorn;u ny-wr&thorn;e.
<PB REF="00000130.tif" N="114"></L>
<L>Ayhte nys non ildre istreon;</L>
<L>ac hit is godes lone.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> loue.</NOTE></L>
<L>hwanne hit is his wille.</L>
<L N="188">&thorn;ar-of we schulle wende.</L>
<L>And vre owe lyf.</L>
<L>myd alle for-leten.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne schulle vre ifon.</L>
<L N="192">to vre vouh. gripen.</L>
<L>welden vre May&thorn;enes.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> madmes.</NOTE></L>
<L>and leten vs by-hinde.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="12" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>12.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="196">Ne ilef &thorn;u nouht to fele.</L>
<L>uppe &thorn;e s&eacute;&eacute; &thorn;at flowe&thorn;.</L>
<L>If &thorn;u hafst madmes</L>
<L>monye and inowe.</L>
<L N="200">gold and seoluer.</L>
<L>hit schal gnyde to nouht.</L>
<L>to duste hit schal dryuen.</L>
<L>Dryhten schal<MILESTONE N="263b" UNIT="folio"> libben euere.</L>
<L N="204">Monymon for his gold.</L>
<L>haue&thorn; godes vrre.</L>
<L>And for his seoluer.</L>
<L>hym seolue for-yeme&thorn;.</L>
<L N="208">for-yete&thorn; and forlese&thorn;.</L>
<L>Betere him by-come</L>
<L>iboren &thorn;at he n&eacute;re.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="13" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>13.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="212">Lvste&thorn; ye me leode.</L>
<L>ower is &thorn;e neode.</L>
<L>And ich eu wille l&eacute;re.</L>
<L>wit and wisdom.</L>
<L N="216">&thorn;at alle &thorn;ing ouer-go&thorn;.
<PB REF="00000132.tif" N="116"></L>
<L>syker he may sitte.</L>
<L>&thorn;e hyne haue&thorn; to i-vere.</L>
<L>For &thorn;eyh his eyhte him a-go.</L>
<L N="220">his wit ne ago&thorn; hym neuer-mo.</L>
<L>for ne may he for-vare</L>
<L>&thorn;e hyne haue&thorn; to vere.</L>
<L>&thorn;e wile his owe lyf.</L>
<L N="224">ileste mote.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="14" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>14.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>If &thorn;u hauest seorewe.</L>
<L N="228">ne seye &thorn;u hit nouht &thorn;an arewe.</L>
<L>seye hit &thorn;ine sadelbowe.</L>
<L>and ryd &thorn;e singinde for&thorn;.</L>
<L>&thorn;enne wile wene.</L>
<L N="232">&thorn;et &thorn;ine wise ne con;</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e &thorn;ine wise wel lyke.</L>
<L>serewe if &thorn;u hauest.</L>
<L>and &thorn;e erewe hit wot;</L>
<L N="236">by-fore. he &thorn;e mene&thorn;;</L>
<L>by-hynde he &thorn;e tele&thorn;.</L>
<L>&thorn;u hit myht segge swyhc mon.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e ful wel on.</L>
<L N="240">wy&thorn;-vte echere ore.</L>
<L>he on &thorn;e Muchele more.</L>
<L>By-hud hit on &thorn;ire heorte;</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e eft ne smeorte.</L>
<L N="244">Ne let &thorn;u hyne wite.</L>
<L>al &thorn;at &thorn;in heorte by-wite.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="15" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>15.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="248">NE schal-tu neuere &thorn;i wif.
<PB REF="00000134.tif" N="118"></L>
<L>by hire wlyte cheose.</L>
<L>for neuer n&oacute;ne &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at heo to &thorn;e brynge&thorn;.</L>
<L N="252">Ac leorne hire custe.</L>
<L>heo cu&thorn;e&thorn; hi wel sone.</L>
<L>For mony mon for ayhte.</L>
<L>vuele i-auhte&thorn;.</L>
<L N="256">And ofte mon of fayre.</L>
<L>frakele icheose&thorn;.</L>
<L>wo is him &thorn;at vuel wif.</L>
<L>brynge&thorn; to his cotlyf.</L>
<L N="260">so him is alyue;</L>
<L>&thorn;at vuele ywyue&thorn;.</L>
<L>For he schal vppen eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>dreori i-wur&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="264">Monymon singe&thorn;.</L>
<L>&thorn;at wif hom brynge&thorn;.</L>
<L>wiste he hwat he brouhte.</L>
<L>wepen he myhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="16" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>16.</HEAD>
<L N="268">&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>NE wur&thorn; &thorn;u neuer so wod.</L>
<L>ne so wyn-drunke.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &eacute;uere segge &thorn;ine wife.</L>
<L N="272">alle &thorn;ine wille.</L>
<L>For if &thorn;u iseye &thorn;e bi-vore.</L>
<L>&thorn;ine i-vo alle.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u hi myd worde</L>
<L N="276">iwre&thorn;&thorn;ed heuedest.</L>
<L>Ne scholde heo hit lete.</L>
<L>for &thorn;ing lyuyinde.</L>
<L>&thorn;at heo ne scholde &thorn;e for&thorn; vp-breyde.</L>
<L N="280">of &thorn;ine baleu-sy&thorn;es.</L>
<L>wymmon is word.-wo&thorn;.</L>
<L>and haue&thorn; tunge to swift.
<PB REF="00000136.tif" N="120"></L>
<L>&thorn;eyh heo wel wolde.</L>
<L N="284">ne may heo. hi nowiht welde.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="17" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>17.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alfred.</L>
<L>IDelschipe and ouer-prute.<MILESTONE N="264" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&thorn;at lere&thorn; yong wif vuele &thorn;ewes.</L>
<L N="288">And ofte &thorn;at wolde.</L>
<L>do. &thorn;at heo ne scholde.</L>
<L>&thorn;ene vn&thorn;ev lihte.</L>
<L>leten heo myhte.</L>
<L N="292">If heo ofte a sw&oacute;te</L>
<L>for swunke were.</L>
<L>&thorn;eyh hit is vuel to buwe.</L>
<L>&thorn;at beo nule treowe.</L>
<L N="296">For ofte Muse&thorn; &thorn;e kat.</L>
<L>after hire moder.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;at let wymmon</L>
<L>his mayster iwur&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="300">Ne schal he neuer beon ihurd.</L>
<L>his wordes louerd.</L>
<L>Ac heo hine schal steorne</L>
<L>to-trayen. and to-te&oacute;ne.</L>
<L N="304">And selde wur&thorn; he bly&thorn;e and gled.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;at is his wiues qued.</L>
<L>Mony appel is bryht wi&thorn;-vte.</L>
<L>and Bitter wi&thorn;-inne.</L>
<L N="308">So is mony wymmon.</L>
<L>on hyre fader bure.</L>
<L>Schene vnder schete.</L>
<L>and &thorn;eyh heo is schendful.</L>
<L N="312">So is mony gedelyng.</L>
<L>godlyche on horse.</L>
<L>and is &thorn;eyh lutel wur&thorn;.</L>
<L>wlonk bi &thorn;e glede.</L>
<L N="316">and vuel at &thorn;are neode.
<PB REF="00000138.tif" N="122"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="18" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>18.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn;. Alured.</L>
<L>[N]Eure &thorn;u bi &thorn;ine lyue.</L>
<L>&thorn;e word of &thorn;ine wyue.</L>
<L N="320">to swi&thorn;e &thorn;u ne ar&eacute;de.</L>
<L>If heo beo i-wre&thorn;&thorn;ed</L>
<L>myd worde. o&thorn;er myd dede.</L>
<L>wymmon wepe&thorn; for mod.</L>
<L N="324">oftere &thorn;an for eny god.</L>
<L>And ofte lude and stille.</L>
<L>for to vordrye hire wille.</L>
<L>Heo wepe&thorn; o&thorn;er-hwile.</L>
<L N="328">for to do &thorn;e gyle.</L>
<L>Salomon hit haue&thorn; i-sed.</L>
<L>&thorn;at wymmon can wel vuelne red.</L>
<L>&thorn;e hire red folewe&thorn;.</L>
<L N="332">heo brynge&thorn; hine to seorewe.</L>
<L>for hit sey&thorn; in &thorn;e lo&thorn;.</L>
<L>as scumes forteo&thorn;.</L>
<L>hit is ifurn iseyd.</L>
<L N="336">&thorn;at cold red is quene red.</L>
<L>hu he is vnlede.</L>
<L>&thorn;at folewe&thorn; hire rede.</L>
<L>Ich hit ne segge nouht for &thorn;an.</L>
<L N="340">&thorn;at god &thorn;ing ys god wymmon.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;e hi may icheose.</L>
<L>and icouere over o&thorn;re.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="19" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>19.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="344">Monymon wene&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at he weny ne &thorn;arf.</L>
<L>Freond &thorn;at he habbe.</L>
<L>&thorn;ar me him vayre bi-hat.</L>
<L N="348">sey&thorn; him vayre bi-vore.</L>
<L>and frakele bi-hynde.
<PB REF="00000140.tif" N="124"></L>
<L>so me may &thorn;ane lo&thorn;e</L>
<L>lengust lede.</L>
<L N="352">Ne ilef &thorn;u neuer &thorn;ane mon.</L>
<L>&thorn;at is of feole speche.</L>
<L>Ne alle &thorn;e &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u iherest singe.</L>
<L N="356">Mony mon haue&thorn; swikelne mu&thorn;.</L>
<L>milde and monne for-cu&thorn;.</L>
<L>Nele he &thorn;e cu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>hwenne he &thorn;e wule bi-kache.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="20" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>20.</HEAD>
<L N="360">&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>&THORN;vrh sawe mon is wis.</L>
<L>And &thorn;urh his el&thorn;e. mon is glev.</L>
<L>&thorn;urh lesinge mon is lo&thorn;.</L>
<L N="364">and &thorn;urh lu&thorn;re wrenches. And<MILESTONE N="264b" UNIT="folio">vnwur&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;urh hokede honde. &thorn;at he bere&thorn;.</L>
<L>him seolue he for-vare&thorn;.</L>
<L>From lesynge &thorn;u &thorn;e wune.</L>
<L N="368">And alle vn&thorn;ewes &thorn;u &thorn;e bi-schune.</L>
<L>so myht &thorn;u on &thorn;eode.</L>
<L>leof beon in alle leode.</L>
<L>And luue &thorn;yne nexte.</L>
<L N="372">he is at &thorn;e neode g&oacute;d.</L>
<L>At chepynge. and at chyreche.</L>
<L>freond &thorn;u &thorn;e iwurche.</L>
<L>wy&thorn; pouere and wi&thorn; riche.</L>
<L N="376">wi&thorn; alle monne ilyche.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne myht &thorn;u sikerliche.</L>
<L>sely sytte.</L>
<L>And ek faren ouer lond le</L>
<L N="380">hwider so beo&thorn; &thorn;i wille.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="21" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>21.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>Alle world-ayhte
<PB REF="00000142.tif" N="126"></L>
<L>schulle bi-cumen to nouhte.</L>
<L N="384">And vyches cunnes madmes.</L>
<L>to mixe schulen i-Multen.</L>
<L>And vre owe lif.</L>
<L>lutel hwile ileste.</L>
<L N="388">for &thorn;eyh o mon.</L>
<L>wolde al &thorn;e worlde.</L>
<L>And al &thorn;e wunne.</L>
<L>&thorn;e &thorn;ar-inne wunye&thorn;.</L>
<L N="392">Ne myhte he &thorn;ar-myde his lif.</L>
<L>none hwile holde.</L>
<L>Ac al he schal for-leten.</L>
<L>on a litel stunde.</L>
<L N="396">And schal vre blisse;</L>
<L>to balewe us iwur&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Bute if we wurche&thorn;.</L>
<L>wyllen cristes.</L>
<L N="400">Nu bi&thorn;enche we &thorn;anne vs sulue.</L>
<L>vre lif to leden.</L>
<L>so crist vs gynne&thorn; lere.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne mawe we wenen.</L>
<L N="404">&thorn;at he wule vs wr&thorn;ie.</L>
<L>for so seyde salomon. &thorn;e wise.</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;at her wel de&thorn;.</L>
<L>he cume&thorn; &thorn;ar he lyen fo&thorn;.</L>
<L N="408">on his lyues ende.</L>
<L>he hit schal a-vynde.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="22" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>22.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L>NE gabbe &thorn;u ne schotte.</L>
<L N="412">ne chid &thorn;u wy&thorn; none sotte.</L>
<L>ne myd manyes cunnes tales.</L>
<L>ne chid &thorn;u wi&thorn; nenne dwales.</L>
<L>Ne neuer &thorn;u ne bi-gynne.</L>
<L N="416">to telle &thorn;ine ty&thorn;inges.
<PB REF="00000144.tif" N="128"></L>
<L>At nones fremannes borde.</L>
<L>ne haue &thorn;u to vale worde.</L>
<L>Mid fewe worde. wismon</L>
<L N="420">fele biluken wel con.</L>
<L>And sottes bolt is sone i-scohte.</L>
<L>for-&thorn;i ich holde hine for dote.</L>
<L>&thorn;at say&thorn; al his wille.</L>
<L N="424">&thorn;anne he scholde beon stille.</L>
<L>For ofte tunge breke&thorn; bon;</L>
<L>&thorn;eyh heo seolf nabbe non.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="23" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>23.</HEAD>
<L>&thorn;us que&thorn; Alured.</L>
<L N="428">Wis child is fader blisse.</L>
<L>If hit so bi-tyde&thorn;</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u bern ibidest.</L>
<L>&thorn;e hwile hit is lutel.</L>
<L N="432">ler him mon-&thorn;ewes.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne hit is <MILESTONE N="265" UNIT="folio">wexynde;</L>
<L>hit schal wende &thorn;ar-to.</L>
<L>&thorn;e betere hit schal iwur&thorn;e</L>
<L N="436">euer buuen eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Ac if &thorn;u him lest welde.</L>
<L>werende on worlde.</L>
<L>lude and stille.</L>
<L N="440">his owene wille.</L>
<L>hwanne cume&thorn; ealde.</L>
<L>ne myht &thorn;u hyne awelde.</L>
<L>&thorn;anne de&thorn; hit sone.</L>
<L N="444">&thorn;at &thorn;e bi&thorn; vnyqueme.</L>
<L>Ofer-howe&thorn; &thorn;in ibod.</L>
<L>and make&thorn; &thorn;e ofte sory-mod.</L>
<L>Betere &thorn;e were.</L>
<L N="448">iboren &thorn;at he nere.</L>
<L>for betere is child vnbore.</L>
<L>&thorn;ane vnbuhsum.
<PB REF="00000146.tif" N="130"></L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;e spare&thorn; yeorde.</L>
<L N="452">and yonge childe.</L>
<L>and let hit arixlye.</L>
<L>&thorn;at he hit areche ne may.</L>
<L>&thorn;at him schal on ealde;</L>
<L N="456">sore reowe. Amen.</L>
<L>Expliciunt dicta Regis Aluredi.<NOTE PLACE="end">[<I>End of Text I</I>.]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="103">
<HEAD>XV. The Proverbs of Alfred. TEXT II. [<I>From Wright's print in 'Reliqui&aelig; Antiqu&aelig;,' and Kemble's in his 'Dialogue of Salomon and Saturnus.'</I>]</HEAD>
<LG N="1" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>1.</HEAD>
<L>At Siforde</L>
<L>setin kinhis monie,</L>
<L>fele biscopis,</L>
<L N="4">and fele booc-lerede,</L>
<L>herles prude</L>
<L>and cnites egleche.</L>
<L>&THORN;er was erl Alfred,</L>
<L N="8">of &thorn;e lawe sui&thorn;e wis,</L>
<L>and heke Alfred,</L>
<L>Englene herde,</L>
<L>Englene derling;</L>
<L N="12">in Enkelonde he was king.</L>
<L>Hem he gon lerin,</L>
<L>so we mugen i-herin,</L>
<L>whu we gure lif</L>
<L N="16">lede sulin.</L>
<L>Alfred he was in Enkelonde a king,</L>
<L>wel swi&thorn;e strong and lufsum<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. lussum.</NOTE> &thorn;ing.</L>
<L>He was king and cleric,</L>
<L N="20">ful wel he louede Godes<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. Godes, W. Godis.</NOTE> were;</L>
<L>he was wis on his word,</L>
<L>and war on his werke;</L>
<L>he was &thorn;e wisiste mon</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;ad was in Engelonde on.
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="105"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="2" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>2.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred,</L>
<L>Englene frowere:</L>
<L>Wolde we, mi leden,</L>
<L N="28">lustin gure louird,</L>
<L>and he gu wolde wissin<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. wissen.</NOTE></L>
<L>of wi[s]liche &thorn;inges,</L>
<L>gu we migtin<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mistin.</NOTE> in werelde</L>
<L N="32">wrsipe weldin,</L>
<L>and heke gure sa[u]lle<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. salle.</NOTE></L>
<L>samne<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. samne, W. same.</NOTE> to Criste.</L>
<L>&THORN;is weren &thorn;e sawen</L>
<L N="36">of kinc Alfred:</L>
<L>Arme<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. Arme, W. Armo.</NOTE> and edie ledin.</L>
<L>of livis dom,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. lifis dom.</NOTE></L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="40">. . . . .</L>
<L>&thorn;ad we alle dredin</L>
<L>gure drigtin<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. dristin.</NOTE> Crist,</L>
<L>lovin him and likin,</L>
<L N="44">for he is louird ouir lif.</L>
<L>He is one god</L>
<L>ouer alle godnesse,</L>
<L>and he is gleu<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. gleu, W. gleues.</NOTE></L>
<L N="48">ouer alle glade &thorn;inhes;</L>
<L>he is one blisse</L>
<L>ouer alle blitnesse;</L>
<L>he is one mones<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. mon.</NOTE></L>
<L N="52">mildist maister;</L>
<L>he is one folkes</L>
<L>fadir and frowere;</L>
<L>he is one rigtewis,<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. riste|wis.</NOTE></L>
<L N="56">and suo riche king,</L>
<L>nat him sal ben wone</L>
<L>no &thorn;ing of is wille,
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="107"></L>
<L>wo him her on worolde</L>
<L N="60">wr&thorn;in &thorn;enket.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>3.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred,</L>
<L>Englene frouere:</L>
<L>May no riche king</L>
<L N="64">ben onder Crist selues,</L>
<L>bote &thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> he be booc-lerid,</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>and he writes wel kenne;</L>
<L N="68">. . . . .</L>
<L>and bote he cunne letteris,</L>
<L>lokin him seluen</L>
<L>wu he sule his lond</L>
<L N="72">laweliche holden.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>4.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Helfred:</L>
<L>&THORN;e herl and &thorn;e he&thorn;eling,</L>
<L>&thorn;o ben vnder &thorn;e king,</L>
<L N="76">&thorn;e lond to leden</L>
<L>mid lauelichi dedin;<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. lavelich i-dedin.</NOTE></L>
<L>bo&thorn;e &thorn;e clerc and &thorn;e cni[c]t<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. cnit.</NOTE></L>
<L>demen euenliche rict.</L>
<L N="80">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>For after<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. aftir.</NOTE> &thorn;at mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. man.</NOTE> souit,</L>
<L>als suyich<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. al suiyich.</NOTE> sal he mouin,</L>
<L N="84">and eueriches monnes dom</L>
<L>to his oge dure cherried.<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. cherried.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG N="5" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>5.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>&THORN;e cnith biouit</L>
<L N="88">kenliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. kerliche.</NOTE> to cnouen,</L>
<L>for to weriin &thorn;e lond of here
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="109"></L>
<L>and of heregong,</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e riche habbe gryt,</L>
<L N="92">and &thorn;e cherril be in frit</L>
<L>his sedis to souin,</L>
<L>his medis to mowen,</L>
<L>his plouis to driuin,</L>
<L N="96">to ure alre bi-lif;</L>
<L>&thorn;is is &thorn;e cnich[t]s<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. cnichs.</NOTE> lage,</L>
<L>loke &thorn;at hit wel fare.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>6.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Helfred:</L>
<L>Wid widutin wisdom</L>
<L N="120">is wele ful unwrd,
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="111"></L>
<L>for &thorn;au o mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. man.</NOTE> h[aue]de</L>
<L>hunt seuinti acreis,</L>
<L>and he al heged<NOTE PLACE="marg">? read <I>heuede</I>.</NOTE> [hit] sagin</L>
<L N="124">mid rede golde,</L>
<L>and &thorn;e golde greu<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. grue.</NOTE></L>
<L>so gres deit on &thorn;e rei&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &THORN;er&THORN;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>ne were hi[s]<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. i. . .</NOTE> wele</L>
<L N="128">nout &thorn;e vur&thorn;ere,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. wr&thorn;ere.</NOTE></L>
<L>bote he him fremede</L>
<L>frend y-werche.</L>
<L>For wad is g[old] bute ston,</L>
<L N="132">bute it<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. id.</NOTE> habbe wis mon?</L>
</LG>
<LG N="7" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>7.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>Sulde nefere gu[n]ge<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. gise, W. guge.</NOTE> mon</L>
<L>giuen him to huuele,</L>
<L N="136">&thorn;och he is<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. his.</NOTE> gise<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. gile.</NOTE></L>
<L>wel ne like . . ,</L>
<L>ne &thorn;ech he ne welde</L>
<L>al &thorn;ad he wolde;</L>
<L N="140">sor God may giuen wanne he wele</L>
<L>goed after yuil</L>
<L>wele after wrake;</L>
<L>ge wel him &thorn;et mot scapen.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="8" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>8.</HEAD>
<L N="144">&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>[Stron]ge <NOTE PLACE="marg">K. [Sor]ge.</NOTE> it his to rogen</L>
<L>agen &thorn;e se flod,</L>
<L>so it is<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. his.</NOTE> to swinkin<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sginkin.</NOTE></L>
<L N="148">again hinesel&thorn;e,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. heni sel&thorn;e.</NOTE></L>
<L>[a]ch wel<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. omits.</NOTE> is him ague&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. aguepe.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;e suinch<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sunich. <I>Read</I> swinkere.</NOTE> was,</L>
<L>wanen<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> wanne.</NOTE> her on werlde</L>
<L N="152">wel&thorn;e to winnen,
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="113"></L>
<L>[&thorn;at] he muge on helde</L>
<L>hednesse holdin;</L>
<L>migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. . . . mist, W. ne mist.</NOTE> his wel&thorn;e</L>
<L N="156">werchin Godis wille,</L>
<L>[&thorn;]enne his his gue&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. guewe.</NOTE></L>
<L>swi&thorn;e wel bitogen.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="10" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>10.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L N="160">Monimon wenit</L>
<L>&thorn;at he wenen ne &thorn;arf,</L>
<L>longer<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. longere.</NOTE> liuis,</L>
<L>ac him scal legen &thorn;at wrench;</L>
<L N="164">for wanne he is lif alre beste trowen,</L>
<L>&thorn;enne sal he letin lif his ogene.</L>
<L>Nis no wurt woxen</L>
<L>on woode ne<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. ne, W. no.</NOTE> on felde,</L>
<L N="168">&thorn;et<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;er.</NOTE> euure muge &thorn;e lif up helde.<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. uphelden.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wot no mon &thorn;e time</L>
<L>wanne he sal henne rimen,</L>
<L>ne no mon &thorn;en hende,</L>
<L N="172">wen he sal henne wenden;</L>
<L>Drittin<NOTE PLACE="marg">? Drictin.</NOTE> hit one wot,</L>
<L>domis louird,</L>
<L>wenne we ure lif</L>
<L N="176">letin scullen.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="9" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>9.</HEAD>
<L N="180">&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>Gif &thorn;u hauest wel&thorn;e a wold<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. awold.</NOTE></L>
<L>i &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. i-wis.</NOTE> gerlde ne &thorn;in wil neure for-&thorn;i</L>
<L>al to wlone wur&thorn;en,</L>
<L N="184">[ac]te<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. acte, W. [Ah]te.</NOTE> nis non eldere stren,
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="115"></L>
<L>ac it is Godis loue,</L>
<L>wanne hit is his wille,</L>
<L>&thorn;er-fro<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. wer fro.</NOTE> we sullen wenden,</L>
<L N="188">and ure ogene lif</L>
<L>mid sorw letin,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne scullen ure fon</L>
<L>to ure fe gripen,</L>
<L N="192">welden ure madmes</L>
<L>and lutil us bimenen.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="11" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>11.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfret:</L>
<L N="196">Leue &thorn;u &thorn;e nout to swi&thorn;e</L>
<L>up &thorn;e se-flod;</L>
<L>gif &thorn;u hawest madmes monie</L>
<L>and moch gold and siluir,</L>
<L N="200">it sollen wur&thorn;en to nout,</L>
<L>to duste it sullin<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sullen.</NOTE> driuen;</L>
<L>Drigtin<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. Dristin.</NOTE> sal liuin eure.</L>
<L>Monimon for is gold</L>
<L N="204">hauid Godis eire,</L>
<L>and &thorn;uruch is siluer</L>
<L>is saulle he for-lesed.</L>
<L>Betere him were</L>
<L N="208">i-borin &thorn;at he nere.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="12" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>12.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L N="212">Lustlike lustine<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. lustnie.</NOTE></L>
<L>. . lef dere,</L>
<L>and ich her gu wille leren</L>
<L>wenes mine,</L>
<L N="216">wit and wisdome,
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="117"></L>
<L>&thorn;e alle wel&thorn;e on ure god,</L>
<L>siker he may [sitten],</L>
<L>and hwo hem nu<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. mite.</NOTE> senden.</L>
<L N="220">For &thorn;och his wele&thorn;e him at-go,</L>
<L>is wid ne wen[t] him newere fro.</L>
<L>Ne may he newir for-farin,</L>
<L>hwo him to fere haue&thorn;,</L>
<L N="224">hwilis &thorn;at is lif</L>
<L>lesten may.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="13" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>13.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>Gif &thorn;u hauist sorwe,</L>
<L N="228">ne say &thorn;u hit &thorn;in arege;</L>
<L>seit &thorn;in sadilbowe,</L>
<L>and rid &thorn;e singende.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne sait &thorn;e mon</L>
<L N="232">&thorn;at ti wise ne can,</L>
<L>&thorn;ad &thorn;e &thorn;ine wise</L>
<L>wel &thorn;e likit.</L>
<L>Sorege gif &thorn;u hauist,</L>
<L N="236">and ten arege hit sed,</L>
<L>bi-foren he &thorn;e bimened,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. bimenid.</NOTE></L>
<L>bi-hindin he &thorn;e scarned.</L>
<L>&THORN;u hit migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mist.</NOTE> seien swich mon,</L>
<L N="240">&thorn;ad it &thorn;e ful wel on,</L>
<L>swich mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. men.</NOTE> &thorn;u maist seien &thorn;i sor,</L>
<L>he wolde &thorn;ad &thorn;u heuedest mor.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i hit in &thorn;in herte . . . one,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. hirte one.</NOTE></L>
<L N="244">for-hele hit wid &thorn;in arege,</L>
<L>let &thorn;u neuere &thorn;in arege witin</L>
<L>al &thorn;er &thorn;in herte &thorn;enket.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="16" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>16.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L N="248">Ne sal &thorn;u &thorn;i wif
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="119"></L>
<L>bi hire wlite chesen,</L>
<L>ne for non athte<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> achte.</NOTE> to &thorn;ine bury bringen,</L>
<L>her &thorn;u hire costes cu&thorn;e;</L>
<L N="252">for moni mon for<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. fer.</NOTE> athte<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> achte.</NOTE></L>
<L>iuele i-hasted,</L>
<L>and ofte mon on faire</L>
<L>sokel chesed.</L>
<L N="256">Wo is him &thorn;at iuel wif</L>
<L>brinhit to is cot-lif;</L>
<L>so his oliue</L>
<L>&thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;ai.</NOTE> iuele wiued,</L>
<L N="260">for he sal him often</L>
<L>dreri maken.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="264">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="17" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>17.</HEAD>
<L N="268">&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>Wur&thorn;u neuere swo wod,</L>
<L>ne so drunken,</L>
<L>&thorn;at euere sai &thorn;u &thorn;i wif</L>
<L N="272">al &thorn;at &thorn;i wille be.</L>
<L>For hif hue sege<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. segen.</NOTE> &thorn;e</L>
<L>biforen &thorn;ine fomen alle,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u hire mit worde</L>
<L N="276">wraged<NOTE PLACE="marg">?wra[n]ged.</NOTE> hauedest,</L>
<L>he ne sold it leten<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. letin.</NOTE></L>
<L>for &thorn;inke liuihinde,</L>
<L>&thorn;at he ne solde &thorn;e up-breidin</L>
<L N="280">of &thorn;ine bale-si&thorn;es.</L>
<L>Wimon is word-wod,</L>
<L>and hauit tunke to swist,<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> swift.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000137.tif" N="121"></L>
<L>&thorn;auc<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;ane.</NOTE> he hire selue wel wolde,</L>
<L N="284">ne mai he it nowit welden.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="21" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>21.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Idilscipe and orgul-prude,</L>
<L>&thorn;at lerit gung wif</L>
<L N="288">le&thorn;ere &thorn;ewes,</L>
<L>and often to &thorn;enchen</L>
<L>don &thorn;at he ne scolde.</L>
<L>Gif he for-swu[n]ken<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. for swuken, W. for-swuken.</NOTE></L>
<L N="292">swoti wuere<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;uere.</NOTE> swo hie ne &thorn;ochte,</L>
<L>ac &thorn;och hit is iuel to bewen<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. beuen.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at tertre<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. ter tre.</NOTE> ben ne wille;<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. ville.</NOTE></L>
<L>for ofte mused &thorn;e catt</L>
<L N="296">after &thorn;e moder.</L>
<L>Wose lat is wif his maister wur&thorn;en,</L>
<L>sal he neuer ben his wordes louerd;</L>
<L>ac<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. al.</NOTE> he sal him rere dreige,</L>
<L N="300">and moni tene selliche hawen:</L>
<L>selden sal he ben on sele.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="20" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>20.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Moni appel is wid-uten grene,</L>
<L>bri[c]t<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. brit.</NOTE> one<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. on.</NOTE> leme,</L>
<L>and bittere wid-innen.</L>
<L N="308">So his moni wimmon</L>
<L>in hire faire bure,</L>
<L>schene under schete,</L>
<L>and &thorn;ocke hie is [schendful]</L>
<L N="312">in an stondes wile.</L>
<L>Swo is moni gadeling</L>
<L>godelike on horse,</L>
<L>wlanc on werge,</L>
<L N="316">and unwur&thorn; on wike.
<PB REF="00000139.tif" N="123"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="25" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>25.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Uretu noth<NOTE PLACE="marg">? nocht.</NOTE> to swi&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;e word of &thorn;ine wiue;</L>
<L N="320">for &thorn;anne hue bed i-war&thorn;ed<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. i-wuar&thorn;|ed (?).</NOTE></L>
<L>mid wordes o&thorn;er mid dedes,</L>
<L>wimmon weped for mod</L>
<L>ofter &thorn;anne fro eni god,</L>
<L N="324">and ofte lude and stille</L>
<L>for to wurchen hire wille.</L>
<L>Hue weped o&thorn;er wile,</L>
<L>&thorn;en hue &thorn;e wille biwilen</L>
<L N="328">Salamon hid hawit i-sait,</L>
<L>hue can moni yuel reid.</L>
<L>Hue ne mai hit non o&thorn;ir don,</L>
<L>for wel herliche hue hit bi-gan.</L>
<L N="332">&THORN;e mon &thorn;ad hire red folewi&thorn;,</L>
<L>he bringe&thorn; him to soruge;<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. seruge.</NOTE></L>
<L>for hit is said in lede,</L>
<L>cold red is quene red.</L>
<L N="336">Hi ne sawe it<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. hit.</NOTE> nocht bi &thorn;an,</L>
<L>&thorn;at god &thorn;ing is god wimmon;</L>
<L>&thorn;e mon &thorn;ad michte hire cnoswen,<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> cnowen.</NOTE></L>
<L>and chesen hire from o&thorn;ere.</L>
<L N="340">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="19" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>19.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L N="344">Mani mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. man.</NOTE> wenit</L>
<L>&thorn;at he wenin ne &thorn;arf,</L>
<L>frend &thorn;ad he habbe,</L>
<L>&thorn;er mon him faire bi-hait,</L>
<L N="348">seiet him faire bi-foren,</L>
<L>fokel at-henden.
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="125"></L>
<L>So mon mai wel&thorn;e lengest helden,</L>
<L>giu &thorn;u neuere leuen</L>
<L N="352">alle monnis spechen,</L>
<L>ne alle &thorn;e &thorn;inke</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u herest sinken;</L>
<L>for moni mon hauit fikil mod,</L>
<L N="356">and he is monne cu&eth;.</L>
<L>Ne saltu neuere knewen</L>
<L>wanne he &thorn;e wole bipechen.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="23" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>23.</HEAD>
<L N="360">&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>&THORN;urch<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &THORN;urh.</NOTE> sage mon is wis,</L>
<L>and &thorn;urrh sel&thorn;e mon is gleu,</L>
<L>&thorn;urch<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;urh.</NOTE> lesin mon is lo&eth;,</L>
<L N="364">and<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. omits.</NOTE> &thorn;uruh lu&thorn;ere wrenches unwur&thorn;.</L>
<L>And hokede honden make &thorn;en mon</L>
<L>is hewit to lesen.</L>
<L>Ler &thorn;u &thorn;e neuer</L>
<L N="368">ouer mukil to le&thorn;en;</L>
<L>ac loke &thorn;ine<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;inne.</NOTE> nexte,</L>
<L>he is ate nede god;</L>
<L>and frendchipe<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. frendschipe.</NOTE> o werlde</L>
<L N="372">fairest to wurchen,</L>
<L>wid pouere and wid riche,</L>
<L>wid alle men i-liche,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne maist &thorn;u sikerliche</L>
<L N="376">seli sittin,</L>
<L>and faren ouer londe,</L>
<L>hwar so bet &thorn;i wille.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="380">. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="29" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>29.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Werldes wel&thorn;e
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="127"></L>
<L>to wurmes scal wur&thorn;ien,</L>
<L N="384">and alle cunne madmes</L>
<L>to nocht sulen melten,</L>
<L>and &thorn;ure<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> ure.</NOTE> lif sal lutel lasten.</L>
<L>For &thorn;u mon weldest</L>
<L N="388">al &thorn;is middelert,<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. middelle.</NOTE></L>
<L>and alle &thorn;e wel&thorn;e</L>
<L>&thorn;ad &thorn;e inne wonit,</L>
<L>ne migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. nust, K. mist.</NOTE> &thorn;u &thorn;i lif lengen</L>
<L N="392">none wile,</L>
<L>bote al &thorn;u it salt leten</L>
<L>one lutele stunde,</L>
<L>and al &thorn;i blisse</L>
<L N="396">to bale sal i-wur&thorn;en,</L>
<L>bote &thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> &thorn;u wurche</L>
<L>wille to Criste.</L>
<L>For bi&thorn;eng &thorn;e we mus<NOTE PLACE="marg">? muge.</NOTE> us selwen</L>
<L N="400">to leden ure lif,</L>
<L>so God us ginnid leten,</L>
<L>&thorn;enne muge we wenen</L>
<L>&thorn;ad he us wile wur&thorn;en.</L>
<L N="404">For swo saide Salomon,</L>
<L>&thorn;e wise Salomon:</L>
<L>wis is &thorn;ad wel do&thorn;</L>
<L>hwile he is in &thorn;is werld bo&thorn;,</L>
<L N="408">euere at &thorn;en ende</L>
<L>he comid &thorn;er he hit findit.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="26" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>26.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quod<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. quad.</NOTE> Alfred:</L>
<L>Be &thorn;u neuere to bold,</L>
<L N="412">to chiden agen oni scold,</L>
<L>ne mid mani tales</L>
<L>to chiden agen alle dwales.</L>
<L>Ne neuere &thorn;u biginne</L>
<L N="416">to tellin newe tidinges
<PB REF="00000145.tif" N="129"></L>
<L>at neuere nones monnis bord;</L>
<L>ne hawe &thorn;u to fele word.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wise mon mid fewe word</L>
<L N="420">can fele biluken;</L>
<L>and sottis bold is sone i-scoten.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i ich telle him for a dote,</L>
<L>&thorn;ad<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;at.</NOTE> sait al is y-wille,</L>
<L N="424">&thorn;anne he sulde ben stille:</L>
<L>for ofte tunke brekit bon,</L>
<L>and nauid hire selwe non.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="14" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>14.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L N="428">Wis child is fadiris blisse.</L>
<L>Gif it so bitidit</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u chil[d] weldest,</L>
<L>&thorn;e wile &thorn;at hit is litil</L>
<L N="432">&thorn;u lere him monnis &thorn;ewis;</L>
<L>&thorn;anne hit is woxin,</L>
<L>he sal wenne &thorn;erto;</L>
<L>&thorn;anne sal &thorn;e child</L>
<L N="436">&thorn;as &thorn;e bet wor&thorn;en.<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. wur&thorn;en.</NOTE></L>
<L>Ac gif &thorn;u les him welden</L>
<L>al his owene wille,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne he comit to helde,</L>
<L N="440">sore it sal him rewen;</L>
<L>and he sal banne &thorn;at wigt<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. widt.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at him first tagte.</L>
<L>&THORN;anne sal &thorn;i child</L>
<L N="444">&thorn;i forbod ouer-gangin.</L>
<L>Beter &thorn;e were<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;ere.</NOTE> child</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u ne hauedest;</L>
<L>for betere is child vnboren</L>
<L N="448">&thorn;enne vnbeten.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="131"></L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="452">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="456">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
<LG N="15" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>15.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alfred:</L>
<L>Drunken and vndrunkin</L>
<L N="460">e&thorn;er is wisdome wel god,</L>
<L>&thorn;arf no mon drinkin &thorn;e lasse,</L>
<L>&thorn;an he be wid-ale wis;</L>
<L>ac [gif]<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. [ef].</NOTE> he drinkit</L>
<L N="464">and desiet &thorn;ere a morge,</L>
<L>so &thorn;at he for drunken</L>
<L>desiende werchet,</L>
<L>he sal ligen long anicht,</L>
<L N="468">litil sal he sclepen;</L>
<L>him sugh sorege to,</L>
<L>so de&eth; &thorn;e salit on fles,</L>
<L>suket<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sukit.</NOTE> &thorn;uru is liche,</L>
<L N="472">so dot liche blod;</L>
<L>and his morge sclep</L>
<L>sal ben muchil estin,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. muchil lestin, W. umchilestin.</NOTE></L>
<L>werse &thorn;e swo on euen</L>
<L N="476">yuele haued y-dronken.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="18" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>18.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alvered:<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. Alured.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wur&thorn;u neuere so wod,</L>
<L>ne so desi of &thorn;i mod,</L>
<L N="480">&thorn;ad euere sige &thorn;i frend</L>
<L>al &thorn;at &thorn;e likit,</L>
<L>ne alle &thorn;e &thorn;onkes<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;onches.</NOTE>
<PB REF="00000148.tif" N="132"></L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u &thorn;och hauist;</L>
<L N="484">for ofte sibbie men</L>
<L>foken hem bituenen,</L>
<L>and ef it so bilimpit</L>
<L>lo[&thorn;]e<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. lo[o&thorn;]e.</NOTE> &thorn;at ge wur&thorn;en,</L>
<L N="488">&thorn;anne wot &thorn;i fend</L>
<L>&thorn;ad her wiste &thorn;i frend.</L>
<L>Betere &thorn;e bicome</L>
<L>&thorn;i word were helden,</L>
<L N="492">for &thorn;anne<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;am ue.</NOTE> mud mamelit</L>
<L>more &thorn;anne hit solde,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne sculen his heren</L>
<L>ef it i-herin.<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. iheren.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG N="22" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>22.</HEAD>
<L N="496">&para; &THORN;us quad Alfreuerd:</L>
<L>Gif &thorn;u frend bi-gete</L>
<L>mid &thorn;i fre bigete,</L>
<L>loke &thorn;at &thorn;u him &thorn;eine</L>
<L N="500">mid alle &thorn;euues<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;e uues.</NOTE> &thorn;ines,</L>
<L>loke &thorn;at he &thorn;e be mide</L>
<L>bi-foren and bi-hinden,</L>
<L>&thorn;e bett<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. bet.</NOTE> he sal &thorn;e reden</L>
<L N="504">at alle &thorn;ine neden.</L>
<L>And on him &thorn;u maist &thorn;e tresten,</L>
<L>&thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> is troy&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. trog&thorn;e.</NOTE> degh.</L>
<L>Ac gif &thorn;u hauist a frend to day,</L>
<L N="508">and to moreuin driuist him auei,</L>
<L>&thorn;enne bes &thorn;u one,</L>
<L>al so &thorn;u her were;</L>
<L>and &thorn;anne is &thorn;i fe for-loren,</L>
<L N="512">and &thorn;i frend bo&thorn;en.</L>
<L>Betere &thorn;e bicome frend</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u newedest.
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="133"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="24" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>24.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L N="516">Gif &thorn;u hauist duge,</L>
<L>and drich[t]en &thorn;e senden,</L>
<L>ne &thorn;eng &thorn;u neuere &thorn;i lif</L>
<L>to narruliche leden,</L>
<L N="520">ne &thorn;ine faires</L>
<L>to faste holden.</L>
<L>For wer hachte is hid,</L>
<L>&thorn;er is arm&thorn;e i-noch;</L>
<L N="524">and siker ich it te saige,</L>
<L>letet gif &thorn;e liket,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. licket.</NOTE></L>
<L>swich mon mai after &thorn;e &thorn;i god welden,</L>
<L>ofte<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. oft.</NOTE> binnen &thorn;ine burie</L>
<L N="528">bli&thorn;e wenden,</L>
<L>&thorn;ad he ne wele heren</L>
<L>mid mu&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. enn&thorn;e.</NOTE> monegen;</L>
<L>ac euere<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. evvere.</NOTE> him of-&thorn;inket,</L>
<L N="532">&thorn;en he &thorn;e &thorn;enked.<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;enced.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG N="27" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>27.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alvred:<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. Alfred.</NOTE></L>
<L>Elde cumid to tune,</L>
<L>mid fele unke&thorn;e costes;</L>
<L N="536">and do&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. do&thorn;e.</NOTE> &thorn;e man to helden,</L>
<L>&thorn;at him selwe ne mai he him noch welden.</L>
<L>Hit makit him wel vnmeke,</L>
<L>and binimit him is migte.<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. miste.</NOTE></L>
<L N="540">Gif<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &yogh;if.</NOTE> it swo bitided,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. betided.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u her so longe abidist,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u in &thorn;ine held<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. helde.</NOTE> werldes</L>
<L>wel&thorn;e weldest,</L>
<L N="544">&thorn;i duge&thorn;e gin<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. du&yogh;e&thorn;e giv.</NOTE> &thorn;u delen</L>
<L>&thorn;ine dere frend,</L>
<L>hwile &thorn;ine dages dugen,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u &thorn;e selwen liue mowe.
<PB REF="00000150.tif" N="134"></L>
<L N="548">Haue &thorn;u none leue</L>
<L>to &thorn;e &thorn;ad after &thorn;e bileued,</L>
<L>to sone ne to douter,</L>
<L>ne to none of &thorn;ine foster.</L>
<L N="552">For fewe frend we sculen finden,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne we henne funden:</L>
<L>for he &thorn;at is ute bi-loken,</L>
<L>he is inne sone for-geten.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="28" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>28.</HEAD>
<L N="556">&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Gif &thorn;u i &thorn;in helde best</L>
<L>wel&thorn;es bi-delid,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u ne cunne &thorn;e leden</L>
<L N="560">mid none cunnes listis,</L>
<L>ne &thorn;u ne moge mid strenghe</L>
<L>&thorn;e selwen steren,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne &thorn;anke &thorn;i louerd</L>
<L N="564">of alle is loue,</L>
<L>and of alle &thorn;ine owene liue,</L>
<L>and of &thorn;e dagis licht,</L>
<L>and of alle mur&thorn;e</L>
<L N="568">&thorn;ad he for mon makede.</L>
<L>And hweder so &thorn;u hwendes,</L>
<L>sei &thorn;u aten<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. at en.</NOTE> ende,</L>
<L>wr&thorn;e &thorn;ad i-wur&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="572">i-wur&thorn;e Godes wille.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="30" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>30.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Sone min swo leue,</L>
<L>site me nu bisides,</L>
<L N="576">and hich &thorn;e wile sagen</L>
<L>so&thorn;e &thorn;ewes.</L>
<L>Sone min, ich fele<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. fele, W. fala.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;ad min hew<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. hert.</NOTE> falewid&thorn;,
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="135"></L>
<L N="580">and min wlite is wan,</L>
<L>and min herte woc,</L>
<L>mine dagis arren nei done,</L>
<L>and we sulen unc to-delen;</L>
<L N="584">wenden ich me sal</L>
<L>to &thorn;is o&thorn;ir werlde,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u salt bileuen,</L>
<L>in alle mine wel&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="588">Sone min,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. mine.</NOTE> ich &thorn;e bidde,</L>
<L>&thorn;u ard mi barin dere,</L>
<L>&thorn;ad &thorn;u &thorn;i folck be fader,</L>
<L>and for louerd;</L>
<L N="592">fader be &thorn;u wid child,</L>
<L>and be &thorn;u wudewis<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. wuidewis.</NOTE> frend,</L>
<L>&thorn;e arme gume &thorn;u froueren,</L>
<L>and &thorn;e woke gume &thorn;u coueren,</L>
<L N="596">&thorn;e wronke gume<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. givve.</NOTE> &thorn;u rigtin<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. ristin.</NOTE></L>
<L>mid alle &thorn;ine migtin;<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mistin.</NOTE></L>
<L>and let &thorn;e sune mid lawe,</L>
<L>and lowien &thorn;e sulen Drigtin<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. Dri&yogh;ten.</NOTE></L>
<L N="600">and ower alle o&thorn;ir &thorn;inke</L>
<L>God be &thorn;e ful minde,</L>
<L>and bide &thorn;ad he &thorn;e rede</L>
<L>at alle &thorn;ine dedis,</L>
<L N="604">&thorn;e bet sal he<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. omits.</NOTE> &thorn;e filsten</L>
<L>to don al &thorn;ine wille</L>
</LG>
<LG N="31" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>31.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Sone min so dere,</L>
<L N="608">do so ich &thorn;e lere;</L>
<L>be &thorn;u wis on &thorn;i word,</L>
<L>and war o &thorn;ine speche,</L>
<L>&thorn;enne sulen<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sullen.</NOTE> &thorn;e lowien</L>
<L N="612">leden alle.</L>
<L>&THORN;e gunge mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. men.</NOTE> do &thorn;u lawe,
<PB REF="00000152.tif" N="136"></L>
<L>&thorn;ad helde lat is lond hawen.</L>
<L>Drunken mon &thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> &thorn;u mestes,<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> metes.</NOTE></L>
<L N="616">in weis o&thorn;er in stretes,</L>
<L>&thorn;u gef him &thorn;e weie reme</L>
<L>and let him ford gliden.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mist.</NOTE> &thorn;u &thorn;i lond</L>
<L N="620">mit<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. mid.</NOTE> frendchipe helden.</L>
<L>Sone, &thorn;u best bus<NOTE PLACE="marg">? buge.</NOTE> &thorn;e sot<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. fot, K. sot.</NOTE></L>
<L>of bismare word,</L>
<L>and bet him siwen &thorn;er-mide,</L>
<L N="624">&thorn;ad him ginne<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. givve.</NOTE> to smerten.</L>
<L>And baren, ich &thorn;e bidde,</L>
<L>&thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> &thorn;u on benche sitthest,</L>
<L>and &thorn;u &thorn;en beuir hore sixst</L>
<L N="628">&thorn;e bi-foren stonden,</L>
<L>buch &thorn;e from &thorn;i sete,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sette.</NOTE></L>
<L>and bide him sone &thorn;er-to,</L>
<L>&thorn;anne welle he sawin</L>
<L N="632">sone one his worde,</L>
<L>wel wor&thorn;e &thorn;e wid,</L>
<L>&thorn;ad &thorn;e first taite.</L>
<L>Sete &thorn;anne sei&thorn;in</L>
<L N="636">besiden him<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. bisiden hem.</NOTE> seluen,</L>
<L>for of him &thorn;u migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mist.</NOTE> leren</L>
<L>listes<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. listis.</NOTE> and fele &thorn;eues,</L>
<L>&thorn;e baldure &thorn;u migt<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. mist.</NOTE> ben;</L>
<L N="640">[ne] for-lere &thorn;u his reides,</L>
<L>for &thorn;e helder mon<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. man.</NOTE> me mai of-riden,</L>
<L>betere &thorn;enne of-reden.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="32" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>32.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L N="644">Sone min so dere,</L>
<L>ches &thorn;u neuere to fere</L>
<L>&thorn;en lu&thorn;ere lusninde mon,</L>
<L>for<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. fore.</NOTE> he &thorn;e wile<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. will.</NOTE> wrake don.
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="137"></L>
<L N="648">From &thorn;e wode &thorn;u micht<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. mitht.</NOTE> te faren</L>
<L>wid wilis and wid armes;</L>
<L>ac &thorn;anne &thorn;u hid lest wenest,</L>
<L>&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &thorn;u.</NOTE> lu&thorn;ere &thorn;e biswiket.</L>
<L N="652">&THORN;e bicche bitit ille,</L>
<L>&thorn;an he berke stille;</L>
<L>so deit &thorn;e lusninde lu&thorn;ere mon,</L>
<L>ofte &thorn;en he darit<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. dar it.</NOTE> don,</L>
<L N="656">&thorn;an he be wi&thorn;uten stille,</L>
<L>he bit wi&thorn;inin<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. wi&thorn;inen.</NOTE> hille,</L>
<L>and al he bi-fulit his frend,</L>
<L>&thorn;en he him vnfoldit.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="33" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>33.</HEAD>
<L N="660">&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Lewe sone dere,</L>
<L>ne ches &thorn;u<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &thorn;e.</NOTE> neuere to fere</L>
<L>&thorn;en hokerfule lese mon,</L>
<L N="664">for he &thorn;e wole gile don;</L>
<L>he wole stelin &thorn;in haite<NOTE PLACE="marg">? aihte.</NOTE> and keren,</L>
<L>and listeliche on-suerren;</L>
<L>so longe<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. longer.</NOTE> he uole<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. nole.</NOTE> be bi,</L>
<L N="668">he uole<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. nole.</NOTE> brinhin on and tuenti</L>
<L>to nout, for so&thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. sothe.</NOTE> ich tellit &thorn;e:</L>
<L>and o&thorn;er he wole li&thorn;en and hokerful ben,</L>
<L>&thorn;uru hoker and lesing &thorn;e alo&thorn;ed</L>
<L N="672">alle men &thorn;at hen y-cnowed.</L>
<L>Ac nim<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. min.</NOTE> &thorn;e to &thorn;e a stable mon,</L>
<L>&thorn;at word and dede bi-sette con,</L>
<L>and multeplien<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. multiplien.</NOTE> heure god,</L>
<L N="676">a sug fere &thorn;e his help in mod.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? niod.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG N="34" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>34.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;us quad Alured:</L>
<L>Leue sone dere,</L>
<L>ne ches &thorn;u neuere to fere
<PB REF="00000154.tif" N="138"></L>
<L N="680">littele mon, ne long, ne red,</L>
<L>&thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> &thorn;u wld don after mi red.</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e luttele mon he his so rei,</L>
<L>ne mai non him wonin nei;</L>
<L N="684">so word he wole him seluen bere,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. teir.</NOTE></L>
<L>&thorn;at his<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. is.</NOTE> louird maister he wolde tere;<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. &amp; W. beir.</NOTE></L>
<L>bute he mote himseluen pruden,</L>
<L>he wole maken fule luden;</L>
<L N="688">he wole grennen, cocken, and chiden,<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. chide.</NOTE></L>
<L>and hewere faren mid vnluden.</L>
<L>&THORN;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> &thorn;u me wld i-leuen,</L>
<L>ne mai me neuer him quemen.</L>
<L N="692">&para; &THORN;e lonke mon is le&thorn;e bei,</L>
<L>selde comid is herte rei;</L>
<L>he hauit stoni herte,</L>
<L>no &thorn;ing him ne smerte&thorn;;</L>
<L N="696">bi ford<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. biford.</NOTE> dages he is aferd,</L>
<L>of sticke and ston in huge werd.</L>
<L>&THORN;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> he fallit in &thorn;e fen,</L>
<L>he &thorn;ewit ut after men;</L>
<L N="700">&thorn;if<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> yif.</NOTE> he slit<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. slite.</NOTE> in-to a dige,</L>
<L>he is ded witerliche.</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e rede mon he is a quede,<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. quet.</NOTE></L>
<L>for he wole &thorn;e &thorn;in iwil<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. uvil.</NOTE> rede;<NOTE PLACE="marg">W. &amp; K. red.</NOTE></L>
<L N="704">he is cocker, &thorn;ef, and horeling,</L>
<L>scolde, of wrechedome he is king.</L>
<L>Hic ne sige nout bi &thorn;an,</L>
<L>&thorn;at moni ne ben gentile man;</L>
<L N="708">&thorn;uru &thorn;is lore<NOTE PLACE="marg">K. lere.</NOTE> and genteleri,</L>
<L>he amendit huge companie.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="16" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000155.tif" N="139">
<HEAD>XVI. An Orison of our Lord. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 265.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Tractatus quidam.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Louerd crist ich &thorn;e grete.</L>
<L>&THORN;u art so mylde and swete.</L>
<L>From heouene louerd &thorn;u hider come.</L>
<L N="4">And of &thorn;e swete mayde &thorn;u fleys n&oacute;me.</L>
<L>And hw hit ferde mon may esche.</L>
<L>&THORN;i goddede wes ihud in fleysse.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e mayde &thorn;u were ibore.</L>
<L N="8">God and mon so wel ic&oacute;re.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;u hire to c&oacute;me. heo mayde wes.</L>
<L>And mayde heo wes after wemmeles.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesuc ich &thorn;e gr&eacute;te. as ich er seyde.</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;u were ibore louerd of &thorn;e swete mayde.</L>
<L>&THORN;u vnderuenge al vre w&oacute;we.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-vte sunne. &thorn;at riht wule knowe.</L>
<L>As o&thorn;er childre. &thorn;u eodest and speke.</L>
<L N="16">Hunger and &thorn;urst. &thorn;u &thorn;oledest eke.</L>
<L>Buhsum and poure &thorn;u were iwis.</L>
<L>Forbysne &thorn;u vs yeue. and nouht amys.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesuc ich &thorn;e grete cryst louerd Min.</L>
<L N="20">&THORN;at for vs &thorn;oledest so swi&thorn;e muchel pyn.</L>
<L>Wunderliche &thorn;urh wacche. and fast.<NOTE PLACE="foot">A later hand has added <I>inge</I>, and to the next line <I>vor to &thorn;e us bringe</I>.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;i swete lychome &thorn;u teonedest.
<PB REF="00000156.tif" N="140"></L>
<L>God to donne and vuel to by-leue.<MILESTONE N="265b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="24">Ful gode vorbysne &thorn;u vs yeue.</L>
<L>No more luue ne may mon cheosen.</L>
<L>&THORN;ane de&thorn; to &thorn;olyen. for o&thorn;er to alesen.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesuc ich &thorn;e grete. &thorn;at were &thorn;ar harde ibunde.</L>
<L N="28">Wi&thorn; scurges &thorn;u &thorn;oledest mony blodi wunde.</L>
<L>Bi-vore &thorn;e he&thorn;ene men &thorn;u stode.</L>
<L>Naked and bylaued myd blode.</L>
<L>Buffetes &thorn;u &thorn;oledest inowe.</L>
<L N="32">Bi-spat &thorn;u were and al myd wowe.</L>
<L>Mid on red mantel &thorn;u were by-weued</L>
<L>Crune of &thorn;ornes. &thorn;u heuedest on heued.</L>
<L>Ne myhte &thorn;e mixes. &thorn;o wurse &thorn;e don.</L>
<L N="36">Bute a-mong &thorn;eoues. on rode an-hon.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;u &thorn;ol[e]dest for vre sake.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;e seorewe. &thorn;at heo &thorn;e myhte make.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesu crist &thorn;at so luuedest mon.</L>
<L N="40">Ich &thorn;e grete al so ich best con.</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;oledest. &thorn;at &thorn;i swete lich.</L>
<L>Of he&thorn;ene to-dreued wes sullych.</L>
<L>I&thorn;urled weren myd nayles &thorn;reo</L>
<L N="44">Honden and fet. faste to &thorn;e treo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at cold iren &thorn;u &thorn;oledest in &thorn;i syde.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;e spere kene to &thorn;in heorte glyde.</L>
<L>As &thorn;u &thorn;oledest &thorn;eos fyf wunde.</L>
<L N="48">Of seorewe and sunne. wite vs myd isunde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihesuc ich &thorn;e grete. And &thorn;at is wel ryht.</L>
<L>And &thorn;arto to don. bo&thorn;e mayn and myht.</L>
<L>For &thorn;e muchel &thorn;oleburne. and &thorn;ar-to don bo&thorn;e mayn and myht.</L>
<L N="52">&THORN;at &thorn;u schawedest mon-kunne. &thorn;o &thorn;u &thorn;oledest de&thorn;.</L>
<L>After alle &thorn;e pyne. &thorn;at &thorn;e runnen a blode.</L>
<L>&THORN;oledest louerd crist. &thorn;at me &thorn;e dude on rode.</L>
<L>Hwo so hit ileue&thorn; myd gode wille.<MILESTONE N="266" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="56">Ne may nouht &thorn;e feond. his saule a-spille.
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="141"></L>
<L>Ihesuc ich &thorn;e gr&eacute;te so wysslych.</L>
<L>As &thorn;u de&thorn; &thorn;oledest myldelich.</L>
<L>Ich &thorn;e bidde louerd &thorn;urh &thorn;e ilke rode.</L>
<L N="60">&THORN;ar &thorn;u myd blodie wunde stode.</L>
<L>On &thorn;ine werkes. so my lif leade.</L>
<L>And so do by &thorn;ine rede.</L>
<L>&THORN;at my saule habbe lysse.</L>
<L N="64">&THORN;at myn ende come to eche blysse. Amen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="17" TYPE="item">
<HEAD>XVII. The Duty of Christians. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 266.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Tractatus quidam.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;eo so&thorn;e luue a-mong vs beo.</L>
<L>wy&thorn;-vten euch endynge.</L>
<L>And crist vs lete wel i-&thorn;eo.</L>
<L N="4">and yue vs his blessynge.</L>
<L>And yeue vs &thorn;at we moten fleo.</L>
<L>euer sunegynge.</L>
<L>And &thorn;ene feond and al his gleo.</L>
<L N="8">and al his twyelinge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vte we wur&thorn;i &thorn;ene louerd god.</L>
<L>&thorn;at hider vs brouhte.</L>
<L>He wes wi&thorn; vs swi&thorn;e edmod.</L>
<L N="12">&thorn;ar he vs wrouhte.</L>
<L>And eft he wes ihonge on rode.</L>
<L>for helpe &thorn;ene vor-wrouhte.</L>
<L>Mid his fleysse and myd his blod.</L>
<L N="16">he vs alle bouhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Iblessed beo such e&thorn;erling.</L>
<L>vs mylce &thorn;at he wolde.</L>
<L>He is vre beste king.</L>
<L N="20">we ouhte beon hym holde.
<PB REF="00000158.tif" N="142"></L>
<L>And we beo&thorn; alle. his of-sprung.</L>
<L>iknowe we hit scholde.</L>
<L>For he scop vs and alle &thorn;ing.</L>
<L N="24">of &thorn;ar eor&thorn;e molde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Crist vs haue&thorn; of eor&thorn;e iwrouht.</L>
<L>to eor&thorn;e he wule vs sende.</L>
<L>Mid his de&thorn;e we weren ibouht</L>
<L N="28">from &thorn;e feondes bende.</L>
<L>He hit haue&thorn; al bi-&thorn;ouht.</L>
<L>&thorn;e frum&thorn;e to &thorn;on &eacute;nde.</L>
<L>How we beo&thorn; hider ibrouht.</L>
<L N="32">and hwider we schulle wende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>If we beo&thorn; ryhtwise.</L>
<L>and luuye&thorn; vre dryhte.</L>
<L>And do&thorn; his seruyse.</L>
<L N="36">myd al vre myhte.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;arf vs neuer a-gryse.</L>
<L>bi daye ne bi nyhte.</L>
<L>We schulle in paradys[e].</L>
<L N="40">schynen swi&thorn;e bryhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Is world is neyh &thorn;an ende.</L>
<L>&thorn;e de&thorn; neye&thorn; blyue.</L>
<L>Heonne we schullen wende.<MILESTONE N="266b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="44">ne may non her bi-leue.</L>
<L>&THORN;e dom. is vs neyh hende.</L>
<L>yef we vs lete&thorn; schryue.</L>
<L>Crist vs wile sende.</L>
<L N="48">to &thorn;on eche lyue.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vte we holde &thorn;at ilche bod.</L>
<L>&thorn;at crist vs wile theche.</L>
<L>He yef vs li&thorn; and de&thorn; anfo&thorn;.</L>
<L N="52">he is vre leache.</L>
<L>Vre euch beo wi&thorn; o&thorn;er edmod.</L>
<L>on werke and of speche.
<PB REF="00000159.tif" N="143"></L>
<L>Elles vre louerd god.</L>
<L N="56">on vs wulle don wreche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mid gode beode myd gode &thorn;onk.</L>
<L>we schule to criste grede.</L>
<L>And bidde mylce of vre wrong.</L>
<L N="60">of vre gydihede.</L>
<L>Of vre sunnen &thorn;at beo&thorn; wel strong.</L>
<L>of vre fule dede.</L>
<L>Hwenne cume&thorn; he vs among.</L>
<L N="64">and wile vs myd him lede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vre louerd crist vs wule t&eacute;o.</L>
<L>to heouene myd iwisse.</L>
<L>If we wulle&thorn; vuel fleo.</L>
<L N="68">ne &thorn;urue [we] &thorn;at mysse.</L>
<L>Wel is him &thorn;at schal &thorn;er beo.</L>
<L>he may &thorn;er habbe lysse.</L>
<L>He may &thorn;er. euer crist iseo.</L>
<L N="72">and ioye inouh. and blysse.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er wur&thorn; day buten nyhte.</L>
<L>ne &thorn;arf &thorn;ar no mon syche.</L>
<L>Hwer for&thorn;<NOTE PLACE="foot">? &THORN;er wur&thorn;.</NOTE> gri&thorn; wy&thorn;-vten fiht.</L>
<L N="76">wel god is heoueneriche.</L>
<L>&THORN;er wur&thorn; so&thorn; wi&thorn;-vten vnriht.</L>
<L>and euer hit wur&thorn; ilyche.</L>
<L>&THORN;er wur&thorn; euenyng. carle<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. clare.</NOTE> and cnyht.</L>
<L N="80">poure men and riche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. Ve.</NOTE> so&thorn;e luue is heom among</L>
<L>and mylce and ryhtwisnesse.</L>
<L>Rihte bi-leue and clene &thorn;onk.</L>
<L N="84">and sibbe and edmodnesse.</L>
<L>Ne wur&thorn; &thorn;er vnryht ne wrong.</L>
<L>ne wre&thorn;&thorn;e ne idelnesse.</L>
<L>&THORN;er wur&thorn; ioye and mury song.</L>
<L N="88">wi&thorn;-vte swikelnesse.
<PB REF="00000160.tif" N="144"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>If we wulle&thorn; &thorn;ider in.</L>
<L>to &thorn;are riche wunynge.</L>
<L>Idelschipe. and lu&thorn;er iwyn.</L>
<L N="92">and wra&thorn;&thorn;e and hatynge.</L>
<L>Prude and onde and feondes gyn.</L>
<L>and vyche sunegynge.</L>
<L>We mote for-sake. er vre fyn.</L>
<L N="96">and do &thorn;er-of [mendinge]<NOTE PLACE="foot">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>We schulde among vs habben ay.</L>
<L>so&thorn;e luue and sibbe.</L>
<L>We schulde abute cristes lay.</L>
<L N="100">beon yeornfulle. and clybbe.</L>
<L>We schulde luuye alle way.</L>
<L>for we beo&thorn; alle isybbe.</L>
<L>And vs ibidde. nyht and day.<MILESTONE N="267" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="104">hwihles &thorn;at we libbe.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e so&thorn;e luue is god and mylde.</L>
<L>nys heo nowiht sturne.</L>
<L>Nis heo nou&thorn;er prut ne wilde.</L>
<L N="108">nele heo non ayhte yrne.</L>
<L>&THORN;at folk wor&thorn; eft wro&thorn;e i-spild.</L>
<L>&thorn;e nule to hire turne.</L>
<L>Ihesuc seynte Marie child.</L>
<L N="112">heom wule his riche werne.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e so&thorn;e luue is al rihtwis.</L>
<L>ne kepe&thorn; heo non onde.</L>
<L>Mid &thorn;an folke &thorn;at riht wis is.</L>
<L N="116">he wile ay at-stonde.</L>
<L>Vre louerd crist &thorn;at almyhti is.</L>
<L>alese vs of his bonde.</L>
<L>And lede vs in-to heouene blys.</L>
<L N="120">and sette vs on his ryht honde. Amen.
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="18" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000161.tif" N="145">
<HEAD>XVIII. The Shires and Hundreds of England. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 267.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Her bigynne&thorn; &thorn;e syren. and &thorn;e hundredes of enge|londe.</HEAD>
<P>ENgle lond is. eyhte hundred Myle long. from penwy&thorn; steorte. &thorn;at is fyft&eacute;ne Mylen by-yonde Mihhales steowe. on cornwale. fort &thorn;at cume. to katenes. &thorn;e breade of Engle londe is. &thorn;reo hundred myle brod. from Dewyes steowe. to Doueran. On engle londe syndon. two and &thorn;rytti schire. summe more and summe lasse. And &thorn;reottene byscopryche. And two erchebiscopryche. &thorn;at is alles. vyftene biscopryche. On is &thorn;e erche|biscophryche of Kanterbury. O&thorn;e &thorn;e leod biscopryche. on Rouecestre. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde on lundene. &thorn;e feor&thorn;e. on Nor&thorn;wych. &thorn;e fyfte; on Cicestre. &thorn;e sexte. on wyncestre. &thorn;e seoue&thorn;e on saresbury. &thorn;is bispryche wes hwylen. two bispriche. &thorn;eo o&thorn;er st&oacute;l. wes at remmesbury. And &thorn;e o&thorn;er at schireburne. Ac eadward king. bitauhte &thorn;eos two. Heremon biscop. And he myd &thorn;es kinges leaue Adylegade. &thorn;a twa noman. and makede enne; at sares|buri. &thorn;e eyhteo&thorn;e. on excestre. &thorn;is wes ek two bispriche. O&thorn;er on cornwale. and &thorn;e stol wes at seynte Germane. and &thorn;e o&thorn;er stol; at Bridyport. Ac leofrych biscop. hit makede to one; myd eadwardes kynges leaue. And sette hit to excestre. &thorn;e Nye&thorn;e; on Ba&thorn;un. Ac &thorn;es stol; wes at welle. <MILESTONE N="267b" UNIT="folio">And Ba&thorn;e wes Abbodryche. And on willames daye &thorn;e yonger kynges. wes &thorn;at Abboddie by-numen. And imaked &thorn;er Bisscop stol. &thorn;urh 
<PB REF="00000162.tif" N="146"> iohan. &thorn;e teou&thorn;e on wirecestre. &thorn;e eollefte on hereforde. &thorn;e tweolfte. on lycchesfeld. &thorn;e &thorn;reotteo&thorn;e. on lyncholne. Ac &thorn;is wes hwile. &thorn;reo bisscop-riche. for-&thorn;i her-to here&thorn; .viii. store schire. and on half schire .xiiii. on Dunholme. xv. on Euerwich. &thorn;is wes .v. bispriche. On &thorn;e erche|bisscop-riche. O&thorn;er. on o&thorn;er half &thorn;es wateres .iij. on Rypun .iiij. on hwytebi .v. at beuerley. Her beo&thorn; .xv. bispryche.</P>
<P>Swo we biforan que&thorn;en .xxxij. schiren. syndan. on engelonde. And Nor&thorn;humbre; is wi&thorn;-vtan. And lo&eth;en. and westmara-lond. and Cumberlond. And Cornwale. On Cornwale syndan .vii. lutle schire. And scotlaund. And Brutlaund. And wyht. &THORN;es .xxxij. schire syndon. to-delede on &thorn;reo lawan. On is west-sexene lawe. O&thorn;er Dene lawe. &thorn;e &thorn;rydde Mercena lawe. To west-sexene lawe; bi-lympe&thorn; .ix. schiren. <MILESTONE UNIT=".i."> Kent  <MILESTONE UNIT="ii."> su&thorn;sexe.  <MILESTONE UNIT=".iii."> su&thorn;eray.  <MILESTONE UNIT=".iiii."> Bearruc  schire. <MILESTONE UNIT=".v."> wiltone  schire. On wiltone schire. syndon .xlviii. hundred hida. <MILESTONE UNIT=".vi."> su&thorn;|hampton.  schire. <MILESTONE UNIT=".vii."> sumerseth  schire. <MILESTONE UNIT=".viii."> Dorset  schire. <MILESTONE UNIT=".ix."> Deuena  sch[i]re. To Dene lawe. bilympe&thorn;. xv. schire. Everwich schire. Snotingham. Deoreby schire. Leycestre schire. Lyncolne schire. Hertford schire. Bukingham schire. su&thorn;folk. Nor&thorn;folc. Bedeford. sch[i]re .xii. hun|dred hyda. Eastsexe. Grauntebrugge schire .xxv. hun|dred hida. Huntyndune schire; viij. hundred hida. and half hundred. Norhamtone schire .xxxij. hundred. hida. Middelsex. To Mercene lawe; bilimpe&thorn; .viij. schiren. Gloucestre schire; xxxiiij. hundred hida. wyricestre schire; .xij. hundred hida. Hereford schire; xij. hundred hida. warewik schire; xij. hundred hida. Oxeneford schire; xxiiij. <MILESTONE N="268" UNIT="folio">hundred hida. Slobschire; xxiiij. hundred hida. Chestre schire; .xij. hundred hida. Stafford schire .v. hundred hida. &thorn;is is vnder al; xxvi. &thorn;usend hida. and on half hundred.
</P>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000163.tif" N="147">
<HEAD>The xi Pains of Hell. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 271, <I>col.</I> 2.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Ici comencent les vnze peynes de enfern. les queus seynt pool v[ist]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>PLest uus oyer vne demaunde.</L>
<L>Ke li deable fist estraunge.</L>
<L>De vn cheytif pecch&eacute;ur.<NOTE PLACE="foot">The accents used in the French lines are not in the MS.</NOTE></L>
<L N="4">Ke hors fu mys de grant tristur.</L>
<L>De mort en vie resuscit&eacute;</L>
<L>Par la volunt&eacute; de D&eacute;.</L>
<L>VNsely gost hwat dostu here.</L>
<L N="8">&THORN;u were in helle myne vere.</L>
<L>Hwo haue&thorn; helle dure vnloke.</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;u ert of pyne ibroke.</L>
<L>Dvnke respund le mort a lu</L>
<L N="12">En le secle v il fu.</L>
<L>Cunte en ordre e cunte. &amp; dist.</L>
<L>Les .xi. peynes ke seynt pol vist.</L>
<L>Des autres ke il an senty</L>
<L N="16">Vn sul mot ne menty.</L>
<L>Wiltu ihere me sathan.</L>
<L>Hw ich am of helle igan.</L>
<L>Wrmes habbe&thorn; my fleys ifreten.</L>
<L N="20">And Mine freond me habbe&thorn; foryeten.</L>
<L>Ich mon wes. as &thorn;u wel wost.</L>
<L>And nv ich &aacute; wrecche gost.<MILESTONE N="271b:1" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>In helle ich habbe yare ibeo.</L>
<L N="24">&THORN;at mon may on myn hewe iseo.
<PB REF="00000164.tif" N="148"></L>
<L>Of me mon may forbysne taken.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wile his sunnes for-saken.</L>
<L>To wro&thorn;ere hele he wes ibore.</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;at for sunnes is for-lore.</L>
<L>For &thorn;e mon &thorn;at her wrche&thorn; swo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at his saule to helle g&oacute;.</L>
<L>In mo pyne he schal beo.</L>
<L N="32">&THORN;an foweles vnder heouene fleo.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="1" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Erest &thorn;er beo&thorn; bernynde treon.</L>
<L>No mon ne may herre iseon.</L>
<L>&THORN;er &thorn;e saulen beo&thorn; an-h&oacute;n.</L>
<L N="36">&THORN;at her habbe&thorn; sunnes i-don.</L>
<L>And nolden neuer to chireche gon.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i hi &thorn;olie&thorn; &thorn;er such won.</L>
<L>&THORN;ickure hi honge&thorn; &thorn;er ouer al.</L>
<L N="40">&THORN;an don been in wynterstal.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="2" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;en &thorn;er is on ouen ihat.</L>
<L>Seoue deoulen &thorn;ar stonde&thorn; at.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e saulen vnder-fo&thorn;.</L>
<L N="44">And heom in-to &thorn;e fure do&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;inges &thorn;er beo&thorn; al abuten.</L>
<L>&THORN;at mon auhte muchel duten.</L>
<L>Snov. and is. and lyured blod.</L>
<L N="48">Snaken. and neddren. stinge&thorn; for wod.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;at fur heo do&thorn; heom &thorn;er.</L>
<L>And eft also hi weren er.</L>
<L>Hwich saule. &thorn;e &thorn;er cume&thorn; to.</L>
<L N="52">Naue&thorn; heo neuer reste ne ro.</L>
<L>Heo wolde deye. ac heo ne may.</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;er heom tyd beon alne way.<MILESTONE N="271b:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Swich pyne heo &thorn;olie schal.</L>
<L N="56">&THORN;at wes of his fleysse to gal.</L>
<L>And nolde leten his fleysses wil.</L>
<L>Ac folewede al &thorn;at wes vnskil.</L>
<L>And &thorn;er heo &thorn;olye&thorn; swich wondrawen.</L>
<L N="60">&THORN;at her arereden vnryhte lawen.
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="149"></L>
<L>&THORN;ider cume&thorn; &thorn;e saulen ilome.</L>
<L>&THORN;at her demde false domes.</L>
<L>Mo saulen. &thorn;olie&thorn; &thorn;er swich wo.</L>
<L N="64">&THORN;ene fysses swimme o&thorn;er fueles go.</L>
<L>Heo grede&thorn; lude and wepe&thorn; sore.</L>
<L>Ac b&oacute;te. ne tyd heom neuer more.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3" TYPE="stanza">
<L>A hwel of stele is fur&thorn;er mo.</L>
<L N="68">And berne&thorn; lihte and turne&thorn; o.</L>
<L>A &thorn;usend spoken beo&thorn; &thorn;er-on.</L>
<L>And pykes ouer al idon.</L>
<L>&THORN;er schule &thorn;e saulen beo to-drawe.</L>
<L N="72">&THORN;at her arereden vnryhte lawe.</L>
<L>Mo saulen &thorn;olie&thorn; &thorn;er sucche wowe.</L>
<L>&THORN;ane be flo&thorn;re in &thorn;e snowe.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Fvr&thorn;er &thorn;er is a water wallinde hot.</L>
<L N="76">&THORN;at is. deop. and long. and brod.</L>
<L>Blakkure &thorn;an &thorn;e swarte pich.</L>
<L>And stynke&thorn; so for-holde lych.</L>
<L>Of vych a wrm &thorn;at atter bere&thorn;.</L>
<L N="80">O&thorn;er hit stinge&thorn; o&thorn;er hit tere&thorn;</L>
<L>Ifulled is &thorn;at fule pool</L>
<L>&THORN;at euer is hot. and neuer cool.</L>
<L>Bisydes stonde&thorn; an feondes trume.</L>
<L N="84">And wayte&thorn; hwenne &thorn;e saules cume.</L>
<L>Heo hire a-warie&thorn; al a&thorn;rep.</L>
<L>Al so wulues do&thorn; &thorn;e scep.<MILESTONE N="272:1" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Hwenne &thorn;e feondes heom for-lete&thorn;.</L>
<L N="88">Snaken and neddren heom imete&thorn;.</L>
<L>And dreye&thorn; heom in-to a wel.</L>
<L>&THORN;er heo &thorn;olye&thorn; al vn-sel.</L>
<L>Hwenne heo habbe&thorn; so i-don.</L>
<L N="92">Eft hit beo&thorn; heom al fornon.</L>
<L>Ne may he segge. waylawei.</L>
<L>&THORN;at so schule pynen nyht. and day.</L>
<L>Summe me may &thorn;er iseon.</L>
<L N="96">&THORN;at stonde&thorn; vp to heore kneon.
<PB REF="00000166.tif" N="150"></L>
<L>And summe to heore myd-&thorn;eyh.</L>
<L>And summe to heore vuere breyh.</L>
<L>And summe riht to heore the&thorn;.</L>
<L N="100">As he her his sunnes de&thorn;.</L>
<L>Bakbiteres weren &thorn;eo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at stonde&thorn; vp to heore kneo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wes heore o&thorn;er copynere.</L>
<L N="104">Stonde&thorn; vp to heore swere.</L>
<L>And heo &thorn;at her wedlac breke&thorn;.</L>
<L>To heore mu&thorn;e &thorn;e flod take&thorn;.</L>
<L>He &thorn;at is glad of o&thorn;res harme.</L>
<L N="108">Stonde&thorn; vp in-to &thorn;an arme.</L>
<L>&THORN;at spek in chirche. &thorn;at nes no god.</L>
<L>To his mu&thorn;e take&thorn; &thorn;e flod.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wreye&thorn; his sibbe. o&thorn;er him fled.</L>
<L N="112">Abuuen his eyen. &thorn;e flod ge&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;at do&thorn; his wil &thorn;at nys noht ryht.</L>
<L>Of him ne may me iseo nowiht.</L>
<L>Hwo is wis bi me beo war.</L>
<L N="116">&THORN;at his saule ne cume &thorn;ar.</L>
<L>For &thorn;eyh &thorn;e Middenerd ago.</L>
<L>Heore pyne ileste&thorn; .o.<MILESTONE N="272:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="5" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Uvr&thorn;ur. is a ful deop fen.</L>
<L N="120">Ful of wowares. and of wymmen.</L>
<L>&THORN;e stude is &thorn;ustrore. &thorn;ene &thorn;e nyht.</L>
<L>For &thorn;er. ne cume&thorn; neuer lyht.</L>
<L>And stinke&thorn; fulre &thorn;ane &thorn;e hund.</L>
<L N="124">For Brunston walle&thorn; at &thorn;e grund.</L>
<L>Ten &thorn;usend feondes. and wel mo.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar frete&thorn; heore tunge a two.</L>
<L>And dreye&thorn; vt heore brayn.</L>
<L N="128">Vor heo weren of gauele vayn.</L>
<L>Such is heore pyne &thorn;er.</L>
<L>Vor heo weren gauelers her.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne beo&thorn; &thorn;e wymmen fur&thorn;er i-don.</L>
<L N="132">&THORN;at nowiht nabbe&thorn; heom up-on.
<PB REF="00000167.tif" N="151"></L>
<L>Heom me drepe&thorn; myd &thorn;e piche.</L>
<L>As we brede wi&thorn; &thorn;e spiche.</L>
<L>Neddren heore breosten suke&thorn;.</L>
<L N="136">And snakes heore eyen luke&thorn;.</L>
<L>Helle hundes gnawe&thorn; heore feet.</L>
<L>And four feondes heom stonde&thorn; at.</L>
<L>For heo heore mayden-hod lure.</L>
<L N="140">Er heo come to chireche dure.</L>
<L>And furduden heore istreon.</L>
<L>&THORN;at hit ne moste ifulled beon.</L>
<L>Heo hit wurpen hundes o&thorn;er swin.</L>
<L N="144">For-&thorn;i hi &thorn;olie&thorn; &thorn;ar such pyn.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Uvr&thorn;er &thorn;er beo&thorn; wimmen. and wapmen bo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at feondes dreye&thorn; al a two.</L>
<L>Hwenne hi beo&thorn; so to-drawen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. to-drayen.</NOTE></L>
<L N="148">Gripes frete&thorn; heore Mawen.</L>
<L>Half heo do&thorn; in o fur.</L>
<L>And half in-to a froren mur.<MILESTONE N="272b:1" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>And heore ineward vych del.</L>
<L N="152">Ne beo &thorn;e &thorn;arm ne so smel.</L>
<L>Eft heo werpe&thorn;. al in al.</L>
<L>And wurche&thorn; to &thorn;at ilke gal.</L>
<L>Vuele heo beo&thorn; ipyned ynouh.</L>
<L N="156">&THORN;at her duden wi&thorn; heom woh.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er reueden wrecches heore lond.</L>
<L>And brohten heom to muchel scond.</L>
<L>He ne funde fader ne freond hom by.</L>
<L N="160">For-&thorn;i me drof hom of londe awy.</L>
<L>Of heom hi token vnriht mol.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i hi draye&thorn; myd such sol.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="7" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Uvr&thorn;er &thorn;er is o wateres flod.</L>
<L N="164">&THORN;at is ymeynd al wi&thorn; blod.</L>
<L>A &thorn;usen[d] saulen &thorn;er beo&thorn; bi.</L>
<L>Sore of-&thorn;urst and ful hungri.</L>
<L>In fure hi berne&thorn; al<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Or</I> as.</NOTE> awey.
<PB REF="00000168.tif" N="152"></L>
<L N="168">And so do&thorn; &thorn;at water nyht and day.</L>
<L>Ne moten heo biden neuer o sope.</L>
<L>Nabben heo neuer so muche hope.</L>
<L>Such pine hi habbe&thorn; imet.</L>
<L N="172">&THORN;at breken &thorn;e hesten &thorn;at weren iset.</L>
<L>In holy chirche ouer al.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i hi pleye&thorn; myd such bal.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="8" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vvr&thorn;er &thorn;er beo&thorn; olde men.</L>
<L N="176">&THORN;at among neddren. habbe&thorn; heore den.</L>
<L>Heom heo to-stynge&thorn; vychon.</L>
<L>And frete&thorn; heore fleys. to &thorn;e bon.</L>
<L>And neddren suke&thorn; heore brayn</L>
<L N="180">And creope&thorn; vt. and in ayeyn.<MILESTONE N="272b:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Summe beo&thorn; fur-brend. and summe ifrore.</L>
<L>And alle &thorn;e bones beo&thorn; to-drore.</L>
<L>Hwenne hi beo&thorn; ifrete vychon.</L>
<L N="184">Eft hi beo&thorn; al in on.</L>
<L>Noht for to wenden heom from.</L>
<L>Ac for eft &thorn;olie &thorn;at wrecchedom.</L>
<L>Heo wone&thorn; and grone&thorn; day and nyht.</L>
<L N="188">Ac hit ne helpe&thorn; heom nowiht.</L>
<L>For heo nolden beon ischriven.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwile &thorn;at hi mosten lyuen.</L>
<L>Four deofle heom stonde&thorn; bi.</L>
<L N="192">&THORN;at pyne&thorn; heom ful revly.</L>
<L>Vnsely men. hwi neren hi war.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwile &thorn;at hi lyueden her.</L>
<L>Hwi nolden heo don. for him no god.</L>
<L N="196">&THORN;at heom lesede wy&thorn; his blod.</L>
<L>And yef vs. hus. and lond. and wif.</L>
<L>And wit and wisdom. and Ioye. and lyf.</L>
<L>And al &thorn;at wes in worlde god.</L>
<L N="200">And non of heom. hit ne vnderstod.</L>
<L>Heo nolden noht. &thorn;enche &thorn;er-on.</L>
<L>Ne poure wrecches no god don.</L>
<L>Heo wenden. hit scholde lesten .o.
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="153"></L>
<L N="204">For-&thorn;i heo beo&thorn; in suche wo.</L>
<L>Preostes heste. ne godes lay.</L>
<L>Ne heolden hi noht bi heore day.</L>
<L>Ac trichurs. and lyeres. and les;</L>
<L N="208">&THORN;at weren her. wo is ham &thorn;es.</L>
<L>Ne wenden heo neuer-more beon ded</L>
<L>For &thorn;at wes. &thorn;es feondes red.<MILESTONE N="273:1" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ac euer as heo lyueden lengur.</L>
<L N="212">So here pynen were strengur.</L>
<L>Heo beo&thorn; iput. in &thorn;ilke trume.</L>
<L>&THORN;at ne leuede nouht in godes sone.</L>
<L>Ne &thorn;at ihesuc wes iboren.</L>
<L N="216">Of &thorn;at Mayde &thorn;at wes icoren.</L>
<L>For to nymen &thorn;at holy streon.</L>
<L>Wel wes him. &thorn;at hit moste i-seon.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="9" TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN helle is &aacute; deop gayhol.</L>
<L N="220">&THORN;ar-vnder is a ful hot pol.</L>
<L>Ten &thorn;usend deoflen. and wel mo.</L>
<L>&THORN;er do&thorn; &thorn;e wrecche saulen wo.</L>
<L>&THORN;at nyme&thorn; eaules and heom to-tere&thorn;.</L>
<L N="224">Nis &thorn;er non. &thorn;at heom at-dare&thorn;.</L>
<L>Ho stonde&thorn;. &thorn;ustrur &thorn;ane &thorn;e nyht.</L>
<L>&THORN;eo &thorn;at demde iesu crist.</L>
<L>Nis non o&thorn;er pine so strong.</L>
<L N="228">As &thorn;e stunch. &thorn;at heom is among.</L>
<L>An heyh to-fore &thorn;an heuene king.</L>
<L>Of heom ne speke&thorn; me no&thorn;ing.</L>
<L>Ne dar no seynt heom bidde fore.</L>
<L N="232">For-&thorn;i heo beo&thorn; euer fur-lore.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="10" TYPE="stanza">
<L>Vur&thorn;er. &thorn;er his on o&thorn;er put.</L>
<L>&THORN;at ne cume&thorn; neuer vndut.</L>
<L>Seoue duren &thorn;er beo&thorn; on.</L>
<L N="236">&THORN;e saulen for to under-fon.</L>
<L>Lyhtliche me may cume &thorn;er-inne.</L>
<L>Ac vp neuer for none gynne.</L>
<L>To so deop hit is wel neyh.
<PB REF="00000170.tif" N="154"></L>
<L N="240">As heouene is from &thorn;e eor&thorn;e heyh.<MILESTONE N="273:2" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;er-inne go&thorn; soulen. &thorn;ikkure inouh.</L>
<L>&THORN;an leues fallen of &thorn;e bouh.</L>
<L>&THORN;e put is hot at helle grunde.</L>
<L N="244">&THORN;ar-inne is monyon hungri hund.</L>
<L>Mo hundes &thorn;er-inne beo&thorn;.</L>
<L>&THORN;ane foweles vnder heouene fleo&thorn;.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e lyun &thorn;at wes so strong.</L>
<L N="248">&THORN;at al &thorn;e worlde vnderfong.</L>
<L>Er &thorn;at he was ibrouht a-dun.</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; cristes holy passyun.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="11" TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er-vnder is of iren a wal.</L>
<L N="252">&THORN;at is of saulen ifuld al.</L>
<L>On heom is mony yrene beond.</L>
<L>&THORN;at is hatture &thorn;ene &thorn;e brond.</L>
<L>&THORN;er-inne beo&thorn; &thorn;e saulen i-don.</L>
<L N="256">&THORN;at weren biheaueded o&thorn;er an-hon.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er &thorn;at so hedden isped.</L>
<L>&THORN;at l&eacute;yen hedden in &thorn;eouene bed.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er weren Mansed bi nome.</L>
<L N="260">For-&thorn;i heo habbe&thorn; godes grome.</L>
<L>Ich wile segge eu a so&thorn;.</L>
<L>Hwo so hit halt. god hit him do&thorn;.</L>
<L>Hit is iwriten on &thorn;e bok.</L>
<L N="264">For witnesse &thorn;er-of ich tok.</L>
<L>&THORN;eyh on hundred heueden iseten.</L>
<L>Seo&thorn;&thorn;e kaym wes bi-yeten.</L>
<L>And nyht and day heueden iwaked.</L>
<L N="268">And te&thorn; and tunge. of stel imaked.</L>
<L>And tolden of helle pyne &oacute;;</L>
<L>Yet &thorn;er beo&thorn; a &thorn;usend mo.<MILESTONE N="273b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Hwo se is wis beo ywar.</L>
<L N="272">&THORN;at his saule ne cume &thorn;ar.</L>
<L>Vor &thorn;eyh hi greden euer-mo</L>
<L>Ne helph heom wur&thorn; o slo.</L>
<L>Ac bidde we crist &thorn;at is vs buue.
<PB REF="00000171.tif" N="155"></L>
<L N="276">For his swete moder luue.</L>
<L>Leue vs suche werkes wurche.</L>
<L>And so anuren holy chireche.</L>
<L>Hwar-&thorn;urh we beon iborewe.</L>
<L N="280">And ibrouht vt of kare and seorewe.</L>
<L>Ki ces .xi. peynes escryuera.</L>
<L>Bon Auenture. ly auendra.</L>
<L>Hwo so wrot &thorn;es pynen elleuene.</L>
<L N="284">His soule mote cumme te heuene.</L>
<L>And pleye &thorn;er myd engles bryhte.</L>
<L>&THORN;er heo beo&thorn; in heuene lyhte.</L>
<L>And nabbe he neuer godes grome.</L>
<L N="288">For .Hug'. is his rihte nome</L>
<L>And he is curteys and hendy.</L>
<L>&THORN;i. god him lete wel endy.</L>
<TRAILER>Amen&mdash;eN. Expliciunt .xj. pene. Inferni. quas vidit Beatus Paulus.</TRAILER>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="20" TYPE="item">


<DIV2 TYPE="version"><PB REF="00000172.tif" N="156">
<HEAD>XX. Long Life. [<I>Cotton MS. Caligula A ix, leaf</I> 246.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>MON<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. Non.</NOTE> mai longe liues wene;</L>
<L>Ac ofte him lie&eth; &thorn;e wrench.</L>
<L>Feir weder turne&eth; ofte into reine;</L>
<L N="4">An wunderliche hit make&eth; his blench.</L>
<L>&THORN;aruore mon &thorn;u &thorn;e bi-&thorn;ench;</L>
<L>Al schal falewi &thorn;i grene;</L>
<L>Weilawei nis kin<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ne quene;</L>
<L N="8">&THORN;at ne schal drinche of dea&thorn;es drench.</L>
<L>Mon er &thorn;u falle of &thorn;i bench.</L>
<L>&THORN;ine sunne &thorn;u aquench.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nis non so strong ne sterch ne kene.</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;at mai ago dea&thorn;es wi&thorn;er-blench.</L>
<L>&YOGH;ung and olde, brihet<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> and schene.</L>
<L>Alle he riue&thorn; in one strench.</L>
<L>Fox and ferlich is his wren[c]h.</L>
<L N="16">Ne mai no mon &thorn;ar-to-&yogh;eines.</L>
<L>Weilawei &thorn;reting ne bene.</L>
<L>Mede. liste; ne leches drench.</L>
<L>Mon let sunne and lustes &thorn;ine.</L>
<L N="20">Wel &thorn;u do and wel &thorn;u &thorn;ench.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Do bi salemones rede.</L>
<L>Mon and &thorn;enne &thorn;u schald wel do.</L>
<L>Do ase he &thorn;e tahte and seide.</L>
<L N="24">&THORN;at &thorn;in endinge &thorn;e bringe&thorn; to.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne ne schal &thorn;u neuer mis-do.</L>
<L>Ac sore &thorn;u mi&yogh;t &thorn;e adrede.</L>
<L>Weilawei shuc<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> wene&eth; to lede.</L>
<L N="28">Long lif; and blisse under-fo.</L>
<L>Ac de&thorn; lute&thorn; in his scho,</L>
<L>Him stilliche to for-do.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">

<PB REF="00000174.tif" N="158">
<L>Mon hwi nultu &thorn;e bi-cnowe.</L>
<L N="32">Mon hwi nultu &thorn;e bi-seo.</L>
<L>Of fole ful&thorn;e &thorn;u art isowe.</L>
<L>Wormes fode &thorn;u schald beo.</L>
<L>Her nauestu blisse daies &thorn;reo.</L>
<L N="36">Ac &thorn;i lif al &thorn;u last ine wowe.</L>
<L>Weilawei. de&thorn; &thorn;e schal adun &thorn;rowe.</L>
<L>&THORN;er &thorn;u wenest he&yogh;est to steo.</L>
<L>Ine de&eth; schal &thorn;i lif endi.</L>
<L N="40">And ine wop al &thorn;i gleo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>World and weole &thorn;e bi-swike&eth;</L>
<L>Iwis heo beo&eth; &thorn;in ifo.</L>
<L>&YOGH;ef &thorn;e world wi&eth; weole &thorn;e slike&eth;.</L>
<L N="44">&THORN;at is for to do &thorn;e wo.<MILESTONE N="246b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;are-fore let lust ouer-go.</L>
<L>And eft-&yogh;ones hit &thorn;e like&eth;</L>
<L>Weilawei sore he him biswike&eth;</L>
<L N="48">&THORN;at for on stunde o&thorn;er two.</L>
<L>Wurche&thorn; him pine euer-mo.</L>
<L>Mon ne do &thorn;u nowt swo.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000173.tif" N="157">
<HEAD>XX. Long Life. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 252, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mon may longe lyues wene.</L>
<L>Ac ofte him lye&thorn; &thorn;e wrench.</L>
<L>Feyr weder turne&thorn; ofte in-to reyne.</L>
<L N="4">And wunderliche make&thorn; his blench.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-vore mon. &thorn;u &thorn;e by&thorn;ench.</L>
<L>Al schal falwy &thorn;i grene.</L>
<L>Waylaway. nys king ne quene.</L>
<L N="8">&THORN;at ne schal drynke of de&thorn;es drench.</L>
<L>Mon er &thorn;u falle of &thorn;i bench.</L>
<L>&THORN;yne sunne &thorn;u aquench.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nis non so strong. ne sterk. ne kene.</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;at may a-go de&thorn;es wy&thorn;er-blench.<MILESTONE N="253" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Yung and olde. briht and schene.</L>
<L>Alle he ryue&thorn; on o streng.</L>
<L>Fox and ferlych is his wrench.</L>
<L N="16">Ne may no mon &thorn;ar-to-yeynes.</L>
<L>Waylaway &thorn;reting ne bene.</L>
<L>Mede. liste. ne leches drench.</L>
<L>Mon let sunne and lustes &thorn;ine.</L>
<L N="20">Wel &thorn;u do and wel &thorn;u &thorn;ench.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Do bi salomones rede.</L>
<L>Mon. and &thorn;enne &thorn;u schalt wel do.</L>
<L>Do as he &thorn;e tauhte and seyde.</L>
<L N="24">&THORN;at &thorn;in endinge &thorn;e bringe&thorn; to.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne ne schaltu neuer mys-do.</L>
<L>Ac sore &thorn;u myht &thorn;e adrede.</L>
<L>Waylaway such wene&thorn; to lede.</L>
<L N="28">Long lif. and blysse vnder-fo.</L>
<L>Ac de&thorn; lute&thorn; in his scho.</L>
<L>Hym stilliche. to for-do.
<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="159"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Mon hwi nultu &thorn;e bi-knowe.</L>
<L N="32">Mon hwi nultu &thorn;e bi-seo.</L>
<L>Of fule ful&thorn;e &thorn;u art isowe.</L>
<L>Wurmes fode. &thorn;u schalt beo.</L>
<L>Her nauestu blisse dayes &thorn;re.</L>
<L N="36">Ac &thorn;i lif al &thorn;u last in wowe.</L>
<L>Weylawey de&thorn; &thorn;e schal a-dun &thorn;rowe.</L>
<L>&THORN;er &thorn;u wenest heyust to steo.</L>
<L>In de&thorn; schal &thorn;i lyf endi.</L>
<L N="40">And in wop al &thorn;i gleo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>World and weole. &thorn;e bi-swike&thorn;.</L>
<L>I-wis heo beo&thorn; &thorn;ine ifo.</L>
<L>If &thorn;e world wi&thorn; weole &thorn;e slyke&thorn;</L>
<L N="44">&THORN;at is for to do &thorn;e wo.</L>
<L>&THORN;are-fore. let lust ouer-go.</L>
<L>And eft hit &thorn;e like&thorn;.</L>
<L>Weylawey. sore he him bi-swike&thorn;.<MILESTONE N="253b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="48">&THORN;at for one stunde o&thorn;er two.</L>
<L>Wurche&thorn; him pyne. euer-mo.</L>
<L>Mon. ne do &thorn;u nouht swo.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>

<DIV1 TYPE="item" N="21">


<DIV2 TYPE="version"><PB REF="00000174.tif" N="158">
<HEAD>XXI. An Orison of our Lady. [<I>Cotton MS. Caligula A ix, leaf</I> 246, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>ON hire is al mi lif ilong;</L>
<L>Of hwam ich wule singe</L>
<L>And herien hire &thorn;er-among;</L>
<L N="4">Heo gon us bote bringe</L>
<L>Of helle pine &thorn;at is strong;</L>
<L>Heo brohte us blisse &thorn;at is long</L>
<L>Al &thorn;urh hire chil&eth;inge.</L>
<L N="8">Ich bidde hire one mi song.
<PB REF="00000176.tif" N="160"></L>
<L>Heo &yogh;eoue us god endinge.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah we don wrong.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;u art hele and lif and liht.</L>
<L N="12">And helpest al mon-kunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;u us hauest ful wel idi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;u &yogh;eue us weole and wunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;u brohtest dai and eve ni&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="16">Heo bro&yogh;te woht, &thorn;u bro&yogh;test ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;u almesse and heo sunne.</L>
<L>Bi-sih to me lauedi bri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Hwenne ich schal wende heonne.</L>
<L N="20">So wel &thorn;u miht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Al &thorn;is world schal ago.</L>
<L>Wi&eth; seorhe and wi&eth; sore.</L>
<L>And al &thorn;is lif we schule for-go.</L>
<L N="24">Ne of-&thorn;unche hit us so sore.</L>
<L>&THORN;is world nis butent<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ure ifo.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-fore ich &thorn;enche hirne at-go.</L>
<L>And do bi godes lore.</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;is liues blisse nis wur&eth; a slo.</L>
<L>Ich bidde god &thorn;in ore.</L>
<L>Nu and euere-mo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>To longe ich habbe sot i-beo.</L>
<L N="32">Wel sore ich me adrede.</L>
<L>Iluued ich habbe gomen and gleo.</L>
<L>And prude and feire wede.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at is dweole wel i seo.</L>
<L N="36">&THORN;ar-fore ich &thorn;enche sunne fleo.</L>
<L>And alle mine sot dede.</L>
<L>Ich bidde hire to me bi-seo.</L>
<L>And helpe me and rede:</L>
<L N="40">&THORN;at is so freo.
<PB REF="00000178.tif" N="162"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Agult ich habbe weilawei.</L>
<L>Sunful ich am an wrecche.</L>
<L>Awrec &thorn;e nu on me leuedi.</L>
<L N="44">Er de&thorn; me honne fecche.</L>
<L>Do nim &thorn;e wreche ich am redi.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er let me liuen and amendi.</L>
<L>&THORN;at no feond me ne drecche.</L>
<L N="48">For mine sunnes ich am sori.</L>
<L>Of &thorn;is world ich ne recche.</L>
<L>Leuedi, merci. AMen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="159">
<HEAD>XXI. An Orison of our Lady. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 253, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>ON hire is al my lif ilong.</L>
<L>Of hwam ich wille synge.</L>
<L>And heryen hire &thorn;er-&aacute;-mong.</L>
<L N="4">Heo gon vs bote brynge.</L>
<L>Of helle pyne &thorn;at is strong.</L>
<L>Heo brouhte vs blysse &thorn;at is long.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;ureh hire child&thorn;inge.</L>
<L N="8">Ich bidde hire on my song.
<PB REF="00000177.tif" N="161"></L>
<L>Heo yeue us god endynge.</L>
<L>&THORN;auh we don wrong.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;v eart hele. and lyf. and liht.</L>
<L N="12">And helpest al mon-kunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;u vs hauest ful wel i-diht.</L>
<L>&THORN;v yeue vs weole and wunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;u brouhtest day. and. Eue Nyht.</L>
<L N="16">He brouhte wo &thorn;u brouhtest ryht.</L>
<L>&THORN;u almesse and heo sunne.</L>
<L>Bi-syh to me leuedi bryht.</L>
<L>Hwenne ich schal wende heonne.</L>
<L N="20">So wel &thorn;u Myht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Al &thorn;es world schal a-go.</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>And al &thorn;is lyf [we] schulle&thorn; for-go.</L>
<L N="24">Ne of-&thorn;inche hit vs so sore.</L>
<L>&THORN;is world nys bute vre i-fo.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar-fore ich &thorn;enche hire at-go.</L>
<L>And do bi godes lore.</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;is lyues blysse. nys wur&thorn; al so.</L>
<L>Ich bidde god &thorn;in ore.</L>
<L>Nu and euer-mo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>To longe Ich habbe soth ibeo</L>
<L N="32">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="36"><NOTE PLACE="inline">[<I>The rest of this song is missing.</I>]</NOTE></L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="40">. . . . .
<PB REF="00000179.tif" N="163"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="44">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L N="48">. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
<L>. . . . .</L>
</LG>
