<DIV1 N="22" TYPE="item">
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000178.tif" N="162">
<HEAD>XXII. Doomsday. [<I>Cotton MS. Caligula A ix, leaf</I> 246, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne ich &thorn;enche of domes-dai.</L>
<L>Ful sore ime adrede.</L>
<L>&THORN;er schal after his [werk];</L>
<L N="4">euch mon fongen mede.</L>
<L>Ich habbe crist agult.</L>
<L>wi&eth; &thorn;o&yogh;tes and wi&eth; dede.</L>
<L>Lauerd crist godes sone.</L>
<L N="8">wat is me to rede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;at fur schal kumen in &thorn;is world;<MILESTONE N="247" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>On one sune-ni&yogh;te.</L>
<L>For-bernen al &thorn;is middelerd;</L>
<L N="12">so crist hit wolde di&yogh;te.</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e in &thorn;e water and in &thorn;at lond;</L>
<L>&thorn;e flures &thorn;at beo&thorn; brihte.</L>
<L>Iherd beo &thorn;u lauerd;</L>
<L N="16">so muchel be&thorn; &thorn;ine mihte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e engles in &thorn;e dai-red;</L>
<L>blewe&eth; heore beme.
<PB REF="00000180.tif" N="164"></L>
<L>&THORN;enne come&thorn; ure lauerd; crist</L>
<L N="20">his domes for to deme.</L>
<L>Ne helpe&eth; hit noht &thorn;enne;</L>
<L>to wepen ne to remen.</L>
<L>&THORN;at haue&eth; lutel idon;</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;at godd were icweme</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>From &thorn;at adam was ischapen;</L>
<L>to comen domes-dai.</L>
<L>Moni of &thorn;isse riche.</L>
<L N="28">&thorn;at wereden foh and grei.</L>
<L>An ride&thorn; uppe stede</L>
<L>and uppen palefrai.</L>
<L>Heo schulen atte dome.</L>
<L N="32">suggen weilawei.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne schulen heo now&eth;er fi&yogh;te</L>
<L>mid schelde ne mid spere.</L>
<L>Mid helme ne mid brunie.</L>
<L N="36">ne mid non o&thorn;er gere.</L>
<L>Ne schal &thorn;er nomon o&thorn;er.</L>
<L>mid wise wordes were.</L>
<L>Bute heore almesdede.</L>
<L N="40">heore ernde schal bere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Heo schulen iseon &thorn;e lauedi.</L>
<L>&thorn;at ihesu crist of-kende.</L>
<L>Bi-tweonen hire armes.</L>
<L N="44">sweteliche he wende.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wile &thorn;at we mihte.</L>
<L>to lute<NOTE PLACE="marg">Looks like <I>litte</I> in MS.</NOTE> we hire sende.</L>
<L>&THORN;at makede &thorn;e cwed</L>
<L N="48">so fule he us blende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Heo schul iseon &thorn;ene king</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;is world wrohte.
<PB REF="00000182.tif" N="166"></L>
<L>An uppon &thorn;e rode.</L>
<L N="52">Mid stronge pine abohte.</L>
<L>Adam and his ofspring.</L>
<L>in helle he heom sohte.</L>
<L>To bidden his milce.</L>
<L N="56">to late we beod bi-&thorn;ohte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er stonde&thorn; &thorn;e ri&yogh;twise.</L>
<L>on his ri&yogh;t honde.</L>
<L>An &thorn;e sunfule</L>
<L N="60">so ateliche heo stonde&thorn;.</L>
<L>Mid heore sunnen iwriten.</L>
<L>&thorn;at is so muchel schonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;er hit schulen alle iseon.</L>
<L N="64">al &thorn;at her weren a londe.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Wi&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;i&eth;.</NOTE> &thorn;e ri&yogh;twise</L>
<L>he speke&thorn; wordes swete.</L>
<L>Come&thorn; her mine freond.</L>
<L N="68">oure sunnes for to lete.</L>
<L>In mine fader boure.</L>
<L>ow is imaked sete.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ow schulen engles.</L>
<L N="72">ful sweteliche grete.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Wi&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. &thorn;i&eth;.</NOTE> &thorn;e sunfule.</L>
<L>also &yogh;e mahen ihere.</L>
<L>Go&eth; awariede gostes,</L>
<L N="76">feondes ifere.</L>
<L>In-to berninde fur.</L>
<L>of blisse &yogh;e beo&thorn; skere.</L>
<L>For &yogh;e owre sunnen.</L>
<L N="80">of &thorn;isse worlde bere.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Bidde we ure lauedi.</L>
<L>swetest alre &thorn;inge.
<PB REF="00000184.tif" N="168"></L>
<L>&THORN;at heo ure erende beore.</L>
<L N="84">to &thorn;en heuonkinge.</L>
<L>For his holi nome</L>
<L>and for hire herendinge.</L>
<L>&THORN;at heo ure sawle.</L>
<L N="88">to heouerige bringe.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>

<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000179.tif" N="163">
<HEAD>XXII. Doomsday. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 255.]</HEAD>
<HEAD>Incipit de die iudicii.</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne ich &thorn;enche of domes-day.</L>
<L>ful sore ich may adrede.</L>
<L>&THORN;er schal after his werk</L>
<L N="4">vych mon fongen mede.</L>
<L>Ich habbe crist agult.</L>
<L>wi&thorn; &thorn;ouhtes and wy&thorn; dede.</L>
<L>Louerd crist godes sune.</L>
<L N="8">hwat is me to rede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;at fur schal cumen in &thorn;is world.</L>
<L>on one sone-nyhte.</L>
<L>Vor-bernen al &thorn;is Middelerd.</L>
<L N="12">so crist hit wolde dihte.</L>
<L>Bo&thorn;e in watere. and in &thorn;e londe.</L>
<L>&thorn;e flures &thorn;at beo&thorn; brihte.</L>
<L>I-herd beo &thorn;u louerd.</L>
<L N="16">so muchel beo&thorn; &thorn;ine Mihte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e engles in &thorn;e daye-rewe.</L>
<L>blowe&thorn; heore b&eacute;me.
<PB REF="00000181.tif" N="165"></L>
<L>&THORN;enne cume&thorn; vre louerd. crist.</L>
<L N="20">his domes for to deme.</L>
<L>Ne helpe&thorn; hit nouht &thorn;enne.</L>
<L>to wepen ne to remen.</L>
<L>&THORN;at haue&thorn; lutel i-don.</L>
<L N="24">&thorn;at god were i-queme.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>From &thorn;at Adam wes i-schapen.</L>
<L>to come domes-day.</L>
<L>Monye of &thorn;isse riche.</L>
<L N="28">&thorn;at werede fouh and grey.</L>
<L>And ryden vppe stede</L>
<L>and uppon palefrey.</L>
<L>Heo schulle&thorn; at &thorn;e dome.</L>
<L N="32">suggen weylawey.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne schulle&thorn; heo nou&thorn;er vyhte.</L>
<L>myd schelde. ne myd sp&eacute;re.</L>
<L>Mid helme ne myd brunye.</L>
<L N="36">ne myd non o&thorn;er gere.</L>
<L>Ne schal &thorn;er no mon o&thorn;er.</L>
<L>myd wise wordes were.</L>
<L>Bute heore almes-dede.</L>
<L N="40">heore erynde schal b&eacute;re.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Heo schulle&thorn; i-seon &thorn;e lauedi.</L>
<L>&thorn;at ihesu crist of-kende.</L>
<L>Bi-twene hire armes.</L>
<L N="44">sweteliche he wende.</L>
<L>&THORN;e hwile &thorn;at we Mihte.<MILESTONE N="255b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>to lute we hire sende.</L>
<L>&THORN;at makede &thorn;e qued.</L>
<L N="48">so fule he vs blende.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Heo schule iseon &thorn;ene kyng.</L>
<L>&thorn;at al &thorn;is world wrouhte.
<PB REF="00000183.tif" N="167"></L>
<L>And vppe on &thorn;e rode.</L>
<L N="52">myd stronge pyne abouhte.</L>
<L>Adam and his ofsprung.</L>
<L>in helle he heom souhte.</L>
<L>To bidden his Milce.</L>
<L N="56">to late we beo&thorn; bi&thorn;ouhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;er stonde&thorn; &thorn;e ryh[t]wise.</L>
<L>on his riht honde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e sunfule.</L>
<L N="60">so atelyche stonde&thorn;.<NOTE PLACE="foot">A later hand adds: on &thorn;e lufthonde.</NOTE></L>
<L>Mid heore sunnen iwryten.</L>
<L>&thorn;at is so muchel<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. muches.</NOTE> schonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;er hit schullen y-seon. alle.</L>
<L N="64">&thorn;at er weren a londe.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Wy&thorn; &thorn;e rihtwise.</L>
<L>he speke&thorn; wordes swete.</L>
<L>Cume&thorn; her myne freond.</L>
<L N="68">eure sunnes for to lete.</L>
<L>In myne fader bure.</L>
<L>ou ys imaked s&eacute;te.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ou schulen engles.</L>
<L N="72">ful sweteliche gr&eacute;te.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Wy&thorn; &thorn;e sunfule.</L>
<L>al so we mawen y-h&eacute;re.</L>
<L>Go&thorn; awaryede gostes.</L>
<L N="76">feondes yuere.</L>
<L>In-to bernynde fur.</L>
<L>of lisse ye beo&thorn; skere.</L>
<L>For ye oure sunnen.</L>
<L N="80">of &thorn;isse worlde bere.<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. beten. A later hand has added: nolde here.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Bidde we vre lauedy.</L>
<L>swettust alle &thorn;inge.
<PB REF="00000185.tif" N="169"></L>
<L>&THORN;at heo vre erende bere.</L>
<L N="84">to &thorn;an heouene kinge.</L>
<L>or his holy nome.</L>
<L>and for hire erendynge.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he vre saule.</L>
<L N="88">to heueryche brynge.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="23" TYPE="item">
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000184.tif" N="168">
<HEAD>XXIII. Death. [<I>Cotton MS. Caligula A ix, leaf</I> 247.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihere&eth; of one &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &yogh;e ohen of &thorn;enche.</L>
<L>&YOGH;e &thorn;at werie&eth; riche schrud.</L>
<L N="4">and sitte&eth; on oure benche.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah me kneoli ou bi-uore.</L>
<L>and mid win schenche.</L>
<L>From &thorn;e dreorie dea&eth;.</L>
<L N="8">ne mai nomon at-blenche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&YOGH;e &thorn;at sittet i-schrud</L>
<L>wi&eth; skarlet and wi&eth; palle.</L>
<L>Wel so&thorn;e ti&thorn;inge</L>
<L N="12">Ich ou wile telle.<MILESTONE N="247b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;e feond &thorn;enche&eth; iwis.</L>
<L>&thorn;e sawle forto cwelle.</L>
<L>Ase we hit finde&thorn; iwriten.</L>
<L N="16">in &thorn;e goddspelle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah of one &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>we schule nime gome.</L>
<L>&THORN;at we weren poure.</L>
<L N="20">&thorn;a we hider come.</L>
<L>We hit here&eth; iwis.</L>
<L>swi&thorn;e ofte and i-lome.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sawle and &thorn;e licome.</L>
<L N="24">selde heo beo&thorn; isome.
<PB REF="00000186.tif" N="170"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne &thorn;at child bid iboren.</L>
<L>and on eor&thorn;e i-falle.</L>
<L>Nolde ich &yogh;euen enne peni.</L>
<L N="28">for his weden alle.</L>
<L>Ah seo&eth;&eth;en moni mon.</L>
<L>bi&yogh;et bores and halle.</L>
<L>For-hwi &thorn;e wrecche sawle</L>
<L N="32">schal in-to pine ualle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enche we on &thorn;e laste dai.</L>
<L>&thorn;at we schule heonne fare.</L>
<L>Vt of &thorn;isse worlde.</L>
<L N="36">wi&eth; pine and wi&eth; kare.</L>
<L>Al so we hider comen.</L>
<L>naked and bare.</L>
<L>And of<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. of.</NOTE> ure sunnen.</L>
<L N="40">&yogh;euen ondsweare.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nabbe no mon so muchel.</L>
<L>al hit wolle agon.</L>
<L>His lond and his hus</L>
<L N="44">and his hom.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sorie soule.</L>
<L>make&thorn; hire mon;</L>
<L>Iwis ne mai at-blenche</L>
<L N="48">ure neauer non.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enne &thorn;e latemest dai.</L>
<L>de&thorn; haue&eth; ibrouhit.</L>
<L>Bi-nime&eth; ure speche.</L>
<L N="52">ure siht and ure &thorn;oht.</L>
<L>And in euche lime</L>
<L>de&thorn; us haf&eth; &thorn;urh-soht.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne beo&eth; ure blisse.</L>
<L N="56">al iturnd to noht.
<PB REF="00000188.tif" N="172"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne mi&yogh;te no tunge tellen.</L>
<L>&thorn;at euer wes iboren.</L>
<L>&THORN;e stronge pine of helle.</L>
<L N="60">&thorn;ah he hedde isworen.</L>
<L>Er &thorn;e sawle and &thorn;e bodi</L>
<L>a two beon to-drehen.<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> to-droren.</NOTE></L>
<L>Bute crist &thorn;at lesede his folc.</L>
<L N="64">&thorn;at &thorn;er wes for-loren.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Anon so &thorn;e sawle.</L>
<L>bi&eth; ifaren ut.</L>
<L>Me nime&eth; &thorn;e licome.</L>
<L N="68">and preone&eth; in a clut.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wes so modi and so strong.</L>
<L>and so swi&thorn;e prud.</L>
<L>And wes iwoned to werien.</L>
<L N="72">moni a feir schrud.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nu li&eth; &thorn;e clei-clot.</L>
<L>al so &thorn;e ston.</L>
<L>And his freondes striue&eth;.</L>
<L N="76">to gripen his i-won.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sorie sowle</L>
<L>make&eth; hire mon.</L>
<L>Of alle hire erure freond.</L>
<L N="80">nu naf&eth; heo non.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enne sai&eth; &thorn;e sawle.</L>
<L>wi&eth; sorie chere.</L>
<L>Awai &thorn;u wrecche fole bali,</L>
<L N="84">nu &thorn;u list on bere.</L>
<L>Ich schal habben for &thorn;e</L>
<L>fendes to ifere.</L>
<L>Awai &thorn;at &thorn;u euere.</L>
<L N="88">to monne ischape were.
<PB REF="00000190.tif" N="174"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne schaltu neauer sitten.</L>
<L>on bolstre ne on benche.</L>
<L>Ne neuer in none halle.</L>
<L N="92">&thorn;er me uin schenche&eth;.</L>
<L>For &thorn;ine fule sunnen.</L>
<L>and for &thorn;in uni-wrenche.</L>
<L>Hi schal wrecche sawle</L>
<L N="96">to ateliche stenche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&eth; alle &thorn;ine frond.</L>
<L>&thorn;at faire &thorn;e bihete.</L>
<L>And feire &thorn;e igretten.</L>
<L N="100">bi weies and bi strete.</L>
<L>Nu heo wolle&eth; wrecche.</L>
<L>alle &thorn;e for-lete.</L>
<L>Nolden he hore-stonkes</L>
<L N="104">non nu &thorn;e imete.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&eth; &thorn;ine dihsches.</L>
<L>midd &thorn;ine swete sonde.</L>
<L>Hwer beo&thorn; &thorn;ine nappes.</L>
<L N="108">&thorn;at &thorn;e glide&thorn; to honde.</L>
<L>Hwer is &thorn;i bred and &thorn;in ale.</L>
<L>&thorn;i tunne and &thorn;ine stonde.</L>
<L>Nu &thorn;u schalt in &thorn;e putte.</L>
<L N="112">wunie wid &thorn;e wonde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Of me &thorn;u heuedest mi&yogh;te.</L>
<L>to don al &thorn;ine wille.</L>
<L>Euer &thorn;u were abuten.</L>
<L N="116">us bo for to spille.<MILESTONE N="248" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Nu &thorn;u schalt wrecche</L>
<L>liggen ful stille.</L>
<L>And ich schal &thorn;ine gultes.</L>
<L N="120">abuggen ful ille.
<PB REF="00000192.tif" N="176"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwi noldest &thorn;u mid crist.</L>
<L>maken us isahte.</L>
<L>Masse leten singe</L>
<L N="124">of &thorn;at he &thorn;e bi-tahte.</L>
<L>Euer &thorn;u were abuten</L>
<L>to echen &thorn;in ahte.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i we beo&eth; an ende</L>
<L N="128">bo&thorn;e bi-pahte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Yelde<NOTE PLACE="foot">The initial letter may be Y, &THORN;, or W, which are all of one shape in this MS. There is a dot over the y and w to dis|tinguish them from &thorn;, but it is not used with the large initial letters.</NOTE> wole me for &thorn;e</L>
<L>masse lete singe.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er in holi chirche.</L>
<L N="132">don ei offringe.</L>
<L>Me wule for &thorn;in ahte</L>
<L>make striuinge.</L>
<L>And pute &thorn;e wi&eth;-uten.</L>
<L N="136">of alle &thorn;ine &thorn;inge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Li awariede bali</L>
<L>&thorn;at neauer &thorn;u ne arise.</L>
<L>Hwenne ich &thorn;enche &thorn;e uppon;</L>
<L N="140">ful sore me mai agrise.</L>
<L>For ich schal bernen in fur.</L>
<L>and chiuerin in ise.</L>
<L>And euer beon in pinen</L>
<L N="144">a feole kunne wise.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nu schal &thorn;in halle.</L>
<L>Mid spade beon iwro&yogh;t.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schald &thorn;erinne.</L>
<L N="148">wrecche beon ibro&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Nu schulen &thorn;ine weden.</L>
<L>Alle beon iso&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Me wule swopen &thorn;in hus</L>
<L N="152">and ut mid &thorn;e swoft.
<PB REF="00000194.tif" N="178"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;i bur is sone ibuld.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u schald wunien inne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e rof &thorn;e firste.</L>
<L N="156">schal ligge o&thorn;ine chinne.</L>
<L>Nu &thorn;e sculen wormes.</L>
<L>wunien wi&eth;-inne.</L>
<L>Ne mai me heom vt driuen:</L>
<L N="160">wi&eth; nones kunnes ginne.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nu is afered of &thorn;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;i mei and &thorn;i mowe.</L>
<L>Alle heo were&eth; &thorn;e weden.</L>
<L N="164">&thorn;at er weren &thorn;in owe.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schald nu in eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>liggen ful lohe.</L>
<L>Wai hwi noldestu er.</L>
<L N="168">of &thorn;isse beon icnowe.<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. iouowe.</NOTE></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nu schal for-rotien</L>
<L>&thorn;ine te&eth; and &thorn;i tunge.</L>
<L>&THORN;i mahe and &thorn;i milte.</L>
<L N="172">&thorn;i liure and &thorn;i lunge.</L>
<L>And &thorn;i &thorn;rote-bolle</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u mide sunge.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schal in &thorn;e putte</L>
<L N="176">faste beon i&thorn;runge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&eth; &thorn;ine weines</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e leoue were.</L>
<L>Of alle &thorn;ine riche weden</L>
<L N="180">nu &thorn;u ard al skere.</L>
<L>Beo &thorn;u in &thorn;e putte</L>
<L>wormes ifere.</L>
<L>Hit bi&eth; sone of &thorn;e</L>
<L N="184">al so &thorn;u neauer nere.
<PB REF="00000196.tif" N="180"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Al &thorn;at ich hatede</L>
<L>hit &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;e ful god.</L>
<L>&THORN;at makede &thorn;e qued &thorn;at</L>
<L N="188">&thorn;at &thorn;e bi-stod.</L>
<L>Heuedest &thorn;u &thorn;i wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;u were al wod.</L>
<L>And ich am wrecche sawle</L>
<L N="192">ful sori-mod.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nu &thorn;u schald bileuen,</L>
<L>and icht<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> mot fare nede.</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;ine gultes</L>
<L N="196">fongon ischal mede.</L>
<L>&THORN;at is hunger and chelc</L>
<L>and furberninge glede.</L>
<L>And so me wule sathanas</L>
<L N="200">ful ateliche brede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>ICh am sori inoh.</L>
<L>bi dai and bi niht.</L>
<L>Ischal to &thorn;eostre stude.</L>
<L N="204">&thorn;er neauer ne kume&eth; liht.</L>
<L>&THORN;at<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> &thorn;ar.</NOTE> ischal i-mete</L>
<L>moni a ful wiht.</L>
<L>Ne schal ich neauer i-seo</L>
<L N="208">crist &thorn;at is so briht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN ful a bitter ba&eth;</L>
<L>ba&thorn;ien ich schal naked.</L>
<L>Of pisch and of bruneston</L>
<L N="212">wallinde is imaked.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is sathanas &thorn;e cwed</L>
<L>redi wi&eth; his rake.</L>
<L>And swo he me wule for-swolehen</L>
<L N="216">&thorn;e fur-berninde drake.
<PB REF="00000198.tif" N="182"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;ah al &thorn;at fur in &thorn;is world</L>
<L>to-gedere were ibroht.</L>
<L>A&yogh;eines &thorn;are hete</L>
<L N="220">nere hit al noht.</L>
<L>Wo is him aliue</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;er-inne is ibroht.</L>
<L>Awai &thorn;as ilke pine.</L>
<L N="224">&thorn;u hauest me bi-soht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwo isehe &thorn;ene cwed,<MILESTONE N="248b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>hu lodlich he beo.</L>
<L>Hornes on his heaued.</L>
<L N="228">hornes on his cneo.</L>
<L>Nis no &thorn;ing aliue</L>
<L>&thorn;at so ateliche beo.</L>
<L>Wo is heom ine helle;</L>
<L N="232">&thorn;et hine schule i-seo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He &yogh;eone&thorn; mid his mu&thorn;e</L>
<L>and stare&thorn; mid his e&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Of his neose-&thorn;urles</L>
<L N="236">cume&eth; &thorn;e rede leie.</L>
<L>&THORN;at fur springe&thorn; him vt.</L>
<L>of eueruche Breye.</L>
<L>He moste deie for care.</L>
<L N="240">hwase hine ise&yogh;e.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Also beo&eth; his e&yogh;e-puttes</L>
<L>ase a bru&thorn;en led.</L>
<L>&THORN;at fur springe&thorn; him of</L>
<L N="244">wunderliche red.</L>
<L>Ne mai no tunge telle</L>
<L>hu lodlich is &thorn;e cwed.</L>
<L>Hwase lokede him on</L>
<L N="248">for care he mi&yogh;te beo dead.
<PB REF="00000200.tif" N="184"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Holde we us clene</L>
<L>ut of hordom.</L>
<L>Masse leten singen,</L>
<L N="252">and almes-dede don.</L>
<L>And wi&eth; hali chirche</L>
<L>maken us i-som;</L>
<L>&THORN;enne<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. Wenne</NOTE> mohe we cwemen</L>
<L N="256">crist at &thorn;e dom.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e king &thorn;at al &thorn;is world scheop</L>
<L>&thorn;urh his holi mi&yogh;te.</L>
<L>Bi-wite vre sawle</L>
<L N="260">from &thorn;an fule wi&yogh;te.</L>
<L>And lete us hatie &thorn;at woh</L>
<L>and luuie &thorn;at ri&yogh;te.</L>
<L>And bringe ure sawle</L>
<L N="264">to heoueriche li&yogh;te. AMEN.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>

<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000185.tif" N="169">
<HEAD>XXIII. Death. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 255, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ihere&thorn; of one &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>&thorn;at ye owen of &thorn;enche.</L>
<L>Ye &thorn;at werye&thorn; &thorn;at riche schrud.</L>
<L N="4">and sytte&thorn; on eure benche.</L>
<L>&THORN;ah me kneoly ou by-uore.</L>
<L>and myd wyn schenche.</L>
<L>From &thorn;e dreorye de&thorn;.</L>
<L N="8">ne may no mon at-blenche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ye &thorn;at sytte&thorn; i-schrud.</L>
<L>myd skarlet and myd palle.</L>
<L>Wel so&thorn;e ty&thorn;inge.</L>
<L N="12">ich ou wile telle.</L>
<L>&THORN;e feond &thorn;enche&thorn; iwis.</L>
<L>&thorn;e saule for to quelle.</L>
<L>As we hit fynde&thorn; iwryten.</L>
<L N="16">in &thorn;e god-spelle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ah of one &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>we schulle nymen gome.</L>
<L>&THORN;at we weren poure.</L>
<L N="20">&thorn;o we hider come.</L>
<L>We hit ihere&thorn; iwis.<MILESTONE N="256" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>swi&thorn;e ofte and il&oacute;me.</L>
<L>&THORN;e saule and &thorn;e lycome.</L>
<L N="24">selde heo beo&thorn; isome.
<PB REF="00000187.tif" N="171"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwenne &thorn;at chyld bi&thorn; iboren.</L>
<L>and on eor&thorn;e ifalle.</L>
<L>Nolde ich yeuen enne peny.</L>
<L N="28">for his weden alle.</L>
<L>Ah seo&thorn;&thorn;en mony mon</L>
<L>by-yet bures and halle.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i [&thorn;e] wrecche saule</L>
<L N="32">schal in-to pyne falle.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enche we on &thorn;e laste day.</L>
<L>&thorn;at we schulle heonne fare.</L>
<L>Vt of &thorn;isse worlde.</L>
<L N="36">wi&thorn; pyne and wi&thorn; kare.</L>
<L>Al so we hider comen.</L>
<L>naked and bare.</L>
<L>And of vre sunnen</L>
<L N="40">yeuen onsware.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nabbe no mon so muchel.</L>
<L>al hit wile &aacute;-gon.</L>
<L>His lond and his ayhte.</L>
<L N="44">his hus. and his hom.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sorye saule.</L>
<L>make&thorn; hire mon.</L>
<L>Iwis ne may at-blenche</L>
<L N="48">vre neuer n&oacute;n.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enne &thorn;e latemeste day.</L>
<L>de&thorn; haue&thorn; ibrouht.</L>
<L>Bi-nyme&thorn; vre speche.</L>
<L N="52">vre syhte. and &thorn;ouht.</L>
<L>And in vyche lyme.</L>
<L>de&thorn; vs haue&thorn; &thorn;ureh-souht.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne beo&thorn; vre blisse.</L>
<L N="56">al i-turnd to nouht.
<PB REF="00000189.tif" N="173"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne myhte no tunge telle.</L>
<L>&thorn;at euer wes ibore.</L>
<L>&THORN;e stronge pyne of helle.</L>
<L N="60">&thorn;auh he hedde iswore.</L>
<L>Er &thorn;e saule and &thorn;et body</L>
<L>a two beon to-drore.</L>
<L>Bute crist &thorn;at lesede his folk.</L>
<L N="64">&thorn;at &thorn;er wes for-loren.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>An&oacute;n so &thorn;e saule.</L>
<L>bi&thorn; i-faren vt.</L>
<L>Me nyme&thorn; &thorn;e lycome.</L>
<L N="68">and preone&thorn; in a clut.</L>
<L>&THORN;at wes so mody and so strong.</L>
<L>and so swy&thorn;e prud.</L>
<L>And wes iwuned to weryen.</L>
<L N="72">mony a veyr schrud.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv li&thorn; &thorn;e cley-clot.</L>
<L>al so &thorn;e ston.</L>
<L>And his freondes stryue&thorn;.</L>
<L N="76">to gripen his iwon.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sorie saule.</L>
<L>make&thorn; hyre mon.</L>
<L>Of alle hire erore freond.</L>
<L N="80">nv naue&thorn; heo non.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;enne sey&thorn; &thorn;e saule.</L>
<L>wi&thorn; sorie chere.</L>
<L>Away &thorn;u wrecche fole baly.</L>
<L N="84">nv &thorn;u lyst on bere.</L>
<L>Ich schal habbe for &thorn;e.<MILESTONE N="256b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>feondes to i-vere.</L>
<L>Away &thorn;at &thorn;u eure.</L>
<L N="88">to monne ischape were.
<PB REF="00000191.tif" N="175"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ne schaltu neuer sytten.</L>
<L>on bolstre ne on benche.</L>
<L>Ne neuer in none halle.</L>
<L N="92">&thorn;ar me wyn schenche.</L>
<L>For &thorn;ine fule sunnen.</L>
<L>and for &thorn;in vnywrenche.</L>
<L>Hy schal &thorn;i wrecche saule.</L>
<L N="96">to atelyche stenche.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&thorn; alle &thorn;ine freond.</L>
<L>&thorn;at fayre &thorn;e bi-hehte.</L>
<L>And feyre &thorn;e igretten.</L>
<L N="100">bi weyes and bi strete.</L>
<L>Nv heo wulle&thorn; wrecche.</L>
<L>alle &thorn;e forlete.</L>
<L>Nolden heo non herestonkes.</L>
<L N="104">nv &thorn;e imete.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&thorn; &thorn;ine disches.</L>
<L>myd &thorn;ine swete sonde.</L>
<L>Hwer beo&thorn; &thorn;ine nappes.</L>
<L N="108">&thorn;at &thorn;e glyde to honde.</L>
<L>Hwer is &thorn;i bred and &thorn;in ale.</L>
<L>&thorn;i tunne and &thorn;i stonde.</L>
<L>Nu &thorn;u schalt in &thorn;e putte.</L>
<L N="112">wunye myd &thorn;e wonde.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ofte &thorn;u heuedest Mihte.</L>
<L>to don al &thorn;ine wille.</L>
<L>Euer &thorn;u were abuten.</L>
<L N="116">vs bo uor to spille.</L>
<L>Nv &thorn;u schalt wrecche.</L>
<L>liggen ful stylle.</L>
<L>And ich schal &thorn;ine gultes.</L>
<L N="120">abuggen ful ille.
<PB REF="00000193.tif" N="177"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwi noldestu myd criste.</L>
<L>maken vs isauhte.</L>
<L>Massen lete synge.</L>
<L N="124">of &thorn;at he &thorn;e bitauhte.</L>
<L>Euer &thorn;u were abuten.</L>
<L>to echen &thorn;in ayhte.</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i we beo&thorn; an ende.</L>
<L N="128">bo&thorn;e bi-pauhte.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Selde wule me for &thorn;e.</L>
<L>masse lete singe.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er in holy chireche.</L>
<L N="132">don ey offringe.</L>
<L>Me wule for &thorn;in ayhte.</L>
<L>maken stryuynge.</L>
<L>And pute &thorn;e wi&thorn;-vten.</L>
<L N="136">of alle &thorn;ine &thorn;inge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ly awariede bodi.</L>
<L>&thorn;at neuer &thorn;u naryse.</L>
<L>Hwenne ich &thorn;enche [&thorn;e] vp-on.</L>
<L N="140">ful sore me may agryse.</L>
<L>For ich schal bernen in fur.</L>
<L>and chyueren in yse.</L>
<L>And euer beon in pynen.</L>
<L N="144">a feole kunne wise.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv schal &thorn;in halle.</L>
<L>myd spade beon i-wrouht.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schalt &thorn;er-inne.</L>
<L N="148">wrecche beon ibrouht.</L>
<L>Nu schulle &thorn;ine weden.<MILESTONE N="257" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>alle beon isouht.</L>
<L>Me wule swopen &thorn;in hus.</L>
<L N="152">and vt myd &thorn;e swofte.
<PB REF="00000195.tif" N="179"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;i bur is sone ibuld.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u schalt wunyen inne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e rof and &thorn;e virste.</L>
<L N="156">schal ligge on &thorn;ine chynne.</L>
<L>Nu &thorn;e schulle wurmes</L>
<L>wunyen wi&thorn;-inne.</L>
<L>Ne may me heom vt dryuen.</L>
<L N="160">myd nones kunnes gynne.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv is aferd of &thorn;e.</L>
<L>&thorn;i mey and &thorn;i mowe.</L>
<L>Alle heo were&thorn; &thorn;e weden.</L>
<L N="164">&thorn;at er weren &thorn;in owe.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schalt nv in eor&thorn;e.</L>
<L>liggen ful lowe.</L>
<L>Way hwi noldestu her.</L>
<L N="168">of &thorn;isse beon iknowe.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv schal for-rotyen.</L>
<L>&thorn;ine te&thorn; and &thorn;i tunge.</L>
<L>&THORN;i Mawe and &thorn;i Milte.</L>
<L N="172">&thorn;i lyure. and &thorn;i lunge.</L>
<L>And &thorn;i &thorn;rotebolle.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;u Mide sunge.</L>
<L>And &thorn;u schalt in &thorn;e putte.</L>
<L N="176">vaste beon i&thorn;runge.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwer beo&thorn; &thorn;ine &thorn;eynes.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;e leoue were.</L>
<L>Of alle &thorn;ine riche weden.</L>
<L N="180">nv &thorn;u art al skere.</L>
<L>Beo &thorn;u in &thorn;e putte.</L>
<L>wrmes if&eacute;re.</L>
<L>Hit bi&thorn; sone of &thorn;e.</L>
<L N="184">al so &thorn;u neuer nere.
<PB REF="00000197.tif" N="181"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Al &thorn;at ich hatede.</L>
<L>hit &thorn;uhte &thorn;e ful god.</L>
<L>&THORN;at makede &thorn;e qued.</L>
<L N="188">&thorn;at &thorn;e bi-stod.</L>
<L>Heuedestu &thorn;i wille.</L>
<L>&thorn;u were al wod.</L>
<L>And ich am wrecche saule.</L>
<L N="192">ful sori-mod.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Nv &thorn;u schalt by-leuen.</L>
<L>and ich mot fare nede.</L>
<L>For alle &thorn;ine gultes.</L>
<L N="196">fongen i schal mede.</L>
<L>&THORN;at is hunger and chele</L>
<L>and fur-bernynde glede.</L>
<L>And so me wule sathanas.</L>
<L N="200">ful atelyche brede.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ich am sori i-nouh.</L>
<L>bi day and bi nyht</L>
<L>Ich schal to &thorn;estre stude.</L>
<L N="204">&thorn;er neuer ne cume&thorn; liht.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ich schal imete</L>
<L>mony o ful wiht.</L>
<L>Ne schal ich neuer i-seo.</L>
<L N="208">crist &thorn;at is so bryht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>IN a bytter ba&thorn;.</L>
<L>ich schal ba&thorn;e naked.</L>
<L>Of pych and of brunston.</L>
<L N="212">wallynde is i-maked.</L>
<L>&THORN;er is sathanas &thorn;e qued.<MILESTONE N="257b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>redi wy&thorn; his rake.</L>
<L>And so me wile for-swolewe</L>
<L N="216">&thorn;e furbernynde drake.
<PB REF="00000199.tif" N="183"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;ah al &thorn;at fur in &thorn;is world.</L>
<L>to-gedere were ibrouht.</L>
<L>Ayeynes &thorn;are hete.</L>
<L N="220">nere hit al nouht.</L>
<L>Wo is hym alyue.</L>
<L>&thorn;at &thorn;er-inne is ibrouht.</L>
<L>Away. &thorn;eos ilke pyne.</L>
<L N="224">&thorn;u hauest me by-souht.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwo iseye &thorn;ene qued.</L>
<L>hw lodlich heo beo.</L>
<L>Hornes on his heued.</L>
<L N="228">hornes. on his kneo.</L>
<L>Nis no &thorn;ing alyue.</L>
<L>&thorn;at so atelich beo.</L>
<L>Wo is heom in helle.</L>
<L N="232">&thorn;at hine schulle&thorn; i-seo.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>He yone&thorn; myd his mu&thorn;e.</L>
<L>and stare&thorn; myd his eye.</L>
<L>Of his neosturles cume&thorn;.</L>
<L N="236">&thorn;e rede leye.</L>
<L>&THORN;at fur springe&thorn; him vt.</L>
<L>of euervyche breye.</L>
<L>He moste deye for kare.</L>
<L N="240">hwo so hine iseye.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Al so beo&thorn; his eye-puttes</L>
<L>as a [colput dup ant gret].<NOTE PLACE="marg">In a later hand.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;at fur springe&thorn; him of.</L>
<L N="244">wunderliche red.</L>
<L>Ne may no tunge telle.</L>
<L>hw lodlich is &thorn;e qued.</L>
<L>Hwo so lokede him on.</L>
<L N="248">for kare he Mihte beo ded.
<PB REF="00000201.tif" N="185"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Holde we vs clene.</L>
<L>vt of hordom.</L>
<L>Masses leten singe.</L>
<L N="252">and almes-dede don.</L>
<L>And wi&thorn; holy chireche.</L>
<L>maken vs i-som.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne muwe we quemen.</L>
<L N="256">crist at &thorn;e dom.</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e kyng &thorn;at al &thorn;is world scop.</L>
<L>&thorn;urh his holy Mihte.</L>
<L>Biwite vre saule.</L>
<L N="260">from &thorn;an vuele wihte.</L>
<L>And lete vs hatye &thorn;at wouh.</L>
<L>and luuye &thorn;at ryhte.</L>
<L>And bringe vre saule.</L>
<L N="264">to heoueriche lyhte. Amen.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>


<DIV1 N="24" TYPE="item">
<DIV2 TYPE="version">

<PB REF="00000200.tif" N="184">
<HEAD>XXIV. Ten abuses. [<I>Cotton MS. Caligula A ix, leaf</I> 248, <I>back</I>.]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwan &thorn;u sixst on leode.</L>
<L>King &thorn;at is wilful.</L>
<L>And domesmon niminde.</L>
<L N="4">Proest &thorn;at is wilde.</L>
<L>Bischop slou.</L>
<L>Old mon lechur.</L>
<L>&YOGH;unch mon lie&yogh;er.</L>
<L N="8">Wimmon schomeles.</L>
<L>Child un-&thorn;eaud.</L>
<L>&THORN;ral vn-buxsum.</L>
<L>A&thorn;eling bri&thorn;eling.</L>
<L N="12">Lond wi&eth;-ute la&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Al so seide bede;</L>
<L>Wo &thorn;ere &thorn;eode.</L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 TYPE="version">
<HEAD>XXIV. Ten abuses. [<I>Jesus Coll. MS.</I> 29, <I>leaf</I> 257, <I>back.</I>]</HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Hwan &thorn;u sixst on<NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. vn.</NOTE> leode.</L>
<L>King &thorn;at is wilful.</L>
