<DIV1 N="2" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000225.tif" N="209">

<PB REF="00000226.tif" N="210">
<HEAD>APPENDIX II. The xi Pains of Hell. [<I>Douce MS.</I> 302, <I>fol.</I> 17, <I>col.</I> 1.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>Incipit narracio quo michel duxit paulum ad infer|num: Interogandum est quis primus rogauit vt anime haberent requiem In infernum, i.e. paulus apostolus et michael archangelus: Dies dominicus est dies electus.</HEAD>
<LG N="1" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>I.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;e sononday is godis oun chosyn day,</L>
<L>&THORN;e wyche angelis in heuen &thorn;ai worchipyn &thorn;ore.</L>
<L>Gret sorow and dole here &yogh;e may,</L>
<L N="4">Hou mychael and poule &thorn;ay went in fere</L>
<L>To se what payns in hel were &thorn;er,</L>
<L>And &thorn;er &thorn;ay se a sorouful sy&yogh;t;</L>
<L>Herkyns to me now moy<NOTE PLACE="marg">u <I>altered to</I> y?</NOTE> &yogh;e here</L>
<L N="8">What payns to synful mon be dy&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Be-cause men nel not beleue,</L>
<L>&THORN;er-fore hit was godis oune wyl</L>
<L>&THORN;at mekel schuld led poule to hel</L>
<L N="12">To se &thorn;e payns, &thorn;e gret parel,</L>
<L>&THORN;e so&thorn; him-selue he my&yogh;t hit preue.
<PB REF="00000227.tif" N="211"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="2" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>II.</HEAD>
<L>&para; To-fore hel &yogh;atis furst &thorn;ai se &thorn;en</L>
<L>Mone an orebil brenyng tre,</L>
<L N="16">Hengyng ful of women and men,</L>
<L>&THORN;at was a sorouful sy&yogh;t to se;</L>
<L>Sum be &thorn;e hed, sum be &thorn;e tungus treuly,</L>
<L>Sum be &thorn;e fyt, sum be &thorn;e hond,</L>
<L N="20">Sum be &thorn;e membirs of here body,</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;ai han sunnyd with-in herthe leuand.</L>
<L>&THORN;e angel to poule he sayd &thorn;on:&mdash;</L>
<L>"&THORN;ese greuyn god ful greuously</L>
<L N="24">With al &thorn;e lymys of here body,</L>
<L>In lechery, slou&thorn;, and gloton&eacute;,</L>
<L>And dyed in det and dedl&eacute; syn."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="3" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>III.</HEAD>
<L>&para; With-yn &thorn;e &yogh;atis, wen &thorn;ay were passid,</L>
<L N="28">A meruelis fournes &thorn;er &thorn;ai se,</L>
<L>Mone a synful soule were &thorn;er-in cast;</L>
<L>.iiij. flamys o foyre stod on alye,</L>
<L>Of dyuers colours wonderfully;</L>
<L N="32">About &thorn;at fournes .vij. sorous &thorn;er were,</L>
<L>Gret snow, gret yse, gret cold gresl&eacute;,</L>
<L>Gret eddyrs, gret stenche, gret leyte, gret foyre.</L>
<L>&THORN;en &thorn;e angel sayd to poule treuly:&mdash;</L>
<L N="36">"&THORN;ese were proud men, raueners echon,</L>
<L>Extorcioners, monslers, robbid mone one;</L>
<L>Satisfaccion in er&thorn; &thorn;ai wold do non,</L>
<L>And deseredyn treu ayrs vnry&yogh;tfully:</L>
</LG>
<LG N="4" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>IV.</HEAD>
<L N="40">&para; Here &thorn;ai schal haue here payns &thorn;er-fore</L>
<L>Fore al &thorn;e synns &thorn;ai han don cursidly.</L>
<L>Sum wepin, sum waylin, sum gron ful sore,</L>
<L>Sum broudun, sum brennen, dissyryn to dye.</L>
<L N="44">Hou dredful is hel here may &yogh;e se,
<PB REF="00000228.tif" N="212"></L>
<L>In &thorn;e wyche is heuenes with-out gladnes,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e wyche is sorou of hert contenualy,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e wych of wepyng is gret plenteuesnes:</L>
<L N="48">In &thorn;e wyche &thorn;er is a brenyng wel,</L>
<L>A. &thorn;osand tymys an our about do&thorn; ren,</L>
<L>Vche day an angel fore smytis him &thorn;en,</L>
<L>A &thorn;ousand soulis &thorn;er-in &thorn;ai bren."</L>
<L N="52">"Alas," sayd poule, "here is gret deel!"</L>
</LG>
<LG N="5" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>V.</HEAD>
<L>&para; Affter poule se an orebbil flood,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e wyche mon&eacute; deuelis bestis were in fuyre;</L>
<L>As feschis in &thorn;e se about &thorn;ai &yogh;od,</L>
<L N="56">Deuowreng soulis as hit chep were;</L>
<L>A brygge was ouer &thorn;at gret water,</L>
<L>&THORN;at soulis passud ouer after here meryt.</L>
<L>Mon&eacute; an euyl moncion was &thorn;er ordent<MILESTONE N="17b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="60">As crist in &thorn;e gospel reherse het<NOTE PLACE="inter">"<I>Lygate faceculus ad comburandum similis cum similibus</I>"</NOTE></L>
<L>"Bynd bundels to-geder to be I-brent.</L>
<L>Bynd spousebrekers with awouters,</L>
<L>And ranegates with raueners,</L>
<L N="64">And cursid leuers with here cumpers,</L>
<L>And cast ham in &thorn;e fuyre with-out end."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="6" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>VI.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;er poule mon&eacute; soulis he se</L>
<L>&THORN;at were dround in &thorn;at watere;</L>
<L N="68">Sum stod vp to &thorn;e kne,</L>
<L>And sum to &thorn;e armes a lytil la&yogh;ghere,</L>
<L>And sum to &thorn;e lippis moche deppere,</L>
<L>And sum to &thorn;e brouys oche day were paynd.</L>
<L N="72">&THORN;en poule sykud and wept with gret doloure,</L>
<L>And at &thorn;e angel anon he fraynd</L>
<L>"What soulis ben &thorn;ese bene drownyd here."
<PB REF="00000229.tif" N="213"></L>
<L>"&THORN;o &thorn;at stodyn vp to &thorn;e kne</L>
<L N="76">Bakbidit here ne&yogh;tbore fore enuy,</L>
<L>And sklaundird hem in er&thorn; ful falseley,</L>
<L>&THORN;at loston here goodis hir lyues y-fere;</L>
</LG>
<LG N="7" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>VII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; And &thorn;o &thorn;at stodin vp to &thorn;e armes</L>
<L N="80">Weron spouse-brekers and leuyd in lechory;</L>
<L>And &thorn;o &thorn;at stod vp to &thorn;e leppis</L>
<L>Be &thorn;e seruys of god &thorn;ai set no&yogh;t by,</L>
<L>And did no reuerens to cristis body,</L>
<L N="84">In hole cherche were euer changilyng</L>
<L>And sayd here prayers vndeuoutly,</L>
<L>And let o&thorn;er men of mas hereng,</L>
<L>Herefore &thorn;ai haue passyng payn;</L>
<L N="88">And &thorn;o &thorn;at stod vp to &thorn;e elbow</L>
<L>At here ne&yogh;tbors harmes &thorn;ay low,</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &thorn;ai ferd wel her hertis hit slow,</L>
<L>And of here losse were glad and fayne.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="8" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>VIII.</HEAD>
<L N="92">&para; Hol&eacute; cherche is a house of prayere,</L>
<L>&THORN;e &yogh;at of heuen crist do&thorn; hit calle,</L>
<L>To worchip &thorn;er-in our saueour;</L>
<L>What-euer &thorn;ou askis &thorn;er haue &thorn;ou schal,</L>
<L N="96">&YOGH;if &thorn;at &yogh;e bene in charet&eacute; alle,</L>
<L>And serue &yogh;our god in loue and dred,</L>
<L>No myschif on &thorn;em hit schal falle,</L>
<L>In al &yogh;our werkis wel schul &yogh;e spede.</L>
<L N="100">A synful mon here-of haue mynd</L>
<L>In hol&eacute; cherche no&thorn;yng &thorn;ou say,</L>
<L>Bot with hole prayers to god &yogh;e pray;</L>
<L>He grawnt &yogh;oue grace, bo&thorn; ny&yogh;t and day,</L>
<L N="104">Him to serue &thorn;at al &yogh;ou send."
<PB REF="00000230.tif" N="214"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="9" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>IX.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en poule wept and sayd, in good so&thorn;nes,</L>
<L>"Wo is him to &thorn;ese payns ben ordent."</L>
<L>&THORN;en he se a plase of gret darknes,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e wyche men and wemen wern in gret turment,</L>
<L N="109">&THORN;at etyn here tongis hereto rent.</L>
<L>&THORN;en &thorn;e angel sayd to poule treuly&mdash;</L>
<L>"&THORN;ese were makers of mon&eacute; with cursid entent,</L>
<L N="112">With wrong mokerers false mesurs and vsere,</L>
<L>&THORN;er-fore wo &thorn;ai etin here tung,</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;ai foreswere ham wettanly,</L>
<L>On cristis passion haue no pet&eacute;</L>
<L N="116">To part with &thorn;e pore &thorn;at were nede,</L>
<L>Bot holdun hit fast &thorn;ai geten with wrong."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="10" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>X.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en after poule a plase he se,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e wyche were mon&eacute; damselse blake,</L>
<L N="120">I-clo&thorn;id in blak al cresly,<NOTE PLACE="foot">? grisly</NOTE></L>
<L>In pych and brymston, fuyre and smoke;</L>
<L>Aboute here nekis were nedirs and snake,</L>
<L>Fore wickid angelus repreuyd hem &thorn;er,</L>
<L N="124">With horns of fyre here heedus to schake,</L>
<L>And went about hom with hedus bere,</L>
<L>And saydon to hom with carful cry,</L>
<L>"Cnow &yogh;e now &thorn;e sun of god,</L>
<L N="128">&THORN;at a&yogh;ayn bo&yogh;t &thorn;e word</L>
<L>&THORN;at &yogh;e han greuyd in dede and word,</L>
<L>And slayn his creatours, &yogh;our childer distrye?"</L>
</LG>
<LG N="11" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XI.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en poule he askid "what ben &thorn;ese."</L>
<L N="132">&THORN;e angel onswerd without tareyng,</L>
<L>"Hyle<NOTE PLACE="foot">? Hol&eacute;</NOTE> god &thorn;ese con displese,
<PB REF="00000231.tif" N="215"></L>
<L>And kept hem not chast to here wedyng,</L>
<L>And slowyn here childer in bur&thorn;-beryng,</L>
<L N="136">And cast ham to houndis in preu&eacute; place,</L>
<L>In watirs, in pittis, about drounyng,</L>
<L>And neuer wold shryue hem of &thorn;at trespase,</L>
<L>Fore dred of sklawnder and penans doyng;</L>
<L N="140">So &thorn;e fynd he con hem blynd,</L>
<L>With disperacion hem schame and schend,</L>
<L>Lest here mysdedis &thorn;ai wold amend</L>
<L>And bro&yogh;t hem ta euyl endyng."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="12" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XII.</HEAD>
<L N="144">&para; &THORN;en after poule he se moche more</L>
<L>Men and wemen on kamels rydyng,</L>
<L>Moch froyt &thorn;er was here face be-fore,</L>
<L>To ete &thorn;er-of was here lykyng,</L>
<L N="148">&THORN;ai my&yogh;t not hit touche fore no &thorn;yng.</L>
<L>&THORN;en &thorn;e angel to poule con say&mdash;</L>
<L>"&THORN;ese brekyn &thorn;e tymys of here fastyng,</L>
<L>And wold not fast &thorn;e good fryday</L>
<L N="152">&THORN;at crist sofyrd de&thorn; apon,</L>
<L>Bot wastin here goodis in glotone,</L>
<L>Fore fleschel&eacute; lust of here body;</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;ai wold not parte with &thorn;e pore nedy</L>
<L>&THORN;ai schil haue hongir and &thorn;rust were-euer &thorn;ai gon."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="13" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XIII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en after poule in plase he se,</L>
<L>A sorouful sy&yogh;t, a hore hold mon,</L>
<L>Be-twene iiij fyndis in turmentr&eacute;,</L>
<L N="160">And gryd and wept with ful gret mon.</L>
<L>&THORN;en poule he askid &thorn;e angel anon</L>
<L>What maner of mon hit my&yogh;t be.<MILESTONE N="18" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;e angel answerd him ful sone&mdash;</L>
<L N="164">"A neclygent mon fore-so&thorn; was he</L>
<L>And kept not obedyans he was bound to,
<PB REF="00000232.tif" N="216"></L>
<L>Ne leuyd not chast in his bod&eacute;,</L>
<L>In word, in dede, in &thorn;o&yogh;t treuly,</L>
<L N="168">Bot couetis prude, euer out of charyt&eacute;;</L>
<L>To al payne ent domysday he schal go."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="14" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XIV.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en poule he weppid with heue chere.</L>
<L>&THORN;e angel sayd, "why wepis &thorn;ou soo?</L>
<L N="172">&THORN;ou sest not &thorn;e gret payn &thorn;at be&thorn; here,</L>
<L>come on, with me now &thorn;ou schal goo."</L>
<L>he lad him to &thorn;e blak pit &thorn;o,</L>
<L>With vij. selys was selid treuly;</L>
<L N="176">&THORN;er-in was care, sorow, and wo,</L>
<L>Stenche and al maner turmentry.</L>
<L>"Stonde vttir poule," quod &thorn;e angel &thorn;en.</L>
<L>Anon he vnselid &thorn;e pit &thorn;ore,</L>
<L N="180">With a stynche gurd out arore,</L>
<L>Al &thorn;e payne hit passid be-fore;</L>
<L>Hit wold haue slayn al crystin men.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="15" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XV.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en poule he askid &thorn;e angel in hye,</L>
<L N="184">"What pepul in &thorn;is pit ben don?"</L>
<L>"&THORN;ese beleuid not in vergyn mary,</L>
<L>Ne treuly in cristis carnacione;</L>
<L>&THORN;ai be&thorn; vncristynd euerechon,</L>
<L N="188">And neuer resayuyd cristis body;</L>
<L>Al-&thorn;o in-to &thorn;at pet &thorn;ay gon,</L>
<L>Of hem schal neuer be memory</L>
<L>On him in heuen, to-fore godis son,</L>
<L N="192">Fore hit is godis wil specialy,</L>
<L>Of eretekis schal be no memor&eacute;,</L>
<L>Ne false cristin men, renegatis &thorn;at dyed curstly,</L>
<L>Of hom is no redempcion."
<PB REF="00000233.tif" N="217"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="16" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XVI.</HEAD>
<L N="196">&para; &THORN;en after poule forso&thorn; he se</L>
<L>In a wonderful depe plase,</L>
<L>As fro &thorn;e er&thorn; to heuen on hy,</L>
<L>Vche soule on o&thorn;er couchid &thorn;er was,</L>
<L N="200">For fader and moder &thorn;ai had dispisid alas!</L>
<L>Orebil wormys devouryd hem &thorn;ere.</L>
<L>&THORN;en poul he herd a dolful noyse,</L>
<L>As layte or &thorn;onder &thorn;at hit were;</L>
<L N="204">&THORN;en was he ware of a soule anon,</L>
<L>Be-twen .iiij. fendes borne he was;</L>
<L>He rored and cryd alas! alas!</L>
<L>&THORN;at euer his bod&eacute; con forth passe</L>
<L N="208">With-out schrift housil contricion!</L>
</LG>
<LG N="17" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XVII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;e angelis of god a&yogh;ayns him criud</L>
<L>"Alas wrechid soule what hast &thorn;ou done?"</L>
<L>In er&thorn; &thorn;e fyndis &thorn;em verefyd,</L>
<L N="212">Dispisid godis laus euerechon,</L>
<L>To-fore him &thorn;ai red his dedis anon,</L>
<L>And cast him in-to derkens deppist of alle.</L>
<L>Quod angel to poule "be-leue vche mon</L>
<L N="216">As &yogh;e do in erthe so haue &yogh;e schal;</L>
<L>He ha&thorn; fre choys to do good or elle,</L>
<L>Fore vche good dede rewardid schal be</L>
<L>In er&thorn;, or ellis on euen on hei,</L>
<L N="220">And vche cursid dede ponyschid truly</L>
<L>In er&thorn;, in purgatore, or ellis in hel,</L>
</LG>
<LG N="18" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XVIII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; For &thorn;is schal be here ponyschyng:&mdash;</L>
<L>Pride, couetyse, wrat[h], enuy,</L>
<L N="224">&THORN;ese be &thorn;e brondis in hel brenyng,</L>
<L>Lechore, slou&thorn;, and glotery;</L>
<L>&THORN;en disparacion of godis mercy,
<PB REF="00000234.tif" N="218"></L>
<L>Of al &thorn;e payns in hel hit is most,</L>
<L N="228">Fore &thorn;ai so&yogh;t no grace ne no mercy,</L>
<L>Bot synnud a&yogh;ayns &thorn;e hole gost;</L>
<L>&THORN;at sin schal neuer fore-&yogh;euen be,</L>
<L>To god hit is most hye trespace</L>
<L N="232">To mys-trost his mercy and grace;</L>
<L>So ded &thorn;at traytur, false iudas,</L>
<L>And dampned him-self perpetualy."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="19" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XIX.</HEAD>
<L>&para; Anon poule a ioyful sy&yogh;t gon se,</L>
<L N="236">A ry&yogh;tful soule angelis beryng,</L>
<L>&THORN;at oure was rauyschid sro his body,</L>
<L>Vp taward heuen &thorn;ai con him bryng.</L>
<L>&THORN;en poule herd a voyse, a heuenl&eacute; &thorn;yng,</L>
<L N="240">A &thorn;ousand angelis to-geder holy,</L>
<L>&THORN;at said and song in his heryng:&mdash;</L>
<L>"Be glad blesful soule perpetualy,</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;e wil of &thorn;i god &thorn;ou hast edon."</L>
<L N="244">&THORN;ai beryn hym vp be-fore oure lord.</L>
<L>&THORN;en mychael let him to gret cumford,</L>
<L>In ioy and blis to haue reward,</L>
<L>Laudes deo &thorn;ai song vcheon.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="20" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XX.</HEAD>
<L N="248">&para; &THORN;en sayd poule, with gret gladnes,</L>
<L>"Wele is ham to euen may go!"</L>
<L>&THORN;e angel answerd in good so&thorn;nes:&mdash;</L>
<L>"&THORN;ai schul haue wele, without wo,</L>
<L N="252">No tong con tel, ne hert &thorn;ynke &thorn;er-to;</L>
<L>&THORN;e lest ioy &thorn;at is in paradyse</L>
<L>In heuen bene a &thorn;ousand vnderde mo;</L>
<L>Was neuer clerke cou&thorn; ham deuyse</L>
<L N="256">&THORN;e lest ioy to mon god ha&thorn; ordend,</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;o ioys schul neuer sese,</L>
<L>Bot euer enduyre and euer encres,
<PB REF="00000235.tif" N="219"></L>
<L>And euer leue in rest and pese,</L>
<L N="260">&THORN;at ioy and blis schal neuer haue ende."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="21" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXI.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en al &thorn;e sorouful soulus in hel,</L>
<L>&THORN;at were &thorn;er-in turmentyng,</L>
<L>&THORN;ai crydyn "hol&eacute; archangel Mechael</L>
<L N="264">Haue mercy on vs in payne bydyng;</L>
<L>And &thorn;ou poul, belouyd with heuen kyng,</L>
<L>To &thorn;at lord for vs &thorn;ou pray!"</L>
<L>&THORN;en sayd &thorn;e angel loke with sore wepyng,</L>
<L N="268">"Prays with poule, &yogh;if &thorn;at &yogh;e may</L>
<L>Gete &yogh;ou grace of one merce."<MILESTONE N="18b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>When he had sayd &thorn;is word anon,</L>
<L>&THORN;ay wept and cryd out euerechon:&mdash;</L>
<L N="272">"A &thorn;e sun of dauid in heuen trone,</L>
<L>Haue merce on vs fore &thorn;i gret pet&eacute;!"</L>
</LG>
<LG N="22" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; A voyse fro heuen answerd a&yogh;ayn&mdash;</L>
<L>"What good dedes haue &yogh;e nov done,</L>
<L N="276">&YOGH;e did me to de&thorn; with passion and payn;</L>
<L>Hwy aske &yogh;e me now remyssioun?</L>
<L>I was crucifid on cros fore &yogh;ou al-on,</L>
<L>With spere and nayles y sched my blood,</L>
<L N="280">Of aysel and gal &yogh;e &yogh;euen me drenkyn,</L>
<L>When I was on-&thorn;erst hongyng on &thorn;e rode;</L>
<L>And I put my-self to &thorn;e de&thorn; fore &yogh;ow,</L>
<L>&THORN;at &yogh;e schul euer haue leuyd with me;</L>
<L N="284">Bot &yogh;e were proud, couetyse, ful of enuy,</L>
<L>And wold do no good dede, bot cursid treuly,</L>
<L>And false lyers in &yogh;our lyue as wel &yogh;e cnow."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="23" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXIII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en sore wepyng poul knelid adowne,</L>
<L N="288">And al &thorn;e angelis in heuen &thorn;er,
<PB REF="00000236.tif" N="220"></L>
<L>And prayd hyle to godis oune sun</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;e soulis in hel sum ryst haue &thorn;er.</L>
<L>Oure lorde he made hem &thorn;is honswere,&mdash;</L>
<L N="292">"&THORN;ro&yogh; &thorn;e besechyng of myn angelis alle,</L>
<L>And of poule myn apostil, leue and dere,</L>
<L>&THORN;is special grace graunt ham I schal,</L>
<L>Fro setter-day at non, y say treuly,</L>
<L N="296">And al &thorn;e fest of &thorn;e sununday</L>
<L>In-to &thorn;e fyrst our of monday,</L>
<L>In reuerens &thorn;at &yogh;e here-fore ham pray,</L>
<L>&THORN;ai schal haue rou and rest perpetualy."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="24" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXIV.</HEAD>
<L N="300">&para; &THORN;en al &thorn;e soulis in hel, with one steuen,</L>
<L>&THORN;ai cryd and sayd with gret gladnes&mdash;</L>
<L>"&THORN;e sun of god, on hi in heuen,</L>
<L>We bles &thorn;i grace and &thorn;i goodnes,</L>
<L N="304">&THORN;at &thorn;ou woldist, of &thorn;i wor&thorn;ines,</L>
<L>Graunt vs &thorn;i grace and &thorn;i mercy</L>
<L>Oure gret payns fore-to reles,</L>
<L>Vche sunday perpetualy;</L>
<L N="308">Here-fore we &thorn;onk &thorn;e lord of al,</L>
<L>Wo-so-euer wil halou &thorn;is sununday</L>
<L>Wele and worch it ful, as I &yogh;oue say,</L>
<L>With angelis of god in heuen fore ay,</L>
<L N="312">Ioy and blis &thorn;er haue &yogh;e schal."</L>
</LG>
<LG N="25" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXV.</HEAD>
<L>&para; &THORN;en poule askid &thorn;e angel anon&mdash;</L>
<L>"Houe mon&eacute; payns in hel &thorn;er be?"</L>
<L>&THORN;e angel answerd him ful sone&mdash;</L>
<L N="316">"iiij. Ml. a .C. and fourt&eacute;,</L>
<L>And hunder men &thorn;a&yogh; &thorn;er were truly</L>
<L>Fro &thorn;e bekyny[n]g of wor[l]d<NOTE PLACE="foot">'1' added in a later hand.</NOTE> ay spekyng,</L>
<L>And vche a .C. tungis had so&thorn;ly
<PB REF="00000237.tif" N="221"></L>
<L N="320">&THORN;ai my&yogh;t not tel &thorn;e payns in hel duryng,</L>
<L>Fore &thorn;ai may not be noumbyrd treuly."</L>
<L>Here-fore dere breder &thorn;at be&thorn; present,</L>
<L>&THORN;at heren &thorn;ese payns, &thorn;ese gret turment,</L>
<L N="324">Torne &yogh;ou to god omnipotent</L>
<L>&THORN;at we mow reyng with him in heuen perpetualy.</L>
</LG>
<LG N="26" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXVI.</HEAD>
<L>&para; Alas! &thorn;at euer one cristyn mon</L>
<L>Wil not haue &thorn;at mater in mynd!</L>
<L N="328">What schame, and chenchip, confucion</L>
<L>&THORN;ai schal haue &thorn;at seruen &thorn;e fynd,</L>
<L>&THORN;at here mysdedis &thorn;ai nyl not mend,</L>
<L>And fore-sake here synnus and be sory,</L>
<L N="332">And sen al day what chamful end</L>
<L>&THORN;ay haue &thorn;at leuyn here vnry&yogh;twysly;</L>
<L>To god &thorn;is is a he trespas,</L>
<L>&THORN;at neuer on be o&thorn;er ware wil be,</L>
<L N="336">And wra&thorn; here god wetyngly</L>
<L>&THORN;at dyud fore hom on rod tre,</L>
<L>&THORN;ai bene acursid syrs in thys case;</L>
</LG>
<LG N="27" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXVII.</HEAD>
<L>&para; Fore hel is not ordend fore ry&yogh;twyse mon,</L>
<L N="340">Bot fore hom &thorn;at seruen &thorn;e fynd,</L>
<L>No more &thorn;an is a preson of lyme and stone</L>
<L>Bot fore hom &thorn;e lawis offend.</L>
<L>Cursid dedis makis men al day eschend,</L>
<L N="344">And &thorn;effys<NOTE PLACE="foot">'&thorn;euys' originally.</NOTE> on galous on hye to hyng.</L>
<L>&THORN;er ry&yogh;twys men &thorn;ai han good end,</L>
<L>&THORN;at seruyn here god in here leuyng.</L>
<L>y pray &yogh;ou seris trest wele hereto,</L>
<L N="348">Fore he &thorn;at leuys here ry&yogh;twysly,</L>
<L>On what de&thorn; euer he dey,</L>
<L>His soule neuer paynd schal be,</L>
<L>Ne neuer after wit of wo:
<PB REF="00000238.tif" N="222"></L>
</LG>
<LG N="28" TYPE="stanza">
<HEAD>XXVIII.</HEAD>
<L N="352">&para; Meruel &yogh;e not of &thorn;is makyng,</L>
<L>y me excuse, hit is not I.</L>
<L>&THORN;us<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. &thorn;<SUP>s</SUP>.</NOTE> mychael lad powle, be goddis bedyng,</L>
<L>To se in hel &thorn;e turmentr&eacute;,</L>
<L N="356">Fore I cou&thorn; neuer bot hy foly;</L>
<L>God ha&thorn; me chastyst fore my leuyng,</L>
<L>I &thorn;onke my god my grace treuly</L>
<L>Of his gracious vesityng;</L>
<L N="360">Be-ware serys, I &yogh;ou pray,</L>
<L>And &yogh;our mysdedis loke &yogh;e amend</L>
<L>Be-tyme, lest &yogh;e be chamyd and schend,</L>
<L>fore al is good &thorn;at ha&thorn; good end</L>
<L N="364">&THORN;us counsels &yogh;oue &thorn;e blynd audlay.<NOTE PLACE="foot">John Audelay, the blind poet.</NOTE>
</L>
</LG>

</DIV2>
</DIV1>
<DIV1 N="3" TYPE="item"><PB REF="00000239.tif" N="223">
<HEAD>APPENDIX III. [<I>Vernon MS. fol.</I> 230, <I>col.</I> 3.]</HEAD>
<DIV2 TYPE="section">
<HEAD>&THORN;e visions of seynt poul wan he was rapt in-to paradys.<NOTE PLACE="head">[The full stop is that of the MS.]</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Lustne&thorn; lordynges. leof and dere,</L>
<L>&YOGH;e &thorn;at wolen. of &thorn;e sonday here:</L>
<L>&THORN;e sonday. a day hit is</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;at Angels and Archaungels. Ioyen I.-wis</L>
<L>More. in &thorn;at ilken day,</L>
<L>&THORN;en eny o&thorn;ur., as I. &thorn;e say.;</L>
<L>&THORN;en wol we. her-ate dwelle:</L>
<L N="8">Ho preyed furst rest. for soules in helle,</L>
<L>&THORN;at is to witen., I. sei &thorn;e so,</L>
<L>Poul. and Michel., Archaungel bo;</L>
<L>For god of his grete miht</L>
<L N="12">&THORN;e peynes of helle. put in heore siht:</L>
<L>Poul sayh. bi-foren helle-&yogh;ates</L>
<L>Brennynge tres. &thorn;at neuer slakes;</L>
<L>Mony on. for heore synne &thorn;onne</L>
<L N="16">Weore I.-pyned. and honged &thorn;er-onne,</L>
<L>Summe bi hondes. and bi feet &thorn;ere,</L>
<L>Summe bi &thorn;e her., summe bi &thorn;e ere,</L>
<L>Summe bi &thorn;e Armes., &thorn;at weore longe,</L>
<L N="20">And summe &thorn;er hengen. bi &thorn;e tonge:</L>
<L>&para; He sau&yogh; a caudren. brennynge at enes,</L>
<L>Of diuerse colours. wi&thorn; seue lemes;</L>
<L>And &thorn;er weore &thorn;ei. for heore synne</L>
<L N="24">Diuersliche. I.-pynet &thorn;er-Inne;
<PB REF="00000240.tif" N="224"></L>
<L>And seuen peynes. weoren &thorn;er also,</L>
<L>&THORN;at duden &thorn;e soules. muche wo:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e furste of snou&yogh;., &thorn;e secunde of ys,</L>
<L N="28">&THORN;e &thorn;ridde fuir., in alle wys,</L>
<L>&THORN;e Feor&thorn;e blod., as I. &thorn;e say,</L>
<L>&THORN;e Fyf&thorn;e Eddres. of foul aray,</L>
<L>&THORN;e sixte leyt., as mon may &thorn;ink,</L>
<L N="32">&para; &THORN;e seue&thorn;e peyne. hit was of stynk.</L>
<L>At &thorn;at penaunces. were &thorn;ei in cast,</L>
<L>Synful soules., and al for-&thorn;rast,</L>
<L>&THORN;e w&yogh;uche &thorn;at nolden., in no chaunce,</L>
<L N="36">For heore synnes. do no penaunce;</L>
<L>&THORN;er weore &thorn;ei turmented. in &thorn;o ledes,</L>
<L>And vche reseyued. aftur his deedes:</L>
<L>Summe wepten. and &yogh;elled &thorn;enne,</L>
<L N="40">Summe gouleden., and summe dude brenne;</L>
<L>&THORN;ei disireden. euere to dye,<MILESTONE N="230b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Hit miht not beo. wi&thorn;-outen ly&yogh;e,</L>
<L>For &thorn;e soule., wher so hit go,</L>
<L N="44">Schal neuer dyen. for weole nor wo;</L>
<L>&THORN;erfore. sore hit is to drede</L>
<L>&THORN;e places of helle. for wikked-hede:</L>
<L>In &thorn;e w&yogh;uche. &thorn;er is a whel brennynge,</L>
<L N="48">Wi&thorn; muche serwe. euer-lastynge;</L>
<L>Vndur &thorn;at wheol. is &thorn;er &thorn;ore</L>
<L>A &thorn;ousund grisly peynes. sore,</L>
<L>Fyue tymes. vche day to telle</L>
<L N="52">Beo turmented. wi&thorn; &thorn;e Angel of helle;</L>
<L>In vche of &thorn;o. fyue tymes</L>
<L>Ben A &thorn;ousund soules. turmented in pynes:</L>
<L>&para; Aftur &thorn;at. sayh he &thorn;er he stod</L>
<L N="56">A wondur orible. grisly flod;</L>
<L>And in &thorn;at flod. say he &thorn;ere</L>
<L>Mony deueles bestes. were;</L>
<L>As Fissches &thorn;ei were. in &thorn;at flod &thorn;o,</L>
<L N="60">Todus., Neddres., Snakes. mony mo;
<PB REF="00000241.tif" N="225"></L>
<L>And &thorn;e synful soules. in hi&yogh;</L>
<L>Eten. and gnowen. wi&thorn;-outen merci;</L>
<L>Of hem tok I. no more kep,</L>
<L N="64">But as a Lyun. do&thorn; of a schep</L>
<L>Ouer &thorn;at watur. he say&yogh; ligge</L>
<L>A wondur long. and an hei&yogh; brugge,</L>
<L>And ouer &thorn;at brugge. saf goon &thorn;en</L>
<L N="68">&THORN;e soules. of good rihtful men,</L>
<L>Wi&thorn;-outen harm. of word. or dede,</L>
<L>And also wi&thorn;-outen. eny drede:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e soules of synnes., as I. &thorn;e telle,</L>
<L N="72">Fallen doun &thorn;er. in pyne to dwelle,</L>
<L>&THORN;er to take. and resseyue so</L>
<L>As &thorn;ei on eor&thorn;e. deserueden to;</L>
<L>Be-war of &thorn;is., i sei beo-fore,</L>
<L N="76">As God seide in &thorn;e gospel &thorn;ore:<NOTE PLACE="inter"><I>Ligate per fasciculos ad comburendum</I></NOTE></L>
<L>Bynde&thorn; hem in knucchenus. for&thorn;i</L>
<L>"To brenne lyk. to licchi,</L>
<L>Spous-brekers. wi&thorn; lechours,</L>
<L N="80">Rauisschers. wi&thorn; rauisschours,</L>
<L>Wikked. wi&thorn; wikked. also,</L>
<L>For so schul &thorn;ei. to-gedere go;</L>
<L>For eueri creature. go schal</L>
<L N="84">Bi &thorn;at brugge., sum or Al,</L>
<L>And lasse or more. schal he be deruet</L>
<L>Er-aftur he ha&thorn;. heer deseruet:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Er sauh. &thorn;e goode mon. poule</L>
<L N="88">In &thorn;at pyne. moni diuerse soule,</L>
<L>Summe to &thorn;e kne. and summe to &thorn;e hipes,</L>
<L>Summe to &thorn;e nauel., summe to &thorn;e lippes;</L>
<L>And summe he sau&yogh; bi-suyled. as souwes</L>
<L N="92">In &thorn;at pyne. vp to &thorn;e brouwes,</L>
<L>And &thorn;ei weore turmented. euerlastyngly;</L>
<L>&THORN;ei wept and gouled. and weore sory:</L>
<L>&para; And Poules herte. was so sor,
<PB REF="00000242.tif" N="226"></L>
<L N="96">&THORN;at for serwe. he wepte &thorn;or,</L>
<L>And of &thorn;at Angel. asked he</L>
<L>Whi summe were &thorn;er. in-to &thorn;e kne:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e Angel seide. to him &thorn;en</L>
<L N="100">"Heo ben Bacbyters. of men,</L>
<L>&THORN;at in word. and dede., as I. &thorn;e say,</L>
<L>Hyndren heor euen cristen. &thorn;at &thorn;ei may;</L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;o. &thorn;at to &thorn;e nauel. &thorn;ou se</L>
<L N="104">Spous-brekers. and lechours &thorn;ei be,</L>
<L>&THORN;at aftur heore dedes. to vndurstonde</L>
<L>Nolde no penaunce. take on honde;</L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;o &thorn;at weren. up to &thorn;e lippes blake,</L>
<L N="108">Stryf. and Iangelyng. in chirche dude make,</L>
<L>Vche to o&thorn;ur. Iangled. wi&thorn; scorn,</L>
<L>To heere godus wordus. &thorn;ei han for-born;</L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;o &thorn;at weren. vp to &thorn;e bri&yogh;es</L>
<L N="112">In &thorn;at flod., Aboue &thorn;e ei&yogh;es,</L>
<L>&THORN;ulke weore glade. of &thorn;e mischeef</L>
<L>Of heore neih&yogh;ebors. and of heore greef:"</L>
<L>And Poul wepte. and seide &thorn;o,</L>
<L N="116">"Muche wo is hem. I.-come to,</L>
<L>&THORN;at so mony peynes. grymme</L>
<L>Ben ordeynt to. for heore synne:"</L>
<L>&para; Seynt Poul &thorn;o. bi-tornd his face</L>
<L N="120">And say&yogh; a-no&thorn;ur. derk place,</L>
<L>Moni Men. and wymmen. &thorn;er Amongus,</L>
<L>&THORN;at for-freten. heore owne tonges:</L>
<L>&para; And Poul asked. of him &thorn;ere</L>
<L N="124">What maner men. &thorn;at &thorn;ei were:</L>
<L>&THORN;e Aungel seide. to him ful sleih,</L>
<L>"&THORN;ei vsuden. Ocur. and vsuri,</L>
<L>Merciable. weore &thorn;ei nouht,</L>
<L N="128">&THORN;erfore hit schal. be dere a-bouht:"</L>
<L>And Poul sau&yogh; &thorn;enne. a-no&thorn;ur plas,</L>
<L>&THORN;at moni peynes. &thorn;er-in was;</L>
<L>&THORN;er he sauh. dispitous &thorn;ing,
<PB REF="00000243.tif" N="227"></L>
<L N="132">As Blake Maydens. in Blac clo&thorn;ing;</L>
<L>And &thorn;ei sodun. euerichon</L>
<L>In wellyng pich. and Brumston;</L>
<L>Brennyng dragouns. and serpentes i-fere</L>
<L N="136">Hongynge. Aboute heor nekkes were,</L>
<L>Gnawyng hem. to don hem schom,</L>
<L>To tere &thorn;e Flesch. from &thorn;e bon;</L>
<L>And &thorn;er weore. foure Angels to telle</L>
<L N="140">&THORN;at weoren of &thorn;e hous. of helle,</L>
<L>Brennynge hornes. hedde &thorn;ei on hed,</L>
<L>&THORN;ei hem turmented. and dude hem qued;</L>
<L>Faste &thorn;ei wente. &thorn;is pepul a-boute,</L>
<L N="144">Wi&thorn; moni turmentes. grete and stoute,</L>
<L>Seying to hem. as was heore wone,</L>
<L>"Knowe&thorn; &yogh;e &thorn;ei seide. godus sone,</L>
<L>&THORN;e w&yogh;uche. &thorn;at muche on &yogh;ou &thorn;ou&yogh;t</L>
<L N="148">Al &thorn;e world. whon he bou&yogh;t;</L>
<L>For &yogh;e nolde neuer. knowen him</L>
<L>&YOGH;e schullen han here. &thorn;eos pynes grym:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Poul &thorn;is asked. feire and wel,</L>
<L N="152">And &thorn;enne onswered. &thorn;e Aungel:</L>
<L>"&THORN;eos serued not chastit&eacute;,</L>
<L>Til tyme of heor weddynge. schulde be,</L>
<L>But lyuede. in heore lecherie,</L>
<L N="156">And heled heore children. and dude hem dye,</L>
<L>And &yogh;af hem to swyn. or to houndes,</L>
<L>Or drouned hem. In slodes groundes,</L>
<L>And schewed hem. to &thorn;e worldus degr&eacute;</L>
<L N="160">As &thorn;ei maydens. hedden i-be;</L>
<L>And in &thorn;is lyf. &thorn;ei lyueden &yogh;ore,</L>
<L>And duden no penaunce. &thorn;erfore":</L>
<L>&para; Aftur &thorn;is. he say&yogh; at ene</L>
<L N="164">Men. and. wymmen., moni and lene;</L>
<L>Lene &thorn;ei weore., wi&thorn;-outen flesche,</L>
<L>&THORN;ei soffred harde. and no&thorn;ing nessche;</L>
<L>Muche lay bi-foren hem. of Mete
<PB REF="00000244.tif" N="228"></L>
<L N="168">&THORN;at hem deynet not. of to ete,</L>
<L>&THORN;o weore &thorn;eose. &thorn;at weore not trewe,</L>
<L>And nolde not faste. &thorn;at hem was duwe,</L>
<L>And hedden. of mony metes de-deyn,</L>
<L N="172">But hit weore likerous. be certeyn:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;En sau&yogh; poul. a serw&yogh;ful siht,</L>
<L>And he loked &thorn;er. for&thorn; riht;</L>
<L>An Old mon sat. &thorn;er wepynge</L>
<L N="176">Bi-twene four deueles. foul &yogh;ellynge;</L>
<L>&para; Poul asked. what he was,</L>
<L>And &thorn;e Angel. seide in plas,</L>
<L>"He was Neclygent. a&yogh;eynes for bod,</L>
<L N="180">And kepte not. &thorn;e lawes of God;</L>
<L>He nas not chast. of bodi i-sou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Ne of herte., ne of his &thorn;ou&yogh;t,</L>
<L>But euer he was. Couetous,</L>
<L N="184">Proud of herte. and contrarius,</L>
<L>&THORN;er-of nolde he. him not schriue,</L>
<L>Ne do no penaunce. bi his lyue,</L>
<L>&THORN;erfore he schal. beo pyned ay,</L>
<L N="188">Wi&thorn;-outen Noumbre. til domus-day:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>POul wepte. and bi-gon to goule:</L>
<L>&THORN;e Angel seide. "whi wepustou, poule?</L>
<L>&YOGH;it say&yogh; &thorn;ou not., as I. &thorn;e telle,</L>
<L N="192">&THORN;e strengest peyne. &thorn;at is in helle:"</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e Angel him schewed., wi&thorn;-outen weoles,</L>
<L>A put a-seled. wi&thorn; seuen seles,</L>
<L>He bad him stonde bac. for &thorn;at &thorn;ing,</L>
<L N="196">&THORN;at he mihte sustene. &thorn;at stynk;</L>
<L>He opened &thorn;e Mou&thorn;. of &thorn;at put,</L>
<L>Hit stonk foule. w&yogh;on hit was vn-schut;</L>
<L>&THORN;e stynk &thorn;at com out. of &thorn;at plas</L>
<L N="200">Passed al &thorn;e peynes. and stinkes &thorn;er was:</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;en seide &thorn;at Angel. to bi ginne</L>
<L>"Hose come&thorn;. &thorn;is put wi&thorn;-Inne,</L>
<L>Bi-fore God. and vre ladi,</L>
<L N="204">Schal neuer of him. beo no merci:
<PB REF="00000245.tif" N="229"></L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>POul askede. "w&yogh;uche ben &thorn;o</L>
<L>&THORN;at schulen. to &thorn;is peyne go:"</L>
<L>He seide., "hose leeue&thorn; not. in wone</L>
<L N="208">&THORN;at Iesu crist., Godus sone,</L>
<L>Tok Flesch and blod. of &thorn;e virgine Marie,</L>
<L>And se&thorn;&thorn;e was boren. of hire bodye;</L>
<L>And also &thorn;ulke., I. telle hit &thorn;e,</L>
<L N="212">&THORN;at neuer wollen. Baptized be;</L>
<L>&THORN;ulke &thorn;at resseyue not. wor&thorn;ily</L>
<L>&THORN;e flesch. and blod. of godus bodi:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>POul loked. for&thorn;ur &thorn;en</L>
<L N="216">And sau&yogh; ful mony men. and wymmen,</L>
<L>Wormes. and serpentes. on hem seeten,</L>
<L>Euer as houndes. &thorn;ei on hem. freeten;</L>
<L>So mony soules. &thorn;er weore in hold,</L>
<L N="220">Vchon on o&thorn;ur. as schep in fold;</L>
<L>Hit was also dep. to nemene</L>
<L>As from &thorn;e eor&thorn;e. vp to heuene;</L>
<L>Of heore serwyng. was muche wondur,</L>
<L N="224">&THORN;ei made a noyse. as hit weore &thorn;undur:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>And &thorn;enne poul loked. touward heuene</L>
<L>And out of eor&thorn;e. he herde a steuene,</L>
<L>A synful soule. he sau&yogh; comynge</L>
<L N="228">Among seue deueles. waymentynge,</L>
<L>&THORN;e w&yogh;uche. &thorn;at same day for&thorn;i</L>
<L>Was i-taken. from &thorn;e bodi;</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e Angels of God., &thorn;at ben vr frendes,</L>
<L N="232">Cri&yogh;eden faste., to &thorn;e Fendes,</L>
<L>Sey&yogh;inge allas.! makynge. heore mon,</L>
<L>"What ha&thorn;. &thorn;at wrecched soule i-don?"</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;e Fendes seiden. verreyment&mdash;</L>
<L N="236">"He ha&thorn; se&yogh;en. his Iuggement,</L>
<L>He ha&thorn; ben muche. mys-Auyset,</L>
<L>Godus Comaundemens. he ha&thorn; dispyset;</L>
<L>In eor&thorn;e he lyued. in foly,</L>
<L N="240">And &thorn;er dude he. no remedi;</L>
<L>His owne chatre. ha&thorn; he rad<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>nota.</I></NOTE>
<PB REF="00000246.tif" N="230"></L>
<L>&THORN;at his synnes were. Inne I.-sprad;</L>
<L>And so for&thorn;. we telle &thorn;e</L>
<L N="244">His owne-self. &thorn;en Iugged he:"</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;en tok &thorn;e deueles. and him bounde,</L>
<L>And caste hym in-to &thorn;e derkeste grounde,</L>
<L>&THORN;er as was wepyng. wi&thorn; muche vnsee&thorn;e,</L>
<L N="248">Goulyng., And grisbatyng. of te&thorn;e;</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;En seide to Poul. &thorn;at Aungel</L>
<L>"Leeue &thorn;ou hit. and knowe hit wel,</L>
<L>So as Mon do&thorn;. in his lyuing,<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>nota.</I></NOTE></L>
<L N="252">So schal he haue. aftur his endyng;</L>
<L>Aftur &thorn;at &thorn;is was. for&thorn; so sent,</L>
<L>In wi&thorn; &thorn;e space. of a moment,</L>
<L>&para; Aungeles of heuene. sai&yogh; he come &thorn;on,</L>
<L N="256">Brouhten &thorn;e soule. of a Rihtful mon;</L>
<L>&THORN;er was Ioye., wi&thorn; loud steuene,</L>
<L>For so &thorn;ei beeren hit. in-to heuene;</L>
<L>Of A &thorn;ousund Angels. he herde &thorn;e vois,</L>
<L N="260">Ioynge. wi&thorn; a semely noys,</L>
<L>And seiden, "murie soule. blesset &thorn;ou be,</L>
<L>For euer mur&thorn;e. schal beo wi&thorn; &thorn;e;</L>
<L>&THORN;ou art i-blesset. of God in trone,</L>
<L N="264">&THORN;e wille of Ihesu. hastou done:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;En seide &thorn;e Angels. in heore sei&yogh;ing,</L>
<L>"Lede&thorn; hym vp. to-foren vr kyng,</L>
<L>Glad may he ben. of alle clerkes</L>
<L N="268">&THORN;at schal him-self. rede his goode werkes;</L>
<L>Aftur schal Mihel. lede him in hi&yogh;</L>
<L>To paradys. to o&thorn;ur holi:"</L>
<L>A Ioyful noyse. was hem Among</L>
<L N="272">Of Angels. and Archangeles. wi&thorn; song:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;Ei &thorn;at in peyne. bi-ne&thorn;en ly&yogh;e</L>
<L>Herden &thorn;is. and al hit sei&yogh;e;</L>
<L>&THORN;ei &yogh;elleden. wi&thorn; lodly cry,</L>
<L N="276">"Poul. Michael. on vs ha merci,</L>
<L>Prei for vs. wi&thorn; good a-cord
<PB REF="00000247.tif" N="231"></L>
<L>To vre god. and to vre lord:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;En seide &thorn;e Angel. to hem &thorn;o&mdash;</L>
<L N="280">"Weputh; Poul and I. wolen also,<MILESTONE N="231" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;at Almihti God., &thorn;at may best,</L>
<L>Send &yogh;ow. sum refuit. and sum rest;"</L>
<L>&para; And &thorn;eose. &thorn;at in peyne weore</L>
<L N="284">Cried on God. wi&thorn; delful beere;</L>
<L>Michael. and poul. also</L>
<L>And A legioun of Aungelus. mo:</L>
<L>&THORN;e soun of hem. was herd ful euene.</L>
<L N="288">Vp in-to &thorn;e Feor&thorn;e. heuene,</L>
<L>Sei&yogh;inge. "haue merci on hem</L>
<L>&THORN;e sone of God. and eke of mon:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>And &thorn;enne &thorn;ei. &thorn;e heuene seih</L>
<L N="292">Open A-non., ful sodeynly,</L>
<L>&THORN;e sone of god. com doun &thorn;o,</L>
<L>And herde hem preye. mony on mo,</L>
<L>&THORN;ei preieden alle. ful tenderli,</L>
<L N="296">"Haue merci on vs. sone of Daui":</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;e vois &thorn;enne. of vre heuene kyng</L>
<L>Ouer al &thorn;e peynes. was herd seying;</L>
<L>"What good ha &yogh;e don. herbifore,</L>
<L N="300">&THORN;at &yogh;e aske. reste. so sore;</L>
<L>I. was don on cros. for &yogh;ou with dere,</L>
<L>And smiten wi&thorn;. a ful scharp spere,</L>
<L>I.-nayled also. wi&thorn; nayles &thorn;ree,</L>
<L N="304">Eysel. and Galle. to drynke bode me;</L>
<L>I. &yogh;af my-self. for &yogh;ou to be,</L>
<L>For &yogh;e schulde ouer-come. wi&thorn; me;</L>
<L>Bote &yogh;e weore &thorn;eues. coueytous,</L>
<L N="308">Proude., and. wro&thorn;e., and envyous;</L>
<L>Good. neuer nolde &yogh;e. do non,</L>
<L>Ne to schrift. nolde &yogh;e not gon,</L>
<L>Ne do penaunce. for no &thorn;ing,</L>
<L N="312">Wi&thorn; Almus-dedes. ne wi&thorn; fastyng;</L>
<L>But &yogh;e weore ly&yogh;ers. al &yogh;or lyf,
<PB REF="00000248.tif" N="232"></L>
<L>And liueden euere. in serwe and strif:"</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;En kneled Poul. and Mihel</L>
<L N="316">And a Milioun Angeles. wel,</L>
<L>Bi-fore &thorn;e sone of God. to pray</L>
<L>&THORN;ei moste ha reste. &thorn;e sonenday;</L>
<L>&THORN;o weore &thorn;eos., as I. ow telle,</L>
<L N="320">&THORN;at weoren. in &thorn;e pynen of helle:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>&THORN;en seide vr lord. to hem in spelle,</L>
<L>For Poul. and also Michaelle,</L>
<L>And myn o&thorn;ure Angels. on hi&yogh;e,</L>
<L N="324">&THORN;at ben in heuene. so goode and tri&yogh;e,</L>
<L>And also. of my grete goodnesse,</L>
<L>Hem to ese. of heore distresse,</L>
<L>&THORN;is reste. I. &yogh;iue &yogh;ow. ful soon</L>
<L N="328">From &thorn;e seter-day. at Non,</L>
<L>Til &thorn;e secunde hour. beo cum</L>
<L>On &thorn;e Monenday., al and sum:</L>
</LG>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Anon &thorn;e soules. hedden &thorn;er rest,</L>
<L N="332">He &yogh;af hit hem. &thorn;at mihte best:</L>
<L>&THORN;e soules cri&yogh;ed. euerichon,</L>
<L>"Blesset beo &thorn;ou lord. sone of mon,</L>
<L>Lord. and God. of Dauid kuynde,</L>
<L N="336">&THORN;is rest bi &thorn;e. haue we in Muynde:"</L>
<L>&para; &THORN;erfore. whos halwe&thorn; wel. &thorn;e sonenday,</L>
<L>He schal ha part. of &thorn;e reste ay,</L>
<L>&THORN;at &thorn;e Angeles. in heuene</L>
<L N="340">Han &thorn;ere. wi&thorn; mylde steuene:</L>
<L>&para; Beo war. of &thorn;e serwe. and drede</L>
<L>And of &thorn;e peynes. &thorn;at we her rede,</L>
<L>And torne we. in alle wyse</L>
<L N="344">Vr lord to serue. &thorn;at hi&yogh;e Iustise;</L>
<L>Bi w&yogh;uche seruyse. we may come</L>
<L>To vre lord god. and wi&thorn; him wone:<NOTE PLACE="end">[In the MS. there follows:&mdash;<B>&THORN;e Pope trental.</B>]</NOTE></L>
</LG>
</DIV2>
</DIV1>
</BODY>
